get=\"_blank\">Read more about Summer Internship Opportunities</a>\r\n<h2>Donate to Summer Camp</h2>\r\n<h5><strong>Donate Funds<a href=\"https://14345.thankyou4caring.org/sslpage.aspx?pid=392\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-451\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/donate_button_purple.png\" alt=\"donate_button_purple\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a></strong></h5>\r\nSummer Adventure Camp is only made possible by private donations from the community. <a title=\"Donate\" href=\"http://ivsn.wpengine.com/donate/\">Donate online</a>.\r\n<h5><strong>Donate Items</strong></h5>\r\nDonations can be dropped off at any of IVSN’s family shelters. <a title=\"Where To Donate\" href=\"http://ivsn.wpengine.com/donate/donate-items/where-to-donate/\">View all donation locations</a>.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Swimsuits, goggles, flip flops</li>\r\n	<li>Towels, sunscreen, bug spray</li>\r\n	<li>Sports equipment, game balls, frisbees, jump rope</li>\r\n	<li>Bags, small backpacks</li>\r\n	<li>Reusable water bottles, first aid kits</li>\r\n	<li>Arts and crafts materials, markers, paper, washable paint</li>\r\n	<li>Glue sticks, children’s scissors, composition books, stickers</li>\r\n	<li>Water balloons, bubbles, chalk</li>\r\n	<li>Kites, parachutes, hula hoops, sand toys</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Read the Summer Camp Blog!</h2>\r\nCheck out the latest camp activities on our <a title=\"Summer Adventure Camp Blog\" href=\"http://ivsnsummercamp.wordpress.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Summer Camp blog</a>!','Summer Camp','','publish','closed','open','','summer-camp','','','2015-03-30 16:54:16','2015-03-30 23:54:16','',33,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?page_id=68',115,'page','',0),(70,2,'2013-09-20 16:52:25','2013-09-20 16:52:25','<h1><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-163\" src=\"http://ivsn.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ivsn_homeless_shelter_opportunity_services_center-320x212.jpg\" alt=\"ivsn_homeless_shelter_opportunity_services_center\" width=\"320\" height=\"212\" />Opportunity Services Center</h1>\r\n<div class=\"map alignright\">[flexiblemap width=\"320\" height=\"280\" showinfo=\"false\" address=\"33 Encina Avenue, Palo Alto, CA 94301\"]</div>\r\n<h2>IVSN’s Opportunity Services Center provides drop-in services for families and single adults.</h2>\r\n33 Encina Avenue\r\nPalo Alto, CA 94301\r\nPhone: (650) 853-8672\r\nHours: Mon-Fri, 8 am-4 pm\r\n<h2>Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><b>Emergency Rental &amp; Utility Assistance</b> for qualifying families and individuals, by appointment.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Bredt Family Center</b> for women, children, and families provides basic services, education, support, and children’s activities.  Open Monday-Friday, 9:00am-6:00pm.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Adult Services Center</b> for single men &amp; women provides basic services, case management, and assistance with CA ID/DLs. Open Monday-Friday, 8:00am-4:00pm.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Clothes Closet</b> distributes free clothing, sleeping bags, backpacks, shoes, winter gear, and toiletries. Open Wednesdays 11:00-am-1:00pm.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIn partnership with the Peninsula HealthCare Connection (PHC), a free on-site clinic provides confidential, compassionate healthcare by appointment. Call 650-853-0321. Open Mon – Fri, 9 am – 4 pm. PHC clinic offers:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Internal Medicine</li>\r\n	<li>Family Practice &amp; Pediatric Care</li>\r\n	<li>Mental Health Care</li>\r\n	<li>SSI/Disability Application</li>\r\n	<li>Case Management</li>\r\n	<li>Supportive Health Service</li>\r\n	<li>For more information, visit <a href=\"http://www.peninsulahcc.org/\" target=\"_blank\">www.peninsulahcc.org</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>How You Can Help</h2>\r\n<a title=\"Donate\" href=\"http://ivsn.wpengine.com/donate/\"><strong>Donate</strong></a>: IVSN’s services are only made possible through generous financial support from the community year-round. Your gift ensures that we may continue to provide housing and supportive services to thousands of homeless children and adults.\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Volunteer\" href=\"http://ivsn.wpengine.com/volunteer/\"><strong>Volunteer</strong></a>: IVSN relies on the generous time and talent of over 18,000 volunteers annually. Every person has volunteer skills to offer, such as teaching workshops, tutoring students, organizing donations, preparing meals, and much more.\r\n<h2>Donation Wish List</h2>\r\n<strong>Gift Certificates</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Safeway, Trader Joe’s, Costco</li>\r\n	<li>Target, K-Mart, Walgreens, CVS Pharmacy</li>\r\n	<li>Gas stations</li>\r\n	<li>Barbers, salons (for interview preparation)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Children/Baby Supplies</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Diapers, wipes, bibs, formula</li>\r\n	<li>Backpacks, school supplies</li>\r\n	<li>Arts &amp; crafts materials</li>\r\n	<li>New toys and games, sports equipment</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Clothing &amp; Accessories</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Men’s and women’s clothing</li>\r\n	<li>Adult business-attire, plus-size clothing, maternity</li>\r\n	<li><b>NEW ONLY</b> underwear, socks &amp; pajamas</li>\r\n	<li>Sweaters, coats</li>\r\n	<li>Thermo pants, long johns (in winter)</li>\r\n	<li>Comfortable shoes, wool socks</li>\r\n	<li>Gloves, scarves, beanies, umbrellas, ponchos</li>\r\n	<li>Tote bags, duffle bags, purses</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Linens &amp; Bedding</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Sheets, blankets, comforters (gently used and clean)</li>\r\n	<li><b>NEW</b> <b>ONLY</b> pillows, pillowcases</li>\r\n	<li>Towels, washcloths</li>\r\n	<li>Sleeping bags, <b>NEW</b> plastic mattress covers</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Kitchen Items</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Dishware, silverware, cups, plates, bowls</li>\r\n	<li>Pots, pans, cooking utensils</li>\r\n	<li>Paper towels, napkins</li>\r\n	<li>Aluminum foil, plastic wrap, Ziploc bags</li>\r\n	<li>Toasters, coffee makers, microwaves, can openers</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Toiletries (NEW ONLY)</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Shampoo, conditioner, lotion</li>\r\n	<li>Body wash, soap bars</li>\r\n	<li>Toothbrushes, toothpaste</li>\r\n	<li>Razors, shaving cream, sun block</li>\r\n	<li>Cosmetic cases, make-up</li>\r\n	<li>Feminine hygiene products</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Cleaning Supplies</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>All-purpose cleaner, glass cleaner, bleach</li>\r\n	<li>Dishwashing soap, laundry detergent</li>\r\n	<li>Sponges, brushes, gloves, paper towels</li>\r\n	<li>Buckets, mops, brooms</li>\r\n	<li>Like-new vacuum cleaners, dust busters</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Household Items</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Trash cans &amp; liners</li>\r\n	<li>Table lamps, alarm clocks, flashlights, batteries</li>\r\n	<li>Extension cords, tool kits</li>\r\n	<li>Humidifiers, irons, ironing boards</li>\r\n	<li>Bike locks, light helmets, kneepads, wrist guards</li>\r\n</ul>','Opportunity Services Center','','publish','closed','open','','opportunity-services-center','','','2015-03-30 16:53:09','2015-03-30 23:53:09','',33,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?page_id=70',114,'page','',0),(73,2,'2013-09-20 16:54:19','2013-09-20 16:54:19',' ','','','publish','closed','open','','73','','','2015-09-02 20:59:37','2015-09-03 03:59:37','',33,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?p=73',8,'nav_menu_item','',0),(75,2,'2013-09-20 16:54:18','2013-09-20 16:54:18',' ','','','publish','closed','open','','75','','','2015-09-02 20:59:37','2015-09-03 03:59:37','',33,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?p=75',12,'nav_menu_item','',0),(76,2,'2013-09-20 16:54:18','2013-09-20 16:54:18',' ','','','publish','closed','open','','76','','','2015-09-02 20:59:37','2015-09-03 03:59:37','',33,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?p=76',10,'nav_menu_item','',0),(77,2,'2013-09-20 16:54:18','2013-09-20 16:54:18',' ','','','publish','closed','open','','77','','','2015-09-02 20:59:37','2015-09-03 03:59:37','',33,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?p=77',4,'nav_menu_item','',0),(78,2,'2013-09-20 16:54:18','2013-09-20 16:54:18',' ','','','publish','closed','open','','78','','','2015-09-02 20:59:37','2015-09-03 03:59:37','',33,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?p=78',5,'nav_menu_item','',0),(79,2,'2013-09-20 16:54:18','2013-09-20 16:54:18',' ','','','publish','closed','open','','79','','','2015-09-02 20:59:37','2015-09-03 03:59:37','',33,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?p=79',9,'nav_menu_item','',0),(80,2,'2013-09-20 17:01:22','2013-09-20 17:01:22','<h1><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-156\" src=\"http://ivsn.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ivsn_homeless_veteran_man-320x213.jpg\" alt=\"ivsn_homeless_veteran_man\" width=\"320\" height=\"213\" />Veterans Hoptel</h1>\r\nIVSN’s Veterans Hoptel provides 1-3 nights of shelter, along with case management and transportation, to low-income Veterans from out-of-town coming to receive medical care and/or assessment from the local Veterans hospital.<b></b>\r\n\r\nThe name “Hoptel” is play on the word “hotel”; a “hop” is a military term for a short stay.\r\n\r\nMany Veterans travel great distances to access world-class medical services at VA hospitals in Silicon Valley. With limited means, these Veterans cannot afford housing during their trip, and would be homeless without the assistance of the Hoptel program.\r\n\r\n<strong>Hoptel guests are provided:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Short term accommodations for 1-3 days in a safe, clean environment</li>\r\n	<li>Food and open kitchen</li>\r\n	<li>Access to laundry</li>\r\n	<li>Transportation assistance to medical appointments</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>For Hoptel Reservations, contact: </b>\r\n\r\nChristopher Lum, MSW, ACSW\r\n\r\n(650) 493-5000 ext 65456\r\n\r\n<b>For more info about the Hoptel, contact: </b>\r\n\r\nMariana Garcia at <a href=\"mailto:mgarcia@ivsn.org\">mgarcia@ivsn.org</a> or (650) 364-1150 ext. 511\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Veterans Hoptel','','publish','closed','open','','veterans-hoptel','','','2015-10-12 13:38:33','2015-10-12 20:38:33','',34,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?page_id=80',113,'page','',0),(81,2,'2013-09-20 17:02:08','2013-09-20 17:02:08','<h1><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-390\" src=\"http://ivsn.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/veteran-dad_crop-320x389.jpg\" alt=\"veteran dad_crop\" width=\"320\" height=\"389\" />Supportive Services for Veteran Families (SSVF)</h1>\r\nSupportive Services for Veteran Families (SSVF) is a housing assistance program established to prevent and end homelessness for Veteran families and single adults in San Mateo County. The SSVF program is co-managed by InnVision Shelter Network and Samaritan House.\r\n<h2>SSVF services for Veterans who are homeless, or at risk of homelessness include:</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Move-in costs, such as:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Security deposit</li>\r\n	<li>First month’s rent</li>\r\n	<li>Utility deposit</li>\r\n	<li>Moving expenses</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>Possible short-term rent subsidy</li>\r\n	<li>Case management</li>\r\n	<li>Information and referrals</li>\r\n	<li>Auto repair</li>\r\n	<li>Transportation assistance</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Eligibility</h2>\r\nTo qualify for SSVF assistance, clients must be:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Veterans who have served at least 24 months of active duty, excluding dishonorable discharge</li>\r\n	<li>Families with children <strong>OR</strong> adult individuals</li>\r\n	<li>Must meet certain income criteria</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>If you are homeless or in need of housing/shelter, contact:</h2>\r\nJannet Salazar, (650) 315-4028, <a href=\"mailto:jsalazar@ivsn.org\">jsalazar@ivsn.org</a>\r\n\r\nJoran Seastrunk, (650) 346-2879, <a href=\"mailto:jseastrunk@ivsn.org\">jseastrunk@ivsn.org</a>\r\n\r\nDawn Holley, (650) 315-4010, <a href=\"mailto:dholley@ivsn.org\">dholley@ivsn.org</a>\r\n<h2>If you are facing eviction or at risk of becoming homeless, contact:</h2>\r\nChristiana Weidanz, (650) 523-0808, <a href=\"mailto:christiana@samaritanhousesanmateo.org\">christiana@samaritanhousesanmateo.org</a>','Supportive Services for Veteran Families (SSVF)','','publish','closed','open','','supportive-services-for-veteran-families-ssfv','','','2015-01-29 16:09:24','2015-01-30 00:09:24','',34,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?page_id=81',112,'page','',0),(82,2,'2013-09-20 17:02:46','2013-09-20 17:02:46',' ','','','publish','closed','open','','82','','','2015-09-02 20:59:37','2015-09-03 03:59:37','',34,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?p=82',15,'nav_menu_item','',0),(83,2,'2013-09-20 17:02:46','2013-09-20 17:02:46',' ','','','publish','closed','open','','83','','','2015-09-02 20:59:37','2015-09-03 03:59:37','',34,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?p=83',14,'nav_menu_item','',0),(84,2,'2013-09-20 17:03:24','2013-09-20 17:03:24','<h1><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-161\" src=\"http://ivsn.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ivsn_homeless_shelter_maple_street-320x239.jpg\" alt=\"ivsn_homeless_shelter_maple_street\" width=\"320\" height=\"239\" />Maple Street Shelter</h1>\r\n<div class=\"map alignright\">[flexiblemap width=\"320\" height=\"280\" showinfo=\"false\" address=\"1580A Maple Street, Redwood City, CA 94063\"]</div>\r\n<h2>IVSN’s Maple Street Shelter provides interim shelter and services for 75 adult men and women.</h2>\r\n1580A Maple Street\r\nRedwood City, CA 94063\r\nPhone: (650) 364-1150\r\nDonation Drop-off Hours: Every day 8 am-7 pm. Please call ahead on weekends.\r\n<h2>Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><b>Case Management: </b>Our trained Case Managers support clients’ unique needs, helping them manage budgets, connect with resources, and make active progress toward regaining permanent housing.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Housing and Job Search Assistance:</b> Staff and volunteers provide clients with training, tools, and resources to find and secure affordable housing and employment.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Financial Literacy and Savings: </b>We teach clients to manage a personal budget and save for emergency needs. Clients in transitional housing must save at least 50% of their income.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Life Skills Education: </b>We empower our clients with skills for long-term success through nightly workshops on financial literacy, parenting, nutrition, and other life skills.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Additional “Beyond the Bed” Services:</b> We offer an array of services that go “beyond the bed” to meet our clients’ unique needs and enable them to become self-sufficient for the long term.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>How You Can Help</h2>\r\n<a title=\"Donate\" href=\"http://ivsn.wpengine.com/donate/\"><strong>Donate</strong></a>: IVSN’s services are only made possible through generous financial support from the community year-round. Your gift ensures that we may continue to provide housing and supportive services to thousands of homeless children and adults.\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Volunteer\" href=\"http://ivsn.wpengine.com/volunteer/\"><strong>Volunteer</strong></a>: IVSN relies on the generous time and talent of over 18,000 volunteers annually. Every person has volunteer skills to offer, such as teaching workshops, tutoring students, organizing donations, preparing meals, and much more.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/volunteer/meal-programs/\"><strong>Provide a Meal</strong></a>: Prepare and serve a nutritious meal for the families at Maple Street Shelter!\r\n<h2><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Maple-Street-Donation-Wish-List-2015.pdf\">In-Kind Donation Wish List</a></h2>','Maple Street Shelter','','publish','closed','open','','maple-street-shelter','','','2015-03-30 16:49:08','2015-03-30 23:49:08','',35,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?page_id=84',111,'page','',0),(85,2,'2013-09-20 17:03:49','2013-09-20 17:03:49','<h1><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-162\" alt=\"ivsn_homeless_shelter_montgomery_street_inn\" src=\"http://ivsn.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ivsn_homeless_shelter_montgomery_street_inn-320x214.jpg\" width=\"320\" height=\"214\" />Montgomery Street Inn</h1>\r\n<div class=\"map alignright\">[flexiblemap width=\"320\" height=\"280\" showinfo=\"false\" address=\"358 N Montgomery St. San Jose, CA 95110\"]</div>\r\n<h2>IVSN’s Montgomery Street Inn provides interim shelter and services for 85 adult men.</h2>\r\n358 N. Montgomery Street\r\nSan Jose, CA 95110\r\nPhone: (408) 271-5160\r\n\r\nMontgomery Street Inn does not accept donations. <a title=\"Where To Donate\" href=\"http://ivsn.wpengine.com/donate/donate-items/where-to-donate/\">View our donation drop-off locations</a>.\r\n<h2>Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><b>Case Management: </b>Our experienced Case Managers support clients’ unique needs, helping them manage budgets, connect with resources, and develop plans that lead to securing employment and permanent housing.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Housing and Job Search Assistance:</b> Staff and volunteers provide clients with training, tools, and resources to find and secure affordable housing and employment.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Financial Literacy and Savings: </b>We teach clients to manage a personal budget and save money for basic needs.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Life Skills Education: </b>We empower our clients with skills for long-term success through regular groups, workshops, and counseling on financial literacy, resume building, health, nutrition, and other life skills.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Additional “Beyond the Bed” Services:</b> We offer an array of services that go “beyond the bed” to meet our clients’ unique needs and enable them to become self-sufficient for the long term.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>How You Can Help</h2>\r\n<a title=\"Donate\" href=\"http://ivsn.wpengine.com/donate/\"><strong>Donate</strong></a>: IVSN’s services are only made possible through generous financial support from the community year-round. Your gift ensures that we may continue to provide housing and supportive services to thousands of homeless children and adults.\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Volunteer\" href=\"http://ivsn.wpengine.com/volunteer/\"><strong>Volunteer</strong></a>: IVSN relies on the generous time and talent of over 18,000 volunteers annually. Every person has volunteer skills to offer, such as teaching workshops, tutoring students, organizing donations, preparing meals, and much more.','Montgomery Street Inn','','publish','closed','open','','montgomery-street-inn','','','2014-03-19 12:00:29','2014-03-19 19:00:29','',35,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?page_id=85',110,'page','',0),(86,2,'2013-09-20 17:04:11','2013-09-20 17:04:11','<h1><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-153\" alt=\"ivsn_homeless_shelter_julian_street_inn\" src=\"http://ivsn.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ivsn_homeless_shelter_julian_street_inn-320x214.jpg\" width=\"320\" height=\"214\" />Julian Street Inn</h1>\r\n<div class=\"map alignright\">[flexiblemap width=\"320\" height=\"280\" showinfo=\"false\" address=\"546 W. Julian Street, San Jose, CA 95110\"]</div>\r\n<h2>IVSN’s Julian Street Inn provides interim shelter and services for 71 homeless adults seeking mental health stability.</h2>\r\n546 W. Julian Street\r\nSan Jose, CA 95110\r\nPhone: (408) 271-0820\r\n\r\nJulian Street Inn does not accept donations. <a title=\"Where To Donate\" href=\"http://ivsn.wpengine.com/donate/donate-items/where-to-donate/\">View our donation drop-off locations</a>.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 1.5em;\">Services</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><b>Case Management: </b>Our experienced Case Managers support clients’ unique needs, helping them manage resident’s complex mental health issues, connect with resources, and develop plans that lead to stability and permanent housing.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Housing and Job Search Assistance:</b> Staff and volunteers provide clients with training, tools, and resources to find and secure affordable housing and employment.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Financial Literacy and Savings: </b>We encourage clients to learn how to manage a personal budget and save for emergency needs.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Life Skills Education: </b>We empower our clients with skills for long-term success through groups and counseling on managing their mental health, complying with medical care, and accessing treatment services.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Additional “Beyond the Bed” Services:</b> We offer an array of services that go “beyond the bed” to meet our clients’ unique needs and enable them to become self-sufficient for the long term.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>How You Can Help</h2>\r\n<a title=\"Donate\" href=\"http://ivsn.wpengine.com/donate/\"><strong>Donate</strong></a>: IVSN’s services are only made possible through generous financial support from the community year-round. Your gift ensures that we may continue to provide housing and supportive services to thousands of homeless children and adults.\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Volunteer\" href=\"http://ivsn.wpengine.com/volunteer/\"><strong>Volunteer</strong></a>: IVSN relies on the generous time and talent of over 18,000 volunteers annually. Every person has volunteer skills to offer, such as teaching workshops, tutoring students, organizing donations, preparing meals, and much more.','Julian Street Inn','','publish','closed','open','','julian-street-inn','','','2014-03-19 11:58:39','2014-03-19 18:58:39','',35,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?page_id=86',109,'page','',0),(87,2,'2013-09-20 17:04:31','2013-09-20 17:04:31','<h1>Homeless Outreach</h1>\r\nIVSN’s Homeless Outreach Team (HOT) is a team of specially-trained case managers focused on helping chronically homeless individuals move off the streets and secure permanent housing.\r\n\r\nHOT Outreach team members work closely with local law enforcement, merchants, and other community stakeholders to serve chronically homeless individuals, with the ultimate goal of helping them move off of the streets and into supportive housing programs.\r\n\r\nHOT Outreach team members provide homeless people living on the streets with proactive case management, and connect them with much-needed and cost-effective services. The HOT program serves the greater community by reducing taxpayer expenses on medical and law enforcement services consumed by chronically homeless individuals.\r\n\r\n<strong>Contact</strong>\r\nConnie Leyva\r\n<a href=\"mailto:cleyva@ivsn.org\">cleyva@ivsn.org</a>\r\n(650) 346-1597\r\n<h2>Healthcare for the Homeless Program</h2>\r\n<strong>Social Security Disability Benefits and Health Insurance (ACE/MCE/MediCal) Application Assistance</strong>\r\n\r\nHealthcare for the Homeless (HCH) Outreach team members work with homeless individuals (adults and children) living on the streets or in shelters, with the goal of:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Increasing homeless individual access to primary care physicians and gain medical coverage/insurance</li>\r\n	<li>Assisting homeless individuals in preparing SSI/SSDI applications</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<strong>Contact</strong>\r\nStephen Lee, <a href=\"mailto:slee@ivsn.org\">slee@ivsn.org</a>, (650) 222-9485\r\n\r\nKatie Dahlinghaus, <a href=\"mailto:kdahlinghaus@ivsn.org\">kdahlinghaus@ivsn.org</a>, (650) 346-4465','Homeless Outreach','','publish','closed','open','','homeless-outreach','','','2013-10-08 11:47:51','2013-10-08 11:47:51','',35,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?page_id=87',108,'page','',0),(88,2,'2013-09-20 17:05:11','2013-09-20 17:05:11','<h1><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-165\" alt=\"ivsn_homeless_shelter_vendome\" src=\"http://ivsn.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ivsn_homeless_shelter_vendome-320x239.jpg\" width=\"320\" height=\"239\" />Permanent Supportive Housing</h1>\r\nPage under construction. Please check back soon!','Permanent Supportive Housing','','private','closed','open','','permanent-supportive-housing','','','2014-01-29 09:43:45','2014-01-29 17:43:45','',35,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?page_id=88',107,'page','',0),(90,2,'2013-09-20 17:05:52','2013-09-20 17:05:52',' ','','','publish','closed','open','','90','','','2015-09-02 20:59:37','2015-09-03 03:59:37','',35,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?p=90',20,'nav_menu_item','',0),(91,2,'2013-09-20 17:05:52','2013-09-20 17:05:52',' ','','','publish','closed','open','','91','','','2015-09-02 20:59:37','2015-09-03 03:59:37','',35,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?p=91',17,'nav_menu_item','',0),(92,2,'2013-09-20 17:05:52','2013-09-20 17:05:52',' ','','','publish','close