s/2013/09/sign_up_to_volunteer.png\" alt=\"sign_up_to_volunteer\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a></h2>\r\n<h2>Volunteer Directly with Clients</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Teach a Life Skills Workshop:</strong> Volunteers teach valuable life skills workshops to clients on a range of topics, including financial literacy, budgeting, resume writing, interview skills, and parenting.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Host a Community-Building Party</strong>: Volunteers plan fun community-building events for the shelter residents, such as birthday parties, movie nights, picnics, and holiday celebrations.</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/volunteer/for-individuals/support-committees/\"><strong>Become a Support Committee Leader</strong></a>: Support Committee members are long-term volunteers who work directly with clients and staff to adopt a shelter and perform a wide range of critical, supportive activities.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Improve a Shelter Facility</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Organize Donations:</strong> Volunteers organize donations at our facilities and help clients find the items they need, such as clothing, food, and school supplies—donated directly to people in need.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Maintain and Beautify Facilities:</strong> Volunteers generously donate their time and supplies to clean, paint, maintain, and beautify our shelters so that clients are housed in welcoming, dignified communities.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Stage Transitional Apartments:</strong> Volunteers use donated household items to stage transitional apartments, making them warm and welcoming for new residents moving into the shelter.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Tend the Organic Garden:</strong> Volunteers help dig, weed, plant, and harvest the gardens at IVSN shelters, which provide fresh fruits, vegetables, and flowers to residents.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Volunteer with Children</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Tutor Children and Youth:</strong> Volunteer tutors support students in the computer labs and children’s centers, helping them complete their homework assignments and excel academically.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Lead Children’s Activities:</strong> Volunteers at our family shelters help supervise children and lead playtime activities, such as arts and crafts, reading time, computer learning, storytelling, and more.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Work With the Teen Program:</strong> Volunteers provide valuable mentorship and guidance to teenage residents by helping them excel in school and pursue a college education.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Advocate and Educate</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/How-to-Manage-a-Drive-for-IVSN2015.pdf\">Host a Donation Drive</a>:</strong> Volunteers host donation drives for items given directly to IVSN clients, such as gift certificates, school supplies, bedding, toiletries, business clothing, and kitchen items.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Outreach to the Community:</strong> Advocate for IVSN and spread the word about how the community can help end homelessness by hosting a “party with a purpose” to collect funds or needed items.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Apply for an Internship:</strong> Students may apply for an internship throughout the year to gain hands-on experience in human services and nonprofit management.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a href=\"http://volunteer.ivsn.org/\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-370 size-full\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/sign_up_to_volunteer.png\" alt=\"sign_up_to_volunteer\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a>','For Individuals','','publish','closed','closed','','for-individuals','','','2015-03-19 19:40:14','2015-03-20 02:40:14','',18,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?page_id=184',98,'page','',0),(185,2,'2013-09-30 20:36:02','2013-09-30 20:36:02','<h1><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-393\" src=\"http://ivsn.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/donate_google_volunteers_painting-320x213.jpg\" alt=\"donate_google_volunteers_painting\" width=\"320\" height=\"213\" />Volunteer With Your Company</h1>\r\nEngage your employees in team-building volunteer projects that make a difference for people in need.\r\n<h2>Volunteer Directly with Clients</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Teach a Life Skills Workshop: </strong>Volunteers teach valuable life skills workshops to clients on a range of topics, including financial literacy, budgeting, resume writing, interview skills, and parenting.</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/volunteer/meal-programs/\"><strong>Prepare and Serve Meals</strong></a>: Volunteers plan, prepare, and serve meals to IVSN clients, donating nutritious food and serving those in need with compassion and care.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Host a Community-Building Party</strong>: Volunteers plan fun community-building events for the shelter residents, such as birthday parties, movie nights, picnics, and holiday celebrations.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Improve a Shelter Facility</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Organize Donations</strong>: Volunteers organize items that have been donated at our facilities and help clients find the items they need, such as clothing, food, and school supplies.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Maintain and Beautify Facilities</strong>: Volunteers generously donate their time and supplies to clean, paint, maintain, and beautify our shelters so that clients are housed in welcoming, dignified communities.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Tend the Organic Garden</strong>: Volunteers help dig, weed, plant, and harvest the gardens at IVSN shelters, which provide fresh fruits, vegetables, and flowers to residents.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Advocate and Educate</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Outreach to the Community:</strong> Advocate for IVSN and spread the word about how the community can help end homelessness by hosting an event or online campaign to collect funds or needed items.</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/How-to-Manage-a-Drive-for-IVSN1.pdf\"><strong>Host a Donation Drive</strong></a>: Volunteers host donation drives for items given directly to IVSN clients, such as gift certificates, school supplies, bedding, toiletries, business clothing, and kitchen items.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Organize a Tour</strong>: Visit our sites! Organize a personal tour of InnVision Shelter Network for you and your colleagues. See our life-changing programs and the positive impact of your contributions firsthand. Our staff can also come to you and present on the work we do to kick off your philanthropy program.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a href=\"http://volunteer.ivsn.org/IVGroup.aspx\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-370\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/sign_up_to_volunteer.png\" alt=\"sign_up_to_volunteer\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a>','For Companies','','publish','closed','closed','','for-companies','','','2014-08-24 10:25:38','2014-08-24 17:25:38','',18,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?page_id=185',97,'page','',0),(186,2,'2013-09-30 20:36:24','2013-09-30 20:36:24','<h1><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-407\" src=\"http://ivsn.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/volunteer_salesforce_painting-320x240.jpg\" alt=\"volunteer_salesforce_painting\" width=\"320\" height=\"240\" />Group Volunteers</h1>\r\n<h2>Volunteer Directly with Clients</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Teach a Life Skills Workshop</strong>: Volunteers teach valuable life skills workshops to clients on a range of topics, including financial literacy, budgeting, resume writing, interview skills, and parenting.</li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/volunteer/meal-programs/\">Prepare and Serve Meals</a>:</strong> Volunteers plan, prepare, and serve meals to IVSN clients, donating nutritious food and serving those in need with compassion and care.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Host a Community-Building Party:</strong> Volunteers plan fun community-building events for the shelter residents, such as birthday parties, movie nights, picnics, and holiday celebrations.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Improve a Shelter Facility<b></b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Organize Donations:</strong> Volunteers organize donations at our facilities and help clients find the items they need, such as clothing, food, and school supplies—donated directly to people in need.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Maintain and Beautify Facilities:</strong> Volunteers generously donate their time and supplies to clean, paint, maintain, and beautify our shelters so that clients are housed in welcoming, dignified communities.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Stage Transitional Apartments:</strong> Volunteers use donated household items to stage transitional apartments, making them warm and welcoming for new residents moving into the shelter.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Tend the Organic Garden:</strong> Volunteers help dig, weed, plant, and harvest the gardens at IVSN shelters, which provide fresh fruits, vegetables, and flowers to residents.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Advocate and Educate<b></b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/How-to-Manage-a-Drive-for-IVSN2015.pdf\">Host a Donation Drive</a>:</strong> Volunteers host donation drives for items given directly to IVSN clients, such as gift certificates, school supplies, bedding, toiletries, business clothing, and kitchen items.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Outreach to the Community:</strong> Advocate for IVSN and spread the word about how the community can help end homelessness by hosting a “party with a purpose” to collect funds or needed items.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><a href=\"http://volunteer.ivsn.org/IVGroup.aspx\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-370\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/sign_up_to_volunteer.png\" alt=\"sign_up_to_volunteer\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a></h2>','For Groups','','publish','closed','closed','','for-groups','','','2015-03-18 17:10:57','2015-03-19 00:10:57','',18,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?page_id=186',96,'page','',0),(187,2,'2013-09-30 20:36:41','2013-09