or\" href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/volunteer/for-youth/camp-counselor/\">Staff a Summer Camp</a>:</strong> Volunteers serve as Camp Counselors to plan fun, educational activities and field trips for children at our family shelters during the summer. <a title=\"Camp Counselor\" href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/volunteer/for-youth/camp-counselor/\">Learn more about volunteering as a Camp Counselor.</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Advocate and Educate<b></b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/How-to-Manage-a-Drive-for-IVSN1.pdf\">Host a Donation Drive</a>:</strong> Volunteers host donation drives for items given directly to IVSN clients, such as gift certificates, school supplies, bedding, toiletries, business clothing, and kitchen items.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Outreach to the Community:</strong> Advocate for IVSN and spread the word about how the community can help end homelessness by hosting a “party with a purpose” to collect funds or needed items.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Apply for an Internship:</strong> Students may apply for an internship throughout the year to gain hands-on experience in human services and nonprofit management. <a title=\"Internships\" href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/about/jobs/internships/\">Learn more about student internships.</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a href=\"http://volunteer.ivsn.org/\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-370 size-full\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/sign_up_to_volunteer.png\" alt=\"sign_up_to_volunteer\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a>','For Youth','','publish','closed','closed','','for-youth','','','2015-05-21 20:22:34','2015-05-22 03:22:34','',18,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?page_id=187',95,'page','',0),(188,2,'2013-09-30 20:37:07','2013-09-30 20:37:07','<h1><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-403\" src=\"http://ivsn.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/volunteer_food_meal_service-320x241.jpg\" alt=\"volunteer_food_meal_service\" width=\"320\" height=\"241\" />Meal Programs</h1>\r\nYour volunteer group can provide and serve healthy and nutritious meals to homeless families and individuals at several InnVision Shelter Network facilities.\r\n\r\nPlease note that we request your group buy and prepare the food for our clients; IVSN’s housing sites are not “soup kitchens,” and as such we ask volunteers to donate the food and their time to serve our clients.\r\n<h2>Meal Provider Volunteer Manual</h2>\r\nWe recommend you review the <a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/Meal-Provider-Volunteer-Manual-020415.pdf\">Meal Provider Volunteer Manual</a> for site-specific details and guidance on how to ensure a fun and productive volunteer experience.\r\n<h2>Sign Up to Provide a Meal</h2>\r\nTo provide a meal for <strong>Commercial Street Inn </strong> in San Jose, view the <a href=\"http://volunteer.ivsn.org/IVSNCalendar.aspx?CLR=14\">Commercial Street Inn Meal Provider Calendar</a> and register for an available meal.\r\n\r\nTo provide a meal for <strong>First Step for Families</strong> in San Mateo, view the<a href=\"http://volunteer.ivsn.org/IVSNCalendar.aspx?CLR=9\"> First Step Meal Provider Calendar</a> and register for an available meal.\r\n\r\nTo provide a meal for <strong>Julian Street Inn</strong> in San Jose, view the <a title=\"Julian Street Inn Meal Provider Calendar \" href=\"http://volunteer.ivsn.org/IVSNCalendar.aspx?CLR=12\">Julian Street Inn Meal Provider Calendar</a> and register for an available meal. <b>Must be 18 years of age to volunteer at this site.</b>\r\n\r\nTo provide a meal for <strong>Maple Street Shelter </strong> in Redwood City, view the <a href=\"http://volunteer.ivsn.org/IVSNCalendar.aspx?CLR=15\">Maple St. Meal Provider Calendar</a> and register for an available meal.\r\n\r\nTo provide a meal for <strong>Montgomery Street Inn </strong>in San Jose, view the <a href=\"http://volunteer.ivsn.org/IVSNCalendar.aspx?CLR=13\">Montgomery Street Inn Meal Provider Calendar</a> and register for an available meal. <b>Must be 18 years of age to volunteer at this site.</b>\r\n\r\nTo provide a meal for <strong>Villa Shelter </strong> in San Jose, view the <a title=\"Villa Meal Provider Calendar\" href=\"http://volunteer.ivsn.org/IVSNCalendar.aspx?CLR=17\">Villa Meal Provider Calendar</a> and register for an available meal.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">To provide a meal for all other sites, please contact </span><span class=\"s1\">Jessie Ellington at <a href=\"mailto:Jellington@ivsn.org\"><span class=\"s2\">Jellington@ivsn.org</span></a></span><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">.</span>','Meal Programs','','publish','closed','closed','','meal-programs','','','2015-10-14 20:33:05','2015-10-15 03:33:05','',18,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?page_id=188',94,'page','',0),(191,2,'2013-09-30 20:38:48','2013-09-30 20:38:48',' ','','','publish','closed','open','','meal-programs','','','2014-08-26 14:46:58','2014-08-26 21:46:58','',18,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?p=191',6,'nav_menu_item','',0),(192,2,'2013-09-30 20:38:48','2013-09-30 20:38:48',' ','','','publish','closed','open','','for-youth','','','2014-08-26 14:46:58','2014-08-26 21:46:58','',18,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?p=192',5,'nav_menu_item','',0),(193,2,'2013-09-30 20:38:48','2013-09-30 20:38:48',' ','','','publish','closed','open','','for-groups','','','2014-08-26 14:46:58','2014-08-26 21:46:58','',18,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?p=193',4,'nav_menu_item','',0),(194,2,'2013-09-30 20:38:48','2013-09-30 20:38:48',' ','','','publish','closed','open','','for-companies','','','2014-08-26 14:46:58','2014-08-26 21:46:58','',18,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?p=194',3,'nav_menu_item','',0),(195,2,'2013-09-30 20:38:48','2013-09-30 20:38:48',' ','','','publish','closed','open','','for-individuals','','','2014-08-26 14:46:58','2014-08-26 21:46:58','',18,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?p=195',2,'nav_menu_item','',0),(197,2,'2013-09-30 20:49:36','2013-09-30 20:49:36','','v-companies','','inherit','closed','open','','v-companies','','','2013-09-30 20:49:36','2013-09-30 20:49:36','',18,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/v-companies.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(198,2,'2013-09-30 20:49:37','2013-09-30 20:49:37','','v-groups','','inherit','closed','open','','v-groups','','','2013-09-30 20:49:37','2013-09-30 20:49:37','',18,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/v-groups.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(199,2,'2013-09-30 20:49:37','2013-09-30 20:49:37','','v-individuals','','inherit','closed','open','','v-individuals','','','2013-09-30 20:49:37','2013-09-30 20:49:37','',18,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/v-individuals.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(200,2,'2013-09-30 20:49:38','2013-09-30 20:49:38','','v-youth','','inherit','closed','open','','v-youth','','','2013-09-30 20:49:38','2013-09-30 20:49:38','',18,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/v-youth.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(205,2,'2013-09-30 21:42:35','2013-09-30 21:42:35',' ','','','publish','closed','open','','205','','','2014-08-26 14:46:36','2014-08-26 21:46:36','',0,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?p=205',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(207,2,'2013-09-30 22:02:14','2013-09-30 22:02:14','<h1><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-395\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/donate_homeless_daughter_kissing_mom-320x239.jpg\" alt=\"donate_homeless_daughter_kissing_mom\" width=\"320\" height=\"239\" />Ways to Give</h1>\r\n<h1><a href=\"https://14345.thankyou4caring.org/sslpage.aspx?pid=392\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-452 alignnone\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/donate_button.png\" alt=\"donate_button\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a></h1>\r\n<h2>Donate Funds</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Donate online</strong>. <a href=\"https://14345.thankyou4caring.org/sslpage.aspx?pid=392\" target=\"_blank\">Click here to donate</a>.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Write a check</strong>. Make checks payable to “InnVision Shelter Network” and mail to:\r\nInnVision Shelter Network\r\n181 Constitution Drive\r\nMenlo Park, CA 94025</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Give over the phone</strong>. Call us at (650) 685-5880 ext. 156 to give us your credit card information.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Donate in Honor of a Loved One</h2>\r\nLooking for the perfect gift for a friend or family member? Donate in honor of a loved one for their birthday, anniversary, graduation, wedding, or other special occasion. The honoree will receive a card from IVSN notifying them of your thoughtfulness and generosity. <a href=\"https://14345.thankyou4caring.org/sslpage.aspx?pid=392\" target=\"_blank\">Click here to donate</a>.\r\n<h2>Donate Monthly</h2>\r\nSign up for our Monthly Giving Club to make a monthly donation. We will arrange for your donation to be delivered automatically from your credit card or checking account. Contact Marissa Robbins at <a href=\"mailto:mrobbins@ivsn.org\">mrobbins@ivsn.org</a> or (650) 685-5880 ext. 156 to sign up.\r\n<h2>Ask Your Employer to Match</h2>\r\nMany companies will match their employees’ charitable gifts. Don’t miss out on the opportunity to double your impact! <a title=\"Employee Matching\" href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/donate/employee-matching/\">Read more about employee matching</a>.\r\n<h2>Donate Stock/Securities</h2>\r\nContributing appreciated securities is a most mutually beneficial way to support IVSN. We also accept gifts of real estate and other property. <a title=\"Donate Stock\" href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/donate/donate-stock/\">Read more about donating securities</a>.\r\n<h2>Make a Tax-Free IRA Gift</h2>\r\nIf you are age 70 1/2 or older, you may qualify for an important incentive for charitable giving. Make a tax-free gift to IVSN through a direct transfer from a traditional Individual Retirement Account. For more information, contact Ruth Richerson at <a href=\"mailto:rricherson@ivsn.org\">rricherson@ivsn.org</a> or (650) 685-5880 ext. 171.','Ways to Give','','publish','closed','closed','','ways-to-give','','','2015-05-21 20:53:01','2015-05-22 03:53:01','',43,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?page_id=207',93,'page','',0),(208,2,'2013-09-30 22:03:21','2013-09-30 22:03:21','<h1><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-392\" src=\"http://ivsn.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/donate_genentech_volunteers-320x240.jpg\" alt=\"donate_genentech_volunteers\" width=\"320\" height=\"240\" />Corporate Partners</h1>\r\nIVSN Corporate Partners are philanthropic leaders in our community. Show your employees, customers, and stakeholders that you are a dedicated partner in ending homelessness.\r\n\r\nFor more information about the Corporate Partners program, please contact Eli Latimerlo at<a href=\"mailto:%20elatimerlo@ivsn.org\"> elatimerlo@ivsn.org</a> or (650) 685-5880 ext. 115.\r\n<h2>Give Financial Support</h2>\r\nAssert your company as a socially responsible leader in philanthropic giving to support local nonprofit organizations. <a href=\"https://14345.thankyou4caring.org/sslpage.aspx?pid=392\" target=\"_blank\">Donate online</a>, or contact Eli Latimerlo at<a href=\"mailto:%20elatimerlo@ivsn.org\"> elatimerlo@ivsn.org</a> or (650) 685-5880 ext. 115.\r\n<h2>Match Employee Gifts</h2>\r\nEncourage your employees to support IVSN’s services for homeless families and individuals. Sign up for an <a title=\"Employee Matching\" href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/donate/employee-matching/\">employee matching gift program</a> and amplify the impact of your employees’ donations.\r\n<h2>Volunteer in Teambuilding Activities</h2>\r\nEngage your employees in volunteer team-building activities that support homeless families and individuals. Projects include hosting a donation drive, improving a shelter, or contributing pro-bono professional services. <a title=\"For Companies\" href=\"http://ivsn.wpengine.com/volunteer/for-companies/\">Learn more about corporate volunteer opportunities</a>.\r\n<h2>Sponsor the Benefit Breakfast</h2>\r\nIVSN’s Benefit Breakfast events promote awareness about issues of homelessness in the Peninsula/Silicon Valley region, and raise critically-needed funds to support IVSN’s services for homeless families and adults. The Breakfasts provide ample opportunities for corporate visibility and recognition. <a title=\"Events\" href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/news-events/events/\">Read more about the Benefit Breakfasts.</a>\r\n<h2>Host a Fundraiser or Donation Drive</h2>\r\nSponsor a drive to raise funds for much needed items, such as financial donations, gift cards, business clothing, children\'s supplies, household items, flashdrives and back-to-school materials, and more. Drive sponsors are needed year-round but especially during the holidays. <a title=\"For Companies\" href=\"http://ivsn.wpengine.com/volunteer/for-companies/\">Sign up to host a drive</a>.\r\n<h2>Contact</h2>\r\nFor more information on any of these opportunities or to suggest your own idea, please contact Eli Latimerlo at<a href=\"mailto:%20elatimerlo@ivsn.org\"> elatimerlo@ivsn.org</a> or (650) 685-5880 ext. 115.','Corporate Partners','','publish','closed','closed','','corporate-partners','','','2014-06-06 13:10:37','2014-06-06 20:10:37','',43,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?page_id=208',92,'page','',0),(209,2,'2013-09-30 22:04:48','2013-09-30 22:04:48','<h1><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-399\" alt=\"donate_homeless_mother_reading\" src=\"http://ivsn.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/donate_homeless_mother_reading-320x213.jpg\" width=\"320\" height=\"213\" />Planned Giving</h1>\r\nThank you for considering a planned gift to InnVision Shelter Network! A planned gift is any gift given for any amount, given for any purpose – operations, capital expansion, or endowment – whether for current or deferred use by IVSN, which requires the assistance of a professional staff person, a qualified volunteer, or the donor’s advisors to complete. In addition, it includes any gift which is carefully considered by a donor in light of estate and financial plans.\r\n\r\nWhile the most common planned gift is typically made through a bequest in a person’s will or living trust, there are a range of other vehicles for you to consider. The following are a few ways to make a planned gift to IVSN.\r\n<h2>A gift in your will or living trust</h2>\r\nA simple charitable bequest can provide very meaningful support for our mission as well as reduce the amount of estate and inheritance taxes paid. Bequests may be specific assets or amounts, or they may be proportional or residual in nature.\r\n<h2>A gift of a new or existing life insurance policy</h2>\r\nMany people have life insurance policies that are no longer needed for their original purposes. Such policies can be given to IVSN and an income tax deduction can be taken for the cash surrender value. Plus, the annual premiums on a new or existing policy given to the organization irrevocably may also be tax-deductible.\r\n<h2>A beneficiary designation on your life insurance policy</h2>\r\nWithout giving up ownership of your life insurance policy, you can still designate IVSN as a whole or partial death beneficiary. Contact your insurance company for a Change of Beneficiary form.\r\n<h2>A gift of financial accounts</h2>\r\nMost checking, savings and brokerage accounts can be bequeathed to IVSN through a simple “payable on death” designation with your financial institution.\r\n<h2>A gift of retirement benefits</h2>\r\nNaming IVSN as primary, partial or contingent beneficiary of your retirement plan is a simple, practical gift idea. Contact your plan custodian for the proper beneficiary change forms.\r\n<h2>A gift of savings bonds</h2>\r\nMany people have fully appreciated savings bonds. These assets cannot be donated during your lifetime without first being converted to cash and, therefore, generating taxable income. By making a gift of savings bonds through your will, you can avoid this tax and support IVSN’s continuing efforts.\r\n<h2>More Information</h2>\r\nFor additional information or to arrange a confidential gift planning consultation without obligation, please contact Amy Wright at <a href=\"mailto:awright@ivsn.org\">awright@ivsn.org</a> or  (650) 685-5880 ext. 132.\r\n\r\n<em>The information above is intended for educational purposes only and should not be considered legal, accounting or other professional advice.</em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Planned Giving','','publish','closed','closed','','planned-giving','','','2013-10-14 23:33:40','2013-10-14 23:33:40','',43,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?page_id=209',91,'page','',0),(210,2,'2013-09-30 22:06:27','2013-09-30 22:06:27','<h1><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-391\" src=\"http://ivsn.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/donate_donate_household_items-320x220.jpg\" alt=\"donate_donate_household_items\" width=\"320\" height=\"220\" />Donate Items</h1>\r\nDonate like-new items to support homeless families and individuals!\r\n\r\nYour donations are given directly free-of-charge to the homeless families and individuals in our programs to help them on their path to permanent housing and self-sufficiency.\r\n\r\nPlease only donate goods in <b>new</b> or <b>gently-used</b> condition. We reserve the right to refuse inappropriate or damaged items.\r\n<h2>Where to Donate</h2>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Donations can be dropped off at various shelters throughout the Peninsula and Silicon Valley. <strong>Please note, we are unable to accept furniture donations directly at each site.</strong> Please contact <a href=\"mailto:reception@ivsn.org\"><span class=\"s2\">reception@ivsn.org</span></a></span><span class=\"s3\"> if you have furniture you would like to donate.</span></p>\r\n<a title=\"Where To Donate\" href=\"http://ivsn.wpengine.com/donate/donate-items/where-to-donate/\">View our donation drop-off locations</a><strong>.</strong>\r\n<h2>Wish Lists By Location</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/First-Step-for-Families-Donation-Wish-List-2015.pdf\">First Step for Families</a>, San Mateo</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/RFH-Donation-Wish-List-2015.pdf\">Redwood Family House</a>, Redwood City</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Maple-Street-Donation-Wish-List-2015.pdf\">Maple Street Shelter</a>, Redwood City</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Haven-Donation-Wish-List-2015.pdf\">Haven Family House</a>, Menlo Park</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/The-Villa-Donation-Wish-List-2015.pdf\">The Villa</a>, San Jose</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/CSI-Donation-Wish-List-2015.pdf\">Commercial Street Inn</a>, San Jose</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Unfortunately, we <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">cannot</span> accept:</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Dirty/stained, torn, broken, or items needing repair</li>\r\n	<li>Game boards/puzzles missing pieces</li>\r\n	<li>Stuffed animals</li>\r\n	<li>Car seats, cribs, strollers</li>\r\n	<li>Outdated electronics, computers over 3 years old</li>\r\n	<li>Carpeting, rugs</li>\r\n	<li>Large sports equipment</li>\r\n	<li>Candles, knick-knacks</li>\r\n	<li>Wine glasses, alcohol or illegal drug-related items</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;','Donate Items','','publish','closed','closed','','donate-items','','','2015-08-18 19:33:42','2015-08-19 02:33:42','',43,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?page_id=210',90,'page','',0),(211,2,'2013-09-30 22:08:57','2013-09-30 22:08:57','<h1>Where to Donate</h1>\r\nInnVision Shelter Network relies on generous donations from the community to support our homeless families and individuals on their path to self-sufficiency. Below are the shelter locations that accept in-kind donations.\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/ms?msid=207935614143082815757.0004cf5d6406571e2e037&amp;msa=0&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;t=m&amp;ll=37.536955,-122.196808&amp;spn=0.522703,0.878906&amp;z=10&amp;output=embed\" width=\"640\" height=\"480\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\"></iframe>\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Family Crossroads\" href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/services/family-services/family-crossroads/\"><strong>Family Crossroads</strong></a>\r\nFamily Crossroads is currently <strong>NOT </strong>accepting in-kind donations while the facility undergoes renovations.\r\n\r\n<a title=\"First Step for Families\" href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/services/family-services/first-step-for-families/\"><strong>First Step for Families</strong></a>\r\n325 Villa Terrace, San Mateo, CA 94401 (<a href=\"http://goo.gl/maps/ovGDS\" target=\"_blank\">map</a>)\r\n<strong>Phone:</strong> (650) 340-8814\r\n<strong>Drop-off Times:</strong> Every day 8am-5pm. Please call ahead for weekend drop-off.\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline; color: #0000ff;\"><a style=\"color: #0000ff; text-decoration: underline;\" href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/First-Step-for-Families-Donation-Wish-List-2015.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">View the First Step for Families Wish List</a></span>\r\n\r\n<strong>The Vendome</strong>\r\n415 E 2nd Avenue, San Mateo, CA 94401 (<a href=\"http://goo.gl/maps/QGSLu\" target=\"_blank\">map</a>)\r\n<strong>Phone:</strong> (650) 340-6733\r\n<strong>Donations Accepted:</strong> adult clothing, kitchen items, cleaning supplies, toiletries, linens and bedding, gift certificates\r\n<strong>Drop-off Times:</strong> By appointment only. Please call ahead. Closed weekends.\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Redwood Family House\" href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/services/family-services/redwood-family-house/\"><strong>Redwood Family House</strong></a>\r\n110 Locust Street, Redwood City, CA 94061 (<a href=\"http://goo.gl/maps/upzG1\" target=\"_blank\">map</a>)\r\n<strong>Phone:</strong> (650) 364-8264\r\n<strong>Drop-off Times:</strong> Monday-Friday 9am-5pm. Closed weekends.\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline; color: #0000ff;\"><a style=\"color: #0000ff; text-decoration: underline;\" href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/RFH-Donation-Wish-List-2015.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">View the Redwood Family House Wish List</a></span>\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Maple Street Shelter\" href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/services/single-adult-services/maple-street-shelter/\"><strong>Maple Street Shelter</strong></a>\r\n1580A Maple Street, Redwood City, CA 94063 (<a href=\"http://goo.gl/maps/5YkS5\" target=\"_blank\">map</a>)\r\n<strong>Phone:</strong> (650) 364-1150\r\n<strong>Drop-off Times:</strong> Every day 8am-7pm. Please call ahead for weekend drop-off.\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline; color: #0000ff;\"><strong><a style=\"color: #0000ff; text-decoration: underline;\" href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Maple-Street-Donation-Wish-List-2015.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">View the Maple Street Shelter Wish List</a></strong></span>\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Haven Family House\" href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/services/family-services/haven-family-house/\"><strong>Haven Family House</strong></a>\r\n260 Van Buren Road, Menlo Park, CA 94025 (<a href=\"http://goo.gl/maps/Jp5K7\" target=\"_blank\">map</a>)\r\n<strong>Phone:</strong> (650) 325-8719\r\n<strong>Drop-off Times:</strong> Monday and Friday only, 9am-5pm\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"color: #0000ff;\"><strong><a style=\"color: #0000ff; text-decoration: underline;\" href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Haven-Donation-Wish-List-2015.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">View the Haven Family House Wish List</a></strong></span></span>\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Opportunity Services Center\" href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/services/family-services/opportunity-services-center/\"><strong>Opportunity Services Center</strong></a>\r\n33 Encina Avenue, Palo Alto, CA 94301 (<a href=\"http://goo.gl/maps/MwVqn\" target=\"_blank\">map</a>)\r\n<strong>Phone:</strong> (650) 853-8672\r\n<strong>Drop-off Times:</strong> Monday-Friday 8am-4pm\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Commercial Street Inn\" href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/services/family-services/commercial-street-inn/\"><strong>Commercial Street Inn</strong></a>\r\n260 Commercial Street, San Jose CA 95112 (<a href=\"https://www.google.com/maps/place/InnVision+Shelter+Network:+Commercial+Street+Inn/@37.3599772,-121.9006952,18z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x808fcc7f4c9ecf85:0xcf88cb2d4d905eaa?hl=en\" target=\"_blank\">map</a>)\r\n<strong>Phone:</strong> (408) 271-1630\r\n<strong>Drop-off Times:</strong> Tuesday and Thursday only, 10am-4pm\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"color: #0000ff;\"><strong><a style=\"color: #0000ff; text-decoration: underline;\" href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/CSI-Donation-Wish-List-2015.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">View the Commercial Street Inn Wish List</a></strong></span></span>\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Villa\" href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/services/family-services/villa/\"><strong>The Villa</strong></a>\r\n184 South 11th Street, San Jose CA 95112 (<a href=\"https://www.google.com/maps/place/184+S+11th+St,+San+Jose,+CA+95112/@37.3382711,-121.8773406,21z/data=!4m7!1m4!3m3!1s0x808fccc0cb1c6e8b:0xd7575bc6aa500eef!2s184+S+11th+St,+San+Jose,+CA+95112!3b1!3m1!1s0x808fccc0cb1c6e8b:0xd7575bc6aa500eef?hl=en\" target=\"_blank\">map</a>)\r\n<strong>Phone:</strong> (408) 271-0685\r\n<strong>Drop-off Times:</strong> Tuesday and Thursday only, 10am-4pm\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"color: #0000ff;\"><strong><a style=\"color: #0000ff; text-decoration: underline;\" href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/The-Villa-Donation-Wish-List-2015.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">View the Villa Wish List</a></strong></span></span>','Where To Donate','','publish','closed','closed','','where-to-donate','','','2015-03-18 14:21:44','2015-03-18 21:21:44','',210,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?page_id=211',89,'page','',0),(213,2,'2013-09-30 22:11:46','2013-09-30 22:11:46','<h1>Donate Your Vehicle</h1>\r\nIVSN welcomes donations of motor vehicles to support our mission of ending homelessness.\r\n\r\nWe partner with <a href=\"http://www.carswithheart.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><b>Cars With Heart</b></a> to manage donations of working and non-working vehicles. Cars With Heart schedules pick-ups, makes minor repairs, and auctions the vehicle, donating the proceeds to IVSN. The services provided by Cars With Heart incur no cost to the donor nor IVSN, and ensure that the donation is maximized to the greatest extent possible to benefit the homeless children and adults at IVSN.\r\n\r\nTo donate your vehicle, complete the online donation form with <a href=\"https://carswithheart.com/donate\" target=\"_blank\">Cars with Heart</a> and designate InnVision Shelter Network as the charity beneficiary. <a href=\"https://carswithheart.com/donate\" target=\"_blank\">Donate your vehicle now.</a>\r\n<h2>Questions?</h2>\r\nContact Marissa Robbins at <a href=\"mailto:mrobbins@ivsn.org\">mrobbins@ivsn.org</a> or (650) 685-5880 ext 156.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Vehicle Donations','','publish','closed','closed','','vehicle-donations','','','2015-06-09 14:47:21','2015-06-09 21:47:21','',210,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?page_id=213',88,'page','',0),(214,2,'2013-09-30 22:12:51','2013-09-30 22:12:51','<h1><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-400\" src=\"http://ivsn.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/donate_pac-12_stanford_donated_room-320x213.jpg\" alt=\"donate_pac-12_stanford_donated_room\" width=\"320\" height=\"213\" />Furniture Donations</h1>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Thank you for thinking of the families and individuals in our programs for your furniture donations!   From time to time, we also need to update or replace the furnishings in our facilities as well. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><a href=\"mailto:reception@ivsn.org\"><span class=\"s1\"><b>Please send us digital photos</b></span> </a><span class=\"s4\">of the furniture you are interested in donating.  Our process is “Real-Time.” We receive your photos and quickly check our internal list of what is currently needed, looking for a match. We do not have warehouse space (too expensive!) so our process is designed to be real-time, and as efficient as we can make it for everyone involved.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s4\">We will reply quickly to let you know if there is a match and then go about scheduling a donation drop off that is convenient for you.  If we have a match and you need your donation to be picked up (rather than you dropping it off) we will also schedule that as well.  Many thanks again for your generous support of our high-impact programs which help homeless families and individuals find a rapid return to housing and long-term self-sufficiency! </span></p>\r\n&nbsp;','Furniture Donations','','publish','closed','closed','','furniture-donations','','','2015-08-18 19:35:00','2015-08-19 02:35:00','',210,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?page_id=214',87,'page','',0),(215,2,'2013-09-30 22:14:20','2013-09-30 22:14:20','<h1><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-397\" src=\"http://ivsn.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/donate_homeless_girl_facepaint-320x213.jpg\" alt=\"donate_homeless_girl_facepaint\" width=\"320\" height=\"213\" />Party With A Purpose</h1>\r\n<strong>Make your celebration matter</strong>\r\n\r\nTurn your next event or party into a fundraiser for InnVision Shelter Network. Raise money and awareness for homeless families by asking your guests to donate money or gift certificates to IVSN in lieu of traditional gifts.\r\n<h2>How it Works</h2>\r\nAs you prepare to host a Party with a Purpose, in addition to preparing the guest list and supplies, here are a few simple steps to follow:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Determine what you want to ask your guests to bring. You could request monetary donations, gift cards, or specific items. <a title=\"Donate Items\" href=\"http://ivsn.wpengine.com/donate/donate-items/\">View our donation wish list</a>.</li>\r\n	<li>Contact IVSN to tell us when and where your party is, and how many guests will be attending.</li>\r\n	<li>We will send you brochures for your party, so your guests will be informed about the impact of their donation.</li>\r\n	<li>Send the collected donations to IVSN with your guests’ names and contact information. We will send them a meaningful thank-you letter for their generous donations!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Party Ideas</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Birthday Parties</li>\r\n	<li>Bar/Bat Mitzvah Celebrations</li>\r\n	<li>Weddings</li>\r\n	<li>Anniversaries</li>\r\n	<li>Holiday Parties: at work or home</li>\r\n	<li>Dinner/Cocktail Parties</li>\r\n	<li>In-Home Sales Parties: donate a portion of the total sales from jewelry, accessories, home decor, and more!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Testimonials</h2>\r\n<strong>Ally M.</strong> of Palo Alto hosted her Sweet 16 Party with a Purpose. Instead of receiving gifts from her high school friends, she asked for financial donations to support programs at Shelter Network. Ally raised a total of $1,500!\r\n\r\n<strong>Eli K.</strong> of Hillsborough asked his friends to donate to Shelter Network for his bar mitzvah. Eli raised $2,000!\r\n\r\n<strong>Jessica S.</strong> hosted a custom jewelry party in her home and donated $8,500 from a portion of the sales!\r\n<h2>Sign Up Today!</h2>\r\nDo you want to host a Party with a Purpose for InnVision Shelter Network? Let us know! Contact Harriet Pecot at (650) 685-5880 ext. 138 or <a href=\"mailto:hpecot@ivsn.org\">hpecot@ivsn.org</a>.','Party With A Purpose','','publish','closed','closed','','party-with-a-purpose','','','2015-10-09 13:31:31','2015-10-09 20:31:31','',43,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?page_id=215',86,'page','',0),(216,2,'2013-09-30 22:16:13','2013-09-30 22:16:13','<h1 class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Plan Your Holiday Giving and Volunteering Now!</span></h1>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Generous support from the community during the holiday season is vital to creating a warm and meaningful experience </span><span class=\"s1\">for thousands of homeless adults and children in IVSN programs. Start planning now for ways you can help this year!</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Questions? Contact our Volunteer Associate Jessie Ellington at <a href=\"mailto:jellington@ivsn.org\"><span class=\"s2\">jellington@ivsn.org</span></a> or (650) 685-5880 ext. 180.<img class=\"wp-image-1504 aligncenter\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Carolands-Holiday-Party_Children.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"450\" height=\"300\" /></span></p>\r\n\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"1\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h2>Give</h2>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Give a Financial Contribution</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\">IVSN relies on generous financial support from the community. Your gift ensures that we may continue to provide high quality, effective services year-round. <a href=\"http://ivsn.wpengine.com/donate/\">Donate Now</a></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Donate in Honor of a Friend or Family Member</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\">Make a financial donation to IVSN in honor of a loved one. We will mail the honoree a special holiday card with artwork created by children at our shelters. <a href=\"http://ivsn.wpengine.com/donate/\">Donate Now</a></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong><a href=\"https://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/form73/index.html?1444862360261\" target=\"_blank\">Host a “Party with a Purpose”</a></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\">In lieu of traditional presents, ask your friends, family, or coworkers to bring a cash gift for neighbors in need to your next holiday gathering.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong><a href=\"https://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/form73/index.html?1444862360261\" target=\"_blank\">Adopt-a-Household</a></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\">Every IVSN client participating in housing services will receive two holiday gift wishes. You can make these wishes come true by “adopting” a family or individual. Purchase a single gift, or shop for a whole family!</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong><a href=\"https://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/form73/index.html?1444862360261\" target=\"_blank\">Donate a Thanksgiving or Holiday Dinner Basket</a></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\">With your donation of gift cards and/or dinner baskets, every family in IVSN programs will be able to enjoy a holiday meal together.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong><a href=\"https://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/form73/index.html?1444862360261\" target=\"_blank\">Host a Gift Drive</a></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\">Ask your friends, family or co-workers to bring gifts for homeless neighbors. Most needed items include gift cards ($30 value), linens, new socks and undergarments.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Volunteer</h2>\r\n<strong><a href=\"https://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/form73/index.html?1444862360261\" target=\"_blank\">Plan a Holiday Party at a Shelter</a></strong>\r\n\r\nHost a party or a “Cookies &amp; Carols” event at one of our shelter residences with your friends, coworkers, or volunteer group. A festive celebration makes the holidays bright and memorable for our clients.  <a href=\"http://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/form43/index.html\" target=\"_blank\">\r\n</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/form73/index.html?1444862360261\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Provide and Serve Holiday Meals</strong></a>\r\n\r\nGather a group of your friends or coworkers to provide and serve a special meal to our residents. On Thanksgiving Day, Christmas Eve, Christmas Day, New Year’s Eve, or New Year’s Day—in addition to weekends (Saturdays and Sundays) throughout the year.<a href=\"https://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/form73/index.html?1444862360261\" target=\"_blank\">\r\n</a>\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Meal Provider Volunteer Manual\" href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/volunteer/meal-programs/\">Click here to find availability and sign up to provide a meal.</a>\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"https://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/form73/index.html?1444862360261\" target=\"_blank\">Decorate a Shelter</a></strong>\r\n\r\nVolunteer with a group of your friends or colleagues to bring in decorations and turn a shelter into a winter wonderland. <a href=\"http://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/form43/index.html\" target=\"_blank\">\r\n</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Holiday Giving','','publish','closed','closed','','holiday-giving','','','2015-10-19 15:24:01','2015-10-19 22:24:01','',43,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?page_id=216',85,'page','',0),(217,2,'2013-09-30 22:17:32','2013-09-30 22:17:32','<h1>Sponsors</h1>\r\nThank you to our generous corporate and community partners!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[one_half]<a href=\"http://www.adobe.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-593\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Adobe-Logo.png\" alt=\"Adobe Logo\" width=\"114\" height=\"144\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.franklintempleton.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-589\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Franklin-Templeton-Logo-320x152.png\" alt=\"Franklin Templeton Logo\" width=\"200\" height=\"95\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://gilead.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-596\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Gilead-Logo-320x80.png\" alt=\"Gilead Logo\" width=\"200\" height=\"50\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.landroversj.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-605\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Land_Rover_San_Jose_Logo.png\" alt=\"Land_Rover_San_Jose_Logo\" width=\"122\" height=\"89\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.oracle.com/index.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-598\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Oracle-Logo-320x41.png\" alt=\"Oracle Logo\" width=\"200\" height=\"26\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.sobrato.org/\" target=\"_blank\"><img