 President and Chief Administrative Officer, Franklin Templeton Investments\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#EverettOliven\"><strong>Everett Oliven</strong></a> | National Vice President of Sales, Strategic Customer Program, SAP America\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#RachelPerkel\"><strong>Rachel Perkel</strong></a> | Senior Vice President of Wealth Mangement Marketing, Wells Fargo Bank, N.A.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#RonaldReis\"><strong>Ronald Reis</strong></a> | Former Co-Owner &amp; Vice President, Data Safe\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#JoeStockwell\"><strong>Joe Stockwell</strong></a> | Principal, Odyssey Management Capital\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#CherylWestmont\"><strong>Cheryl Westmont</strong></a> | Landscape Designer &amp; Owner, Gardenscapes\r\n<h1>Advisory Board</h1>\r\n<strong>William L. Butler | </strong>CEO and Founder, W. L. Butler Construction, Inc.\r\n\r\n<strong>Congresswoman Anna Eshoo | </strong>U.S. Representative, California\'s 18th Congressional District\r\n\r\n<strong>Roger Hagman | </strong>Architect, Hagman Associates\r\n\r\n<strong>Monica Ip | </strong>Partner, Evidentia Consulting, LLP\r\n\r\n<strong>Marcia Pade |</strong> Former Board Chair, InnVision Shelter Network\r\n\r\n<strong>William V. Regan, III | </strong>Former Board Chair, InnVision Shelter Network\r\n\r\n<strong>Congresswoman Jackie Speier | </strong>U.S. Representative, California\'s 14th Congressional District\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<b id=\"RodFerguson\">Rod Ferguson, Chair\r\n</b>Co-founder and Venture Capitalist, Panorama Capital\r\n\r\nRod is a co-founder of Panorama Capital, a venture capital firm that spun off from JPMorgan Partners (JPMP) in July 2006, where he focuses primarily on life sciences investments. He joined JPMP as a Managing Director in their life sciences venture practice in 2001. From 1999 to 2001, Dr. Ferguson was a partner at InterWest Partners, a venture capital firm, where he focused on life sciences investments. Prior to InterWest, he held a variety of management positions over an 11-year career at Genentech, Inc., most recently as Senior Director of Business and Corporate Development, responsible for worldwide licensing transactions for both technology and pharmaceutical products. Prior to joining Genentech, Inc., Rod was an associate with the law firm McCutchen, Doyle, Brown, &amp; Enersen (currently known as Bingham McCutchen llp). Rod serves on the technology advisory board of The Economist, a variety of advisory boards in the life sciences industry, and two non-profit boards.  In addition, he serves on the board of directors of several private life science companies. Rod earned a B.S. in Biochemistry<b> </b>from the University of Illinois, a Ph.D. in Biochemistry from the State University of New York, and a J.D. from Northwestern University.\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<b id=\"MatthewBahls\">Matthew Bahls, Vice-Chair\r\n</b>Associate Director of Development, Stanford School of Engineering\r\n\r\nMatthew has worked for Stanford University in a variety of capacities over the last ten years, including a stint as Assistant Director of Community Relations. He is currently an Associate Director of Development for Stanford\'s School of Engineering. In addition to his volunteer role with InnVision Shelter Network, Matt is on the Board of the Downtown Streets Team and an ad hoc advisor for Canopy. He is also a docent at the Jasper Ridge Biological Preserve. Matt holds a B.A. from Wesleyan University, and a Masters in Chinese and analytic philosophy from Boston University.\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<b id=\"JohnBrew\">John Brew, Treasurer\r\n</b>Partner, Atlas Technology Group LLC\r\n\r\nJohn is a partner at Atlas Technology Group LLC, a firm specializing in M&amp;A advisory services to the technology industry. Previously, John spent 22 years in investment banking with RBC Capital Markets and Robertson Stephens &amp; Co., leading teams in both corporate finance and M&amp;A. John holds an MBA from The Wharton School at the University of Pennsylvania, and a B.S. from Stanford University.\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<b id=\"StevanLuzaich\">Stevan N. Luzaich, Secretary\r\n</b>Partner, Corey, Luzaich, Pliska, De Ghetaldi, &amp; Nastari, LLP\r\n\r\nSteve joined the law firm in 1975. A Bay Area native, Steve has more than 35 years of legal experience, and leads one of the most respected estate-planning practices in San Mateo County. During his years of practice, he has developed and implemented virtually every type of estate-planning mechanism. His legal experience also includes partnership and corporation formation, as well as real estate transactions. Steve has served as legal counsel for the Millbrae Lion\'s Club since 1978, and as counsel for CORA (Community Overcoming Relationship Abuse). Steve holds a B.A. from the University of California at Berkeley, and a J.D. from Hastings College of the Law, University of California.\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<b id=\"MarianneBaldrica\">Marianne Baldrica\r\n</b>Regional Vice President, NASDAQ OMX Group\r\n\r\nMarianne Baldrica is the Regional Vice President for NASDAQ OMX Group. In this role she develops and executes the strategic direction for oversight of all NASDAQ-listed companies in the western, working closely with CEOs and executives of some of the most well-known companies in the world. Under her leadership, a team of relationship managers is charged with building and enhancing customer relationships with NASDAQ’s listed companies throughout the 13 western states, British Columbia and Alberta, Canada. The region includes 700 companies, 51 of which are in the NASDAQ 100 index. Marianne’s previous experience includes roles at DEMER IR Consulting and SAIC. She has a bachelor’s degree from the University of San Francisco and completed graduate level coursework at Stanford University. She lives in Los Altos and volunteers with the Junior League Oakland/East Bay, Second Harvest Food Bank and the American Heart Association.\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<b id=\"HollyCampbell\"><b>Holly Campbell</b>\r\n</b>Vice President, Corporate Responsibility, Adobe Systems\r\n\r\nHolly oversees Adobe’s global Corporate Responsibility strategy, which includes programs that make a meaningful impact on youth development, the environment, our communities, and the world at large. In addition to the sustainability efforts, programs such as Adobe Youth Voices and Adobe’s Youth Coding Initiative are inspiring the next generation of creatives and changemakers, and providing educational opportunities to underserved youth. Prior to joining Adobe, Holly worked in corporate and international communications for Quantum Corp. She holds a Bachelor of Arts degree in art history from Humboldt State University, and was a fellow in the art history and museum studies graduate program at the University of Southern California.\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<b id=\"ChristinaDickerson\">Christina Dickerson</b>\r\n\r\nVice President, Corporate Development, Corium International, Inc.\r\n\r\nChristina directs corporate development and governance at Corium and holds responsibility for strategic planning for the company.  Prior to joining Corium, Christina spent 16 years in investment banking, serving in both advisory and portfolio management roles at Salomon Brothers, the Jim Pattison Group and J.P. Morgan.  She has been involved in leadership and fundraising positions in a variety of civic and community organizations, including Sacred Heart Schools and Stanford University. Christina holds an A.B. in International Relations and an A.B. in Economics from Stanford.\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<b id=\"OliverKohler\">Oliver Kohler\r\n</b>Chief Administrative Officer and Sr. Vice President of Global Business Services, Cisco Systems\r\n\r\nOlivier leads the Global Business Services organization for Cisco Systems, including oversight of the Customer/Partner Experience, Financial Shared Services, Global Procurement Services, Real Estate/Workplace Resources, and Business Intelligence and Information Management. Prior to joining Cisco, Olivier held successive positions of increasing leadership at Hewlett Packard Company, starting as a Software Engineer in Geneva, Switzerland, and culminating with the Global Head and General Manager of Enterprise Strategic Alliances in Cupertino. Olivier has been active as a volunteer with multiple hunger relief organizations, and is a certified Soccer Coach with American Youth Soccer Organziation. Olivier attended the Geneva Business School, studying Business Management, Accounting, and Information Technology.\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<b id=\"JulieGruber\">Julie Gruber\r\n</b>Senior Vice President General Counsel , Gap Inc.\r\n\r\nJulie Gruber is Senior Vice President General Counsel for Gap Inc., overseeing advertising, commercial law and worldwide intellectual property matters. Before joining Gap in 1998, Julie worked at Bronson, Bronson and McKinnon in San Francisco and clerked for the Honorable Ronald M. Whyte in the Federal District Court in San Jose. In addition to her work with InnVision Shelter Network, Julie serves on the Executive Committee for the American Heart Association’s Go Red For Women Campaign. She is a graduate of the University of California’s Hastings College of the Law and received her B.A. in Political Science from Yale University.\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<b id=\"DavidLichtenger\">David Lichtenger\r\n</b>Managing Partner, Intrepid Capital\r\n\r\nDavid is an active real estate investor as well as a proven entrepreneur and executive with over 25 years of real estate and construction experience. He is a General Partner of California Residential Opportunity Fund III L.P. Since CROF has started investing in 2010, it has had an interest in 822 homes. David founded Intrepid Capital in 2008 and Integrated Facility Solutions (IFS) in 1999. David has been involved in the planning, design, and construction of over 10 million square feet of projects. Prior to IFS, David was involved in various real estate development projects as well as founding and managing his own contracting company. David has been active in many associations including: Board Member and Vice Chair of the Lincoln Club of Northern California, Hoover Institute (Member of Hoover Council), SIEPR (Active Associate), Silicon Valley Leadership Group (SVLG), the American Institute of Architects (AIA), InnVision (Board Member), and The Triple \"C\" Foundation (Board &amp; Founder). He is also the Chairman of the Scientific &amp; Medical Research Facilities Working Group of the California Institute of Regenerative Medicine (CIRM). David attended Rutgers University and Columbia University.\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<b id=\"RayMueller\">Ray Mueller\r\n</b>Mayor, City of Menlo Park\r\n\r\nRay Mueller is Mayor of the City of Menlo Park, and the Chief of Staff to Santa Clara County Supervisor S. Joseph Simitian. Ray was elected to the Menlo Park City Council as the top vote getter in the 2012 General Election. In 2013, became Mayor of five member council charged with oversight of municipal services and budget, enacting ordinances and determining land use policy within jurisdictional limits. Menlo Park is home to Sand Hill Road, where many of the Silicon Valley’s top venture capital firms reside, the global headquarters of Facebook, and to InnVision Shelter Network. Ray is a California native, and has been a resident of the Bay Area for close to 20 years. Ray holds a J.D. from Hastings College of the Law and a B.S. from UC Berkeley.\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<b id=\"MarquiseMurphy\">Marquise Murphy\r\n</b>Realtor, Home Smart Platinum Living\r\n\r\nMarquise Murphy is a licensed realtor with Home Smart Platinum Living, focusing on residential property transactions. His career includes banking experience with Wells Fargo, JP Morgan, and HSBC. Marquise serves as the Vice Chair President for the Young Professionals Network of San Mateo County. He was appointed to InnVision Shelter Network’s Board of Directors after graduating as a client of IVSN’s Maple Street Shelter in Redwood City. Marquise brings his personal experience with IVSN’s services to influence his input on strategic decision-making at the board level.\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<b id=\"KevinOConnor\">Kevin O\'Connor\r\n</b>Senior vice President and Chief Administrative Officer, Franklin Templeton Investments\r\n\r\nAs CAO and Senior Vice President of Franklin Templeton Investments, Kevin’s primary areas of responsibility include corporate communications, global public relations, employee communications, executive communications and community relations. In addition, he works with the executive team to establish corporate priorities and build understanding throughout the organization. Since joining as a customer service associate in 1991, he has held a variety of retirement and institutional services and operations leadership positions. Kevin holds an M.B.A from the University of San Francisco, and a B.A. in English from the University of California at Davis.\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<b id=\"EverettOliven\">Everett Oliven\r\n</b>National Vice President of Sales, Strategic Customer Program, SAP America\r\n\r\nEverett has over 20 years’ experience as a sales leader and management consultant. Since joining SAP America in 2002, he has served as a Regional Vice President of Sales and Chief Operation Officer, Financial Services. Previous to SAP, Everett was a consultant with Booz Allen &amp; Hamilton in San Francisco, and Accenture in Chicago and Buenos Aires, Argentina. Before joining the InnVision Shelter Network board, he served on the board of the San Francisco chapter of Rebuild Together. Everett holds a BA in Political Science from Honors College at the University of Michigan in Ann Arbor and earned his MBA at the Wharton School at the University of Pennsylvania.\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<b id=\"RachelPerkel\" style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">Rachel Perkel\r\n</b>Senior Vice President of Wealth Management Marketing, Wells Fargo Bank, N.A.\r\n\r\nRachel has been with Wells Fargo since 2004 and is currently the head of Marketing for Wells Fargo\'s Wealth Management Group. Prior to her current role, Rachel was the Head of Product and served on the Board of Directors of Wells Fargo Investments. She was also responsible for the WellsTrade online brokerage business.  Before joining Wells Fargo, Rachel worked at Charles Schwab for nine years, where she held a variety of marketing and product management roles.  Rachel has also worked as a product manager at Advent Software, and has held positions as a buy-side analyst at Fidelity Investments and an investment banker at Kidder, Peabody.\r\n\r\nRachel has served on boards and committees for numbers of Bay Area of non-profit organizations, including the San Francisco Jewish Community Federation, the Bureau of Jewish Education, and the Ronald C. Wornick Jewish Day School. Rachel earned her B.A. degree in Economics from Brandeis University, and an MBA from Stanford University.\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<b id=\"RonaldReis\">Ronald P. Reis\r\n</b>Former Co-Owner &amp; Vice President, Data Safe\r\n\r\nRon recently completed his second career, having worked with his brother as Co-Owner and Vice President of Data Safe—an off-site storage and information management firm serving 2,200 businesses throughout Northern California.  He was President of the industry\'s trade association, PRISM International, in 2001. Prior to Data Safe, Ron was Director of Mercy Center in Central California, Assistant Professor of Speech Pathology at the University of Denver, and Chief of Speech Pathology &amp; Audiology at Hillside Hospital in Ohio. He has been a private practitioner, specializing in stuttering and speech-phobic businesspeople. Ron currently volunteers for St. Vincent de Paul at Fair Oaks Community Center in Redwood City.  He holds Bachelor\'s and Master\'s Degrees from the University of Redlands, and a Ph.D. from Kent State University.\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<b id=\"JoeStockwell\">Joe Stockwell\r\n</b>Principal, Odyssey Management Capital\r\n\r\nJoe Stockwell is currently a Principal with Odyssey Management Capital specializing in Telecom and Media. Joe has held a variety of leadership positions in the Communications and Media space, including Corporate Development at WURL, Inc., President and Chairman at PT Access Networks, President of Epik Communications, and Sr. Director of Corporate Development at Apple. Joe holds a BBA in Marketing from Cleveland State University, and a JD from Boston College.\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<b id=\"CherylWestmont\">Cheryl Westmont\r\n</b>Landscape Designer &amp; Owner, Gardenscapes\r\n\r\nCheryl has been an avid gardener for over twenty years and her family\'s garden in Hillsborough is a showcase of her creativity and care. She has taken landscape design classes at the College of San Mateo, has a library of books and magazines that she has read, as well as references for clients, and is an Associate of the Association of Professional Landscape Designers (APLD). Her prior career was as a health care executive in the role of marketing, with the majority of her professional career as the Marketing Manager at the Palo Alto Medical Foundation.  Cheryl earned a B.A. in Business Administration from Texas A&amp;M University.','Board Of Directors','','publish','closed','closed','','board-of-directors','','','2015-09-11 15:38:42','2015-09-11 22:38:42','',6,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?page_id=239',78,'page','',0),(240,2,'2013-09-30 23:22:53','2013-09-30 23:22:53','<h1>Leadership Team</h1>\r\n<a href=\"#BruceIves\"><strong>Bruce Ives</strong></a> | Chief Executive Officer\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#BrianGreenberg\"><strong>Brian Greenberg</strong></a>, Ph.D. | Vice President, Programs &amp; Services\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#JimGreer\"><strong>James B. Greer</strong></a> | Interim Chief Financial Officer\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#AmyWright\"><strong>Amy Wright</strong></a> | Vice President, Development\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#DwightPowery\"><strong>Dwight Powery</strong></a> | Vice President, Strategy, Technology, and Operations\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#LorenaCollins\"><strong>Lorena Collins</strong></a> | Associate Vice President, Programs and Services\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#JacobLile\"><strong>Marc Sabin</strong></a> | Senior Director, Programs and Services\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#PhilipDah\"><strong>Philip Dah</strong></a> | Senior Director, Multi-Service Centers\r\n<div align=\"center\"></div>\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<b id=\"BruceIves\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1394 size-thumbnail\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/untitled-3-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" />Bruce Ives\r\n</b>Chief Executive Officer\r\n\r\nBruce is an accomplished executive with extensive management and leadership experience gained during 19 years at Hewlett-Packard where he held diverse positions of increasing management responsibility overseeing large teams and budgets. While at Hewlett-Packard, Bruce also founded and led the legal team’s pro bono program, helping countless tenants, veterans, and women facing domestic violence, as well as others who need but can’t afford legal services. Under his guidance, the effort has grown to over 600 volunteers worldwide.\r\n\r\nRegarding his leadership role of this organization, Bruce says, “InnVision Shelter Network has a highly respected team with a proven track record for getting results. For decades, they have successfully provided the resources needed to help families and individuals break the cycle of homelessness. I am honored to be chosen to lead an organization where I can put my community values and business skills to best use.”\r\n\r\nBruce’s lifetime commitment to public service began with his first job out of college at an inner-city school district. After law school, he joined the Los Angeles Public Defender’s office.He went on to be the District Director for Congresswoman Anna Eshoo in San Mateo and Santa Clara counties. A resident of Menlo Park, he was an elected Trustee of the Menlo Park School District and currently serves on the Board of Directors of Public Advocates, a public interest law firm that works on issues of housing and education equity. He also serves as Treasurer for Congregation Beth Am in Los Altos Hills.\r\n\r\nBruce earned a Bachelor of Arts degree from Harvard University, and a Juris Doctor degree from the University of California, Berkeley.\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<b id=\"BrianGreenberg\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-243\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/greenberg.png\" alt=\"greenberg\" width=\"103\" height=\"141\" />Brian Greenberg, Ph.D.</b>\r\n\r\nVice President, Programs and Services\r\n\r\nBrian Greenberg, Ph.D. manages InnVision Shelter Network\'s shelter and housing programs and direct services personnel.  He is a licensed psychologist with over 25 years of experience developing and managing behavioral health and housing programs. Prior to his current position, Dr. Greenberg worked for Walden House for 18 years, overseeing research and evaluation, adolescent services, and development.\r\n\r\nBrian has published articles in peer-reviewed journals concerning his work with substance abuse treatment research and housing, and serves as a clinical consultant for drug treatment programming. He received his undergraduate degree from Ohio State University and his Master\'s degree and Ph.D. from the California School of Professional Psychology in Berkeley, CA.\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<b id=\"JimGreer\"><img class=\" size-thumbnail wp-image-1430 alignleft\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/JBG1-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"James Greer\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" />James B. Greer</b>\r\n\r\nInterim Chief Financial Officer\r\n\r\nJim Greer oversees the accounting and finance functions at InnVision Shelter Network. Jim joined the agency in early 2014, bringing deep strategic CFO experience to IVSN from both for-profit and nonprofit organizations. He has over 35 years of accounting and finance experience, over 25 of those as CFO. He has been CFO of 4Cs of San Mateo and The Parkinson’s Institute locally. Jim holds a bachelor’s degree from Stanford, and an MBA from UCLA with a dual concentration in Accounting and Finance.\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-248\" src=\"http://ivsn.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/wright.png\" alt=\"wright\" width=\"103\" height=\"141\" />\r\n\r\n<b id=\"AmyWright\">Amy Wright\r\n</b>Vice President, Development\r\n\r\nAmy Wright joined the development team in 2004, where she took on many development roles and established the Leadership Gifts program to increase revenue from private individuals. As Vice President of Development, she oversees all private and public fundraising activities to support InnVision Shelter Network\'s $16M annual budget. Prior to joining the nonprofit, Amy worked in the private sector for more than 15 years in strategic marketing and investor relations in international telecommunications, internet communications, and software development companies based in Silicon Valley.\r\n\r\nAmy enjoys being engaged in her community and volunteers for Jasper Ridge Farm and other local nonprofit organizations. She holds a B.A. in Business Administration from the University of San Diego.\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-246\" src=\"http://ivsn.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/powery.png\" alt=\"powery\" width=\"103\" height=\"141\" />\r\n\r\n<b id=\"DwightPowery\">Dwight Powery\r\n</b>Vice President, Strategy, Technology, and Operations\r\n\r\nDwight Powery joined InnVision Shelter Network through Encore Fellowships, a program designed to match experienced professionals to nonprofits solving critical social problems. He is an experienced Hewlett Packard executive of 28 years, with proven leadership in global account management, global operations, process and efficiency improvement and customer service delivery across multi-functional teams.\r\n\r\nDwight\'s community service experience includes work with the Arthritis Foundation of Northern California, coaching youth basketball and as a board member of Friends of CARRA (Children Arthritis Rheumatology and Research Alliance). He graduated with a B.A. in Computer Science from Columbia University and attended the Executive Development program at the Fuqua School of Business at Duke University. Dwight is married to Maria and has three daughters.  He enjoys cycling, running and digital photography.\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-650\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/LorenaCollins2.png\" alt=\"LorenaCollins2\" width=\"103\" height=\"141\" />\r\n\r\n<b id=\"LorenaCollins\">Lorena Collins\r\n</b>Associate Vice President, Programs and Services\r\n\r\nLorena Collins has over 30 years of experience in nonprofit work in the fields of homeless services, mental health, and drug and alcohol recovery treatment. She joined InnVision Shelter Network in 2005, serving as the Senior Director of IVSN’s Montgomery and Julian Street Inn, as well as several transitional and permanent housing programs in San Jose. In her current role as the Associate Vice President of Programs and Services, Lorena oversees the programming and staff at nine shelters, in addition to IVSN’s Alumni Association, Motel Voucher Program, and the Central Intake Department for homeless families.\r\n\r\nLorena volunteers her time as a board member of Building Peaceful Families, a nonprofit dedicated to improving the health and well-being of children, and has served as a long-standing team member of the Santa Clara County Superior Court STOP calendar, which works with convicted domestic violence offenders with mental health conditions. Lorena holds a bachelor’s degree in Communication Disorders and Sciences from San Jose State University, and has extensive experience conducting trainings in crisis intervention and mental health services. She is also fluent in American Sign Language.\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<b id=\"JacobLile\">\r\nMarc Sabin</b>\r\n\r\nSenior Director, Programs and Services\r\n\r\n*Bio coming soon*\r\n<div align=\"center\"></div>\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<b id=\"JacobLile\"> </b>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div align=\"center\"></div>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-652\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/PhilipDah.png\" alt=\"PhilipDah\" width=\"103\" height=\"141\" />\r\n\r\n<b id=\"PhilipDah\">Philip Dah\r\n</b>Senior Director, Multi-Service Centers\r\n\r\nPhilip Dah oversees InnVision Shelter Network’s multi-service center, the Opportunity Services Center, and other service programs in Palo Alto. Philip began his career at IVSN when the Urban Ministry of Palo Alto, a community organization, merged with InnVision in 2000. Philip served as Program Director at IVSN’s Montgomery Street Inn from 2004 to 2005, and was then promoted to direct the agency’s Palo Alto programs in 2006.\r\n\r\nPhilip was born and raised in Ghana and studied Business Administration at the University of Ghana. He moved to the United States in 1996, and now spends most of his free time with his family camping, cooking, biking and attending music festivals in Northern California.','Leadership Team','','publish','closed','closed','','leadership-team','','','2015-07-01 11:40:42','2015-07-01 18:40:42','',6,'http://ivsn.wpengine.com/?page_id=240',77,'page','',0),(241,2,'2013-09-30 23:15:46','2013-09-30 23:15