,'image/jpeg',0),(480,12,'2013-10-15 19:22:14','2013-10-15 19:22:14','','ted2','','inherit','closed','open','','ted2','','','2013-10-15 19:22:14','2013-10-15 19:22:14','',459,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/ted2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(490,12,'2013-10-21 22:41:57','2013-10-21 22:41:57','','sabrina_thumbnail','','inherit','closed','open','','sabrina_thumbnail','','','2013-10-21 22:41:57','2013-10-21 22:41:57','',435,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/sabrina_thumbnail.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(491,12,'2013-10-21 22:43:49','2013-10-21 22:43:49','','Meisha1_thumbnail','','inherit','closed','open','','meisha1_thumbnail','','','2013-10-21 22:43:49','2013-10-21 22:43:49','',431,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Meisha1_thumbnail.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(494,12,'2013-10-21 23:12:14','2013-10-21 23:12:14','','ivsn_newsletter_091013_web','','inherit','closed','open','','ivsn_newsletter_091013_web','','','2013-10-21 23:12:14','2013-10-21 23:12:14','',250,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ivsn_newsletter_091013_web.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(498,12,'2013-10-22 22:47:53','2013-10-22 22:47:53','<h1>What Do You Care About?</h1>\r\n<h2>Share Your Interests with IVSN</h2>\r\nHomelessness affects people from all walks of life, cutting across every segment of our community.  With that in mind, we want to communicate in a way that speaks to you.\r\n\r\nPlease take our 2 minute survey and share what inspires you!\r\n<a id=\"formAnchor1238418508\" name=\"form1238418508\"></a>\r\n<script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"http://www.formsite.com/include/form/embedManager.js?1238418508\"></script><script type=\"text/javascript\">// <![CDATA[\r\nEmbedManager.embed({\r\n	key: \"http://www.formsite.com/res/showFormEmbed?EParam=PyBo85CFjhEsbxUbMlcXKFDT8VXvnlRr&1238418508\",\r\n	width: \"100%\"\r\n});\r\n// ]]></script>\r\n<!-- Notes:  To control the width of the form, change width: \"100%\" to any number or percentage. To pre-populate fields in the form or to use a custom resize callback, see http://www.formsite.com/documentation/embedded-form.html -->','Interest Survey','','publish','closed','open','','interest-survey','','','2013-10-22 22:58:51','2013-10-22 22:58:51','',9,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=498',59,'page','',0),(501,12,'2013-10-22 23:22:11','2013-10-22 23:22:11','','breakfast video thumbnail','','inherit','closed','open','','breakfast-video-thumbnail','','','2013-10-22 23:22:11','2013-10-22 23:22:11','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/breakfast-video-thumbnail.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(503,12,'2013-10-23 00:04:53','2013-10-23 00:04:53','','Household Donations','','inherit','closed','open','','household-donations','','','2013-10-23 00:04:53','2013-10-23 00:04:53','',210,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Household-Donations.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(505,2,'2013-10-23 20:12:41','2013-10-23 20:12:41','[one_half]<h1>Our Services: Beyond the Bed</h1>\r\nInnVision Shelter Network’s “Beyond the Bed” model combines shelter/housing with comprehensive services that enable homeless families and individuals to rapidly return to permanent housing and self-sufficiency.\r\n<h2>Shelter &amp; Services That Go “Beyond the Bed”</h2>\r\n“Beyond the Bed” is just as it sounds: more than a bed. Our clients have access to an extensive array of life-changing supportive services beyond shelter, coordinated by dedicated and experienced Case Managers and direct services staff.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><b>Case Management: </b>Our trained Case Managers support clients’ unique needs, helping them manage budgets, connect with resources, and make active progress toward regaining permanent housing.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Housing and Job Search Assistance:</b> Staff and volunteers provide clients with training, tools, and resources to find and secure affordable housing and employment.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Financial Literacy and Savings: </b>We teach clients to manage a personal budget and save for emergency needs. Clients in transitional housing must save at least 50% of their income.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Children’s Services: </b>Our therapeutic child care and after-school programs help children and youth overcome the trauma of homelessness and continue their education in a stable environment.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Life Skills Education: </b>We empower our clients with skills for long-term success through nightly workshops on financial literacy, parenting, nutrition, and other life skills.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Additional “Beyond the Bed” Services:</b> We offer an array of services that go “beyond the bed” to meet our clients’ unique needs and enable them to become self-sufficient for the long term.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nHard work and commitment are required from the homeless men, women, and children we serve. In return, InnVision Shelter Network provides safe shelter, nutritious food, counseling services, therapeutic childcare and after-school activities, job and housing search assistance, and additional “Beyond the Bed” services.\r\n[/one_half]\r\n[one_half_last]\r\n<img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-418\" alt=\"services_homeless_mother_son_family_sign\" src=\"http://ivsn.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/services_homeless_mother_son_family_sign-320x214.jpg\" width=\"320\" height=\"214\" />\r\n<h2>Impact</h2>\r\nOur “Beyond the Bed” services deliver high-impact, metrics-based results.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Year after year, 90% of family graduates from our transitional housing program return to permanent housing.</li>\r\n	<li>The average length of stay in shelter is just 150 days—far less than the national average.</li>\r\n	<li>Charity Navigator has awarded us their highest 4-star rating, placing InnVision Shelter Network in the top 5% of all ranked nonprofits.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nInnVision Shelter Network’s “Beyond the Bed” model works. It is efficient and effective, and empowers our clients to achieve ongoing self-sufficiency and a rapidly return to permanent housing.\r\n[/one_half_last]','2 Column page','','publish','closed','open','','2-column-page','','','2013-10-31 08:27:56','2013-10-31 15:27:56','',31,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=505',58,'page','',0),(511,2,'2013-10-23 14:14:56','2013-10-23 21:14:56','<h2>Lynne Twist, Keynote Address</h2>\r\nLynne Twist, a global visionary and author of <em>The Soul of Money</em>, delivers a moving keynote about the power of taking a stand to make a positive change in our communities.\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/DF-j9JvLTNA?list=UUyBRiERCgWhTIorZARRZ-pg\" height=\"315\" width=\"560\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n<h2>Karae Lisle, CEO</h2>\r\nKarae Lisle, CEO of InnVision Shelter Network, shares about the reality of homelessness on the Peninsula and in Silicon Valley, and illustrates IVSN\'s \"Beyond the Bed\" services that work to permanently end homelessness.\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/Z3O0RwWesdQ?list=UUyBRiERCgWhTIorZARRZ-pg\" height=\"315\" width=\"560\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n<h2>Susan Manheimer, San Mateo Chief of Police</h2>\r\nChief Manheimer shares her personal perspective on partnering with InnVision Shelter Network to end homelessness in our community.\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/4IihEM9t61w?list=UUyBRiERCgWhTIorZARRZ-pg\" height=\"315\" width=\"560\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n<h2>Jillian Manus, IVSN Board of Directors</h2>\r\nIVSN Board Member Jillian Manus surprises the client speaker Sabrina with a special donation, and inspires event guests to support the nonprofit\'s programs to end homelessness.\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/1CNPr8ZwCes?list=UUyBRiERCgWhTIorZARRZ-pg\" height=\"315\" width=\"560\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>','Video of the Benefit Breakfast 2013','','publish','open','open','','video-of-the-benefit-breakfast-2013','','','2014-01-29 08:32:34','