3 10:17:08','2013-11-13 18:17:08','',546,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/daughter-kissing-mom.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(548,12,'2013-11-13 10:20:27','2013-11-13 18:20:27','','daughter kissing mom_sq','','inherit','closed','open','','daughter-kissing-mom_sq','','','2013-11-13 10:20:27','2013-11-13 18:20:27','',546,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/daughter-kissing-mom_sq.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(553,12,'2013-11-13 15:30:05','2013-11-13 23:30:05','','Save the Date Icon','','inherit','closed','open','','save-the-date-icon','','','2013-11-13 15:30:05','2013-11-13 23:30:05','',49,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Save-the-Date-Icon.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(558,12,'2013-11-14 17:04:02','2013-11-15 01:04:02','','IVSN Breakfast Sponsor Recognition_March 13 2014','','inherit','closed','open','','ivsn-breakfast-sponsor-recognition_march-13-2014','','','2013-11-14 17:04:02','2013-11-15 01:04:02','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/IVSN-Breakfast-Sponsor-Recognition_March-13-2014.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(559,12,'2013-11-15 11:44:08','2013-11-15 19:44:08','<h1><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-399\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/donate_homeless_mother_reading-320x213.jpg\" alt=\"donate_homeless_mother_reading\" width=\"320\" height=\"213\" />Donate Stock</h1>\r\nA stock transfer to IVSN is a meaningful way to make an impact on our mission to end homelessness.\r\n<h2>How to Transfer Stock</h2>\r\nTo donate stock or other securities, please print and complete the <a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/IVSN-SecuritiesTransferRequestForm-RBC_UPDATED.docx\" target=\"_blank\">Securities Transfer Request Form (DOC)</a>. Once completed, fax to your broker to complete the transfer.\r\n\r\nAlternatively, you may send the following information to your broker:\r\n\r\nAccount Name: InnVision Shelter Network\r\nDTC#: 0235\r\nAccount #: 303-85228\r\nBroker: RBC Wealth Management\r\nContact: Catherine Chen\r\nPhone: (415) 445-8308\r\n<h2>Send a Copy to IVSN to Ensure Your Donation</h2>\r\nTo ensure that IVSN receives your donation, please send a copy of your Securities Transfer Request Form to IVSN, in addition to sending to you broker. Please send a copy to Ruth Richerson at <a href=\"mailto:rricherson@ivsn.org\" target=\"_blank\">rricherson@ivsn.org</a>, or fax to 650-685-5881.\r\n<h2>Questions?</h2>\r\nPlease contact Ruth Richerson at <a href=\"mailto:rricherson@ivsn.org\" target=\"_blank\">rricherson@ivsn.org</a>, or 650-685-5880 ext. 171.','Donate Stock','','publish','closed','open','','donate-stock','','','2015-10-18 21:57:58','2015-10-19 04:57:58','',43,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=559',57,'page','',0),(565,12,'2013-11-19 08:54:30','2013-11-19 16:54:30','<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-566\" alt=\"christine family_blog\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/christine-family_blog.jpg\" width=\"600\" height=\"398\" />\r\n\r\nMeet Christine, a young wife and mother of baby Logan. Christine was born at Stanford Hospital, and has lived in the Bay Area all her life. After graduating from Woodside High School, she attended San Jose City College, but during her freshman year she experienced a medical emergency. As she put it, “Life had some road bumps in store for me, and I was diagnosed with cervical cancer. I had to drop out of college to receive treatment.”\r\n\r\nDuring this time, a chance meeting brought Christine and her high school sweetheart, Richard, back together. When she finished treatment, Christine was cancer-free, and the couple married. A year passed and they found they were expecting a child, despite doctors telling Christine she was unlikely to have children. “We are thrilled to have a beautiful baby boy,” Christine said. “He is the center of our world.”\r\n\r\nRight after Logan was born, the family experienced yet another crisis. While Christine was on maternity leave, Richard lost his job. Within a few months, it became clear that they could not afford to make ends meet, and they became homeless. Thankfully, they were referred to InnVision Shelter Network and entered the transitional housing program for homeless families in Menlo Park.\r\n\r\n“The staff made us feel welcome. It was a safe place where we could get through this crisis and focus on our future. Our Case Manager did an excellent job enrolling us in their life skills training classes and connecting us to other resources that we needed,\" Christine said. “And Logan blossomed in the on-site preschool.”\r\n\r\nChristine’s family has successfully graduated from InnVision Shelter Network. Within four months of starting the “Beyond the Bed” program, Christine and Richard both found employment and moved into an apartment they can afford. Their Case Manager, Teresa, says, “They were a great team, and worked hard to motivate each other. They are good parents, and they responded positively to our Beyond the Bed programming. Once we helped identify their unique strengths and build upon them, they were unstoppable!”\r\n\r\nInnVision Shelter Network is proud of Christine and Richard’s success. They have found permanent housing, regained self-sufficiency, and are progressing as a young family, with plans to give back to their community.\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"https://14345.thankyou4caring.org/sslpage.aspx?pid=392\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-452\" alt=\"donate_button\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/donate_button.png\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"https://14345.thankyou4caring.org/sslpage.aspx?pid=392\" target=\"_blank\">Donate Now</a> to support homeless families like Christine and Richard\'s at InnVision Shelter Network.\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>','Christine\'s Family Works Hard for Health and Housing','','publish','closed','open','','christines-family-works-hard-for-health-and-housing','','','2013-11-19 08:59:48','2013-11-19 16:59:48','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/?p=565',28,'post','',0),(566,12,'2013-11-19 08:54:14','2013-11-19 16:54:14','','christine family_blog','','inherit','closed','open','','christine-family_blog','','','2013-11-19 08:54:14','2013-11-19 16:54:14','',565,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/christine-family_blog.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(567,12,'2013-11-19 08:55:57','2013-11-19 16:55:57','','christine family_blog thumbnail','','inherit','closed','open','','christine-family_blog-thumbnail','','','2013-11-19 08:55:57','2013-11-19 16:55:57','',565,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/christine-family_blog-thumbnail.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(572,12,'2013-11-21 17:10:55','2013-11-22 01:10:55',' ','','','publish','closed','open','','572','','','2014-08-26 14:46:36','2014-08-26 21:46:36','',43,'http://www.ivsn.org/?p=572',3,'nav_menu_item','',0),(576,12,'2013-11-22 14:18:45','2013-11-22 22:18:45','<h1 align=\"left\"><b><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-577\" alt=\"elisa photo\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/elisa-photo.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"300\" /></b></h1>\r\nNo one would guess that this bright, bubbly four-year-old was experiencing homelessness. A few months ago, Elisa moved with her mother and older sister to InnVision Shelter Network’s (IVSN) transitional shelter for families. They left their home to escape from a domestic violence situation, but had no place to turn to.\r\n\r\nAt first, Elisa was closed off and easily upset. She began attending IVSN’s on-site Therapeutic Child Development Center, where she worked with trained teachers who showed her how to express herself in a healthy way. Over time, Elisa became one of the most enthusiastic children at IVSN. She thoughtfully supported other children in the class, and always made sure to clean up after arts &amp; crafts activities. As a result, Elisa received the “Helper of the Week” award!\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-579\" alt=\"elisa with family\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/elisa-with-family.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\nElisa loves to spend time with her family. She looks up to her 11-year-old sister, Sarah, who is a GATE student and excels in school. Their devoted mother, Sugei, works hard as a waitress, and she is saving money while receiving services at InnVision Shelter Network. The family meets regularly with mental health counselors at IVSN to work through their traumatic past and make progress toward a self-sufficient future.\r\n\r\nElisa is fortunate to have the support of her family and the IVSN community. She hears that Santa will be coming to the shelter this holiday, and she knows just what to ask for: a new home for her family.','Meet 4-Year-Old Elisa, Helper of the Week!','','publish','closed','open','','meet-4-year-old-elisa-helper-of-the-week','','','2013-11-22 14:22:49','2013-11-22 22:22:49','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/?p=576',27,'post','',0),(577,12,'2013-11-22 14:18:02','2013-11-22 22:18:02','','elisa photo','','inherit','closed','open','','elisa-photo','','','2013-11-22 14:18:02','2013-11-22 22:18:02','',576,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/elisa-photo.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(578,12,'2013-11-22 14:18:07','2013-11-22 22:18:07','','elisa photo_sq','','inherit','closed','open','','elisa-photo_sq','','','2013-11-22 14:18:07','2013-11-22 22:18:07','',576,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/elisa-photo_sq.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(579,12,'2013-11-22 14:22:20','2013-11-22 22:22:20','','elisa with family','','inherit','closed','open','','elisa-with-family','','','2013-11-22 14:22:20','2013-11-22 22:22:20','',576,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/elisa-with-family.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(587,12,'2013-12-04 13:23:03','2013-12-04 21:23:03','','Sobrato Family Foundation Logo','','i