:56','2013-12-23 19:19:56','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/sponsor-a-table-button.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(617,12,'2013-12-23 15:03:11','2013-12-23 23:03:11','The staff at InnVision Shelter Network recently received a letter from Steve, a graduate of our transitional housing program. Steve became homeless due to health problems that put him in a wheelchair, forcing him to lose his job.\r\n\r\nWith IVSN\'s help, Steve has regained employment, moved into permanent housing, and accessed medical care so that he can walk again—giving a whole new meaning to helping someone \"get back on their feet.\"\r\n\r\nSteve, thank you for your heartfelt gratitude and for your persistent motivation to succeed.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-618\" alt=\"client letter\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/client-letter.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"686\" />','Heartwarming Letter from Steve, an IVSN Graduate','','publish','closed','open','','heartwarming-letter-from-steve-an-ivsn-graduate','','','2013-12-23 15:05:24','2013-12-23 23:05:24','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/?p=617',26,'post','',0),(618,12,'2013-12-23 15:02:31','2013-12-23 23:02:31','','client letter','','inherit','closed','open','','client-letter','','','2013-12-23 15:02:31','2013-12-23 23:02:31','',617,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/client-letter.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(619,12,'2013-12-23 15:05:18','2013-12-23 23:05:18','','client letter_thumbnail','','inherit','closed','open','','client-letter_thumbnail','','','2013-12-23 15:05:18','2013-12-23 23:05:18','',617,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/client-letter_thumbnail.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(622,12,'2013-12-26 10:43:00','2013-12-26 18:43:00','','rsvp button','','inherit','closed','open','','rsvp-button','','','2013-12-26 10:43:00','2013-12-26 18:43:00','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/rsvp-button.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(627,12,'2014-01-06 12:14:00','2014-01-06 20:14:00','','villa event web image','','inherit','closed','open','','villa-event-web-image','','','2014-01-06 12:14:00','2014-01-06 20:14:00','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/villa-event-web-image.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(628,12,'2014-01-06 12:58:04','2014-01-06 20:58:04','','rsvp button','','inherit','closed','open','','rsvp-button-2','','','2014-01-06 12:58:04','2014-01-06 20:58:04','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/rsvp-button.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(632,12,'2014-01-10 16:04:53','2014-01-11 00:04:53','<h1>Internships</h1>\r\n<h2>Apply for a 10-week summer internship at IVSN!</h2>\r\n<h1><img class=\" wp-image-1149 size-large aligncenter\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/Interns2014-1024x594.jpg\" alt=\"Interns2014\" width=\"550\" height=\"319\" /></h1>\r\nInnVision Shelter Network is a nonprofit serving homeless families and individuals in the San Francisco Bay Area. As a summer intern, you will:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Make a real difference</strong> in our work to end homelessness through hands-on, educational, and impactful internship projects.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Join a cohort</strong> of highly-motivated students taking on a variety of challenges, from managing a summer camp for homeless children, to grant writing and fundraising, to developing strategic plans for future services, and many more.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Find a mentor</strong> in your internship supervisor, and gain immediate access to executives and vice presidents in the nonprofit sector.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Participate in special intern social events</strong> throughout the Bay Area, including historic site visits, a Giants game, tours of Google and other Silicon Valley companies, and more!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Program Dates</strong>: June 13 – August 19, 2016\r\n\r\n<strong>Application Due</strong>:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Round 1: Friday, November 6, 2015</li>\r\n	<li>Round 2: Friday, February 12, 2016</li>\r\n	<li>Round 3: Friday, April 1, 2016</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Available Positions:</strong>\r\n\r\nWe have four main kinds of positions:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Summer Camp Directors</strong>, working in San Mateo, Menlo Park, Palo Alto, or San Jose at one of our <a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/services/family-services/summer-camp/\" target=\"_blank\">Children\'s Summer Adventure Camps</a></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Strategic Projects Internships</strong>, working at Headquarters in Menlo Park in one of a wide variety of positions. While some of the following positions may not be available, previous examples include:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Marketing Intern</li>\r\n	<li>Technology Innovation Intern</li>\r\n	<li>Research Intern</li>\r\n	<li>Leadership Giving Intern</li>\r\n	<li>Corporate Partnerships Intern</li>\r\n	<li>CEO Intern</li>\r\n	<li>Safety Coordinator Intern</li>\r\n	<li>Operations Intern</li>\r\n	<li>Volunteer Programs Intern</li>\r\n	<li>Housing Policy Intern</li>\r\n	<li>Grants Intern</li>\r\n	<li>Community Engagement Intern</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Direct Client Service Internships</strong>, working directly with clients at a shelter site or in the field. While some of the following positions may not be available, previous examples include:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Homeless Outreach Intern</li>\r\n	<li>Health Care for the Homeless Intern</li>\r\n	<li>Client Experience Intern</li>\r\n	<li>Children Services Intern</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Create Your Own Internship! </strong>Some of our most successful interns have come to us with an idea or project in mind. Pitch it to us and if we like it, we will find you a mentor/supervisor to help you see your project through to completion!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Click below to apply today!</strong></p>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/SummerInternProgram2016/index.html\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/apply-internship-button.png\" alt=\"apply internship button\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a>\r\n\r\nFor questions please contact Adam Klein, Senior Manager of Strategic Initiatives, at <a href=\"mailto:aklein@ivsn.org\">aklein@ivsn.org</a>.\r\n<div align=\"center\"></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Internships','','publish','closed','open','','internships','','','2015-10-28 15:53:06','2015-10-28 22:53:06','',251,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=632',55,'page','',0),(633,12,'2014-01-10 16:03:03','2014-01-11 00:03:03','','intern','','inherit','closed','open','','intern','','','2014-01-10 16:03:03','2014-01-11 00:03:03','',632,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/intern.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(635,12,'2014-01-13 17:40:14','2014-01-14 01:40:14','<h1>Support Committees</h1>\r\nVolunteer members of IVSN\'s Support Committees go above and beyond to help end homelessness.\r\n<h2>What are Support Committees?</h2>\r\nA Support Committee is a group of volunteers that provide ongoing support to one program/site at InnVision Shelter Network, with special emphasis on helping create a warm and caring environment for the residents. Support Committees serve as liaisons with the community at large, with membership and community involvement drawn from a wide spectrum of the greater community.\r\n<h2>Why are Support Committees important?</h2>\r\nSupport Committees are critical to making IVSN’s shelter and services go “beyond the bed.” Support Committees empower clients with self-confidence, hope, and supportive community. They promote positive interactions between staff, clients, and volunteers. Support Committees provide the platform upon which clients lift themselves up to overcome homelessness and regain self-sufficiency.\r\n<h2>How Support Committees can support a shelter</h2>\r\nThere are countless ways that Support Committees can help IVSN clients and staff, such as:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Advocate for IVSN in the community</li>\r\n	<li>Promote holiday gift drives and dinner baskets</li>\r\n	<li>Connect with meal providers</li>\r\n	<li>Assist with special site projects</li>\r\n	<li>Manage donation needs</li>\r\n	<li>Fulfill clients’ special needs</li>\r\n	<li>Foster a sense of community at the shelter</li>\r\n	<li>Support staff in times of need</li>\r\n	<li>Find resources for facilities projects</li>\r\n	<li>Organize donation drives</li>\r\n	<li>Promote enthusiasm and positivity for clients</li>\r\n	<li>Recruit volunteers from the community</li>\r\n	<li>Help express IVSN’s gratitude to volunteers and donors</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a href=\"http://volunteer.ivsn.org/SNApp.aspx\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-370\" alt=\"sign_up_to_volunteer\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/sign_up_to_volunteer.png\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a>','Support Committees','','publish','closed','open','','support-committees','','','2014-01-13 17:40:14','2014-01-14 01:40:14','',184,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=635',56,'page','',0),(645,12,'2014-01-24 14:52:38','2014-01-24 22:52:38','','jim_greer_web','','inherit','closed','open','','jim_greer_web','','','2014-01-24 14:52:38','2014-01-24 22:52:38','',240,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/jim_greer_web.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(646,12,'2014-01-27 17:33:27','2014-01-28 01:33:27',' ','','','publish','closed','open','','646','','','2014-07-08 15:19:40','2014-07-08 22:19:40','',251,'http://www.ivsn.org/?p=646',7,'nav_menu_item','',0),(649,12,'2014-01-27 17:40:54','2014-01-28 01:40:54','','Lorena Collins','','inherit','closed','open','','lorena-collins','','','2014-01-27 17:40:54','2014-01-28 01:40:54','',240,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/Lorena-Collins.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(650,12,'2014-01-28 10:13:12','2014-01-28 18:13:12','','LorenaCollins2','','inherit','closed','open','','lorenacollins2','','','2014-01-28 10:13:12','2014-01-28 18:13:12','',240,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/LorenaCollins2.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(651,12,'2014-01-28 10:31:13','2014-01-28 18:31:13','','MilaZelkha','','inherit','closed','open','','milazelkha','','','2014-01-28 10:31:13','2014-01-28 18:31:13','',240,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/MilaZelkha.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(652,12,'2014-01-28 10:33:25','2014-01-28 18:33:25','','PhilipDah','','inherit','closed','open','','philipdah','','','2014-01-28 10:33:25','2014-01-28 18:33:25','',240,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/PhilipDah.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(654,12,'2014-01-29 13:18:44','2014-01-29 21:18:44','','JacobLile_website','','inherit','closed','open','','jacoblile_website','','','2014-01-29 13:18:44','2014-01-29 21:18:44','',240,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/JacobLile_website.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(658,12,'2014-01-30 14:43:24','2014-01-30 22:43:24','','Cupertino Electric','','inherit','closed','open','','cupertino-electric','','','2014-01-30 14:43:24','2014-01-30 22:43:24','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Cupertino-Electric.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(659,12,'2014-01-30 14:44:56','2014-01-30 22:44:56','','Rock Bottom Brewery Logo','','inherit','closed','open','','rock-bottom-brewery-logo','','','2014-01-30 14:44:56','2014-01-30 22:44:56','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Rock-Bottom-Brewery-Logo.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(660,12,'2014-01-30 14:45:41','2014-01-30 22:45:41','','NXP_logo','','inherit','closed','open','','nxp_logo','','','2014-01-30 14:45:41','2014-01-30 22:45:41','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/NXP_logo.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(661,12,'2014-01-30 14:46:26','2014-01-30 22:46:26','','Cisco','','inherit','closed','open','','cisco','','','2014-01-30 14:46:26','2014-01-30 22:46:26','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Cisco.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(662,12,'2014-01-30 14:47:37','2014-01-30 22:47:37','','Talari-Network-Logo','','inherit','closed','open','','talari-network-logo','','','2014-01-30 14:47:37','2014-01-30 22:47:37','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Talari-Network-Logo.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(663,12,'2014-01-30 14:53:20','2014-01-30 22:53:20','','Cisco','','inherit','closed','open','','cisco-2','','','2014-01-30 14:53:20','2014-01-30 22:53:20','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Cisco1.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(665,12,'2014-02-03 15:16:02','2014-02-03 23:16:02','<img class=\"alignright wp-image-1584 size-medium\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/IMG_6231-edit-320x236.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"320\" height=\"236\" />\r\n<h1>NextGen Advisory Board</h1>\r\n<h2>IVSN\'s NextGen Advisory Board brings together young professional leaders who are socially conscious and striving to make an impact.</h2>\r\nThe NextGen Advisory Board, founded in January 2014, uses the skills of its diverse membership to develop and execute functional projects based on the needs of IVSN, driving both strategic and tactical innovation for the agency.\r\n\r\nThe NextGen Board strives to increase awareness and educate the young professional population of Silicon Valley about the severity of homelessness in our community and about the successful methods IVSN has employed to tackle homelessness and poverty.\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h2>Members</h2>\r\nThe NextGen Advisory Board membership is made up of strong professional and academic backgrounds;  the composition of the board includes a variety of professionals from large tech companies, emerging growth companies, venture capital firms, law firms, and social sector organizations. Additionally, diversity in gender, country of origin, and professional titles make up this board composition.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#MichaelHeadley\"><b>Michael Headley</b></a>, Digital Realty, Board Co-Chair\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#SarahBoisseree\"><b>Sarah Boisseree</b></a>, Financial Analyst at NetApp, Board Co-Chair\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#AdamKlein\"><b>Adam Klein</b></a>, Senior Manager of Strategic Initiatives at InnVision Shelter Network, Staff Liaison\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#RohanBafna\"><b>Rohan Bafna</b></a>, Microsoft XBox\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#FaustoBustos\"><b>Fausto Bustos</b></a>, PhD Student at UC Berkeley School of Public Health Student\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#KalaChapman\"><b>Kala Chapman</b></a>, Google\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#LisaAnneChung\"><b>Lisa-Anne Chung</b></a>, Senior Product Manager at Upwork\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#JuliaDuncan\"><b>Julia Duncan</b></a>, Foreign Affairs Officer at U.S. Department of State\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#CasandraEspinoza\"><b>Casandra Espinoza</b></a>, Founder of Share Ave\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#MarshallFisher\"><b>Marshall Fisher</b></a>, Associate Investment Director at Cambridge Associates\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#AllenHe\"><b>Allen He</b></a>, Senior Corporate Strategy Analyst at NetApp\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#WillLindemann\"><b>Will Lindemann</b></a>, Director of Growth at Branch Metrics\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#PromeetMansata\"><b>Promeet Mansata</b></a>, Product Manager at @WalmartLabs\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#StefanMoser\"><b>Stefan Moser</b></a>, Scientist at Amyris Inc.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#MattPesko\"><b>Matt Pesko</b></a>, Resident in Psychiatry at Stanford Hospital and the Veteran\'s Administration Hospital\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#SeanTaube\"><b>Sean Taube</b></a>, Attorney at Wilson Sonsini Goodrich &amp; Rosati\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#ElizabethWoodson\"><b>Elizabeth Woodson</b></a>, Stanford University Student\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h2>Get Involved</h2>\r\n<a href=\"https://docs.google.com/forms/d/13cRFl6RxlnTrz7SYmFIN8t-_CU4Wqz3UWpIobxxpGBw/viewform\" target=\"_blank\">Fill out this short form</a> to connect with NextGen! One of our members will contact you shortly.\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h2>Press</h2>\r\n<strong>July 29, 2014 </strong>- San Mateo County Times - <a href=\"http://www.mercurynews.com/san-mateo-county-times/ci_26237326/margaret-lavin-innvision-shelter-network-and-linkedin-partner\">InnVision Shelter Network and LinkedIn Partner to Assist Bay Area Homeless in Search for Employment</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>July 18, 2014 </strong>- Mountain View Voice - <a href=\"http://www.mv-voice.com/news/2014/07/18/linkedin-to-hold-job-preparation-clinic-for-homeless\">LinkedIn to hold job preparation clinic for homeless</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>March 17, 2014 </strong>- San Mateo Daily Journal - <a href=\"http://www.smdailyjournal.com/articles/lnews/2014-03-17/next-generation-targeting-homelessness-nonprofit-forms-youth-advisory-board-of-young-and-educated-high-tech-professionals/1776425119831.html\" target=\"_blank\">Next generation targeting homelessness: Nonprofit forms youth advisory board of young and educated high-tech professionals</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>March 17, 2014</strong> - The Almanac - <a href=\"http://www.almanacnews.com/news/2014/03/17/innvision-creates-new-advisory-board\" target=\"_blank\">Menlo Park\'s InnVision creates NextGen Advisory Board</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>March 6, 2014</strong> - Silicon Valley Business Insider - <a href=\"http://www.bizjournals.com/sanjose/news/2014/03/06/young-googlers-venture-capitalists.html?page=all\" target=\"_blank\">Young Googlers, VCs, an Oakland Raider team up to tackle Silicon Valley homelessness</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>March 3, 2014</strong> - Yahoo Finance - <a href=\"http://finance.yahoo.com/news/innvision-shelter-network-creates-young-153000045.html\" target=\"_blank\">InnVision Shelter Network Creates Young Community Leaders Board to Tackle Local Homelessness</a>\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h2>NextGen Board Bios</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-706\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/headley.png\" alt=\"headley\" width=\"103\" height=\"141\" /><b id=\"MichaelHeadley\">Michael Headley</b>, Digital Realty\r\n\r\nMichael Headley serves as the Co-Chair of the IVSN NextGen Advisory Board, focusing on supply chain optimization, cost reduction, and technology integration. Headley currently works at Digital Realty mapping business processes and identifying opportunities for automation and efficiency through enhanced technology. His passion for serving the community comes from a core belief that all people deserve the opportunity to lead a rewarding and fulfilling life, especially those in in need. Headley holds a BS in Electrical Engineering from the University of Virginia.\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1373\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Sarah-Boisseree-320x435.jpg\" alt=\"OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA\" width=\"103\" height=\"140\" /><b id=\"SarahBoisseree\">Sarah Boisseree</b>,<b id=\"SarahBoisseree\"> </b>NetApp\r\n\r\nSarah Boisseree serves as the Co-Chair of the NextGen Board and works as a Financial Analyst at NetApp, a data storage and management company. She graduated from Stanford University in 2013 with a B.S. in Management Science and Engineering. At Stanford, Sarah was a Resident Assistant and a member of the executive council for her sorority. Previously, Sarah held summer internships at the public accounting firm PwC and with the Stanford Graduate School of Business Executive Education program. She first became involved with IVSN in high school as a volunteer at IVSN\'s First Step for Families in her hometown of San Mateo, CA. Sarah is also a finance advisor and a marketing advisor to collegiate chapters of her sorority. In her free time, Sarah enjoys reading, photography, traveling, and watching professional cycling.\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1591\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/AdamKlein-1280x800.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"103\" height=\"131\" /><b id=\"AdamKlein\">Adam Klein</b>,<b id=\"AdamKlein\"> </b>InnVision Shelter Network\r\n\r\nAdam Klein serves as the Staff Liaison and is a founding member of the NextGen Advisory Board, and works at IVSN as the Programs and Services Initiatives Manager. Klein graduated Phi Beta Kappa and with Distinction from Stanford University in 2013 with a degree in International Relations, where he was a Tour Guide Student Manager, an Admissions Associate, and a Resident Assistant. Previously, Klein was the Event Chair of the American Cancer Society\'s Relay for Life in his hometown of Burlingame, CA, served as the Student Member of the San Mateo Union High School District Board of Trustees, and worked as a Regional Director for Students for Barack Obama.\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-842 size-full\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Rohan_Bafna.png\" alt=\"RohanBafna\" width=\"103\" height=\"138\" /><b id=\"RohanBafna\"></b>\r\n\r\n<b id=\"RohanBafna\">Rohan Bafna</b>,<b id=\"RohanBafna\"> </b>Microsoft XBox\r\n\r\nRohan Bafna currently works at Microsoft XBox as an Engineering Manager. He is also currently pursuing his MBA from the Haas School of Business at UC Berkeley. He holds a Masters in Computer Engineering from New Jersey Institute of Technology. He has been an active volunteer for Vibha since 2006 playing various roles including most notably the co-ordinator of the Atlanta Chapter and the race director for Atlanta and Bay Area DreamMile events separately. He enjoys travelling, reading, ice-skating, and amateur photography.\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1593\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Picture1-21.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"103\" height=\"136\" /><b id=\"FaustoBustos\">Fausto Bustos</b>, UC Berkeley School of Public Health Student\r\n\r\nFausto Bustos is a second-year PhD student in Infectious Disease Epidemiology at the UC Berkeley School of Public Health. He is concurrently pursuing a Master\'s degree in Biostatistics. His doctoral work will focus on the transmission of dengue and other viral tropical diseases in Nicaragua. He graduated from Stanford University with degrees in Human Biology and Political Science, conducting research in molecular biology and political communications. He also received a Masters of Epidemiology from the Harvard School of Public Health, studing the transmission of influenza from poultry to humans while there. He has previously worked at the US State Department, and is currently a Guest Researcher at the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention. He is also a co-founder and senior consultant at College Aces, LLC, a college admissions consulting firm.\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-704\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/cardona.png\" alt=\"cardona\" width=\"103\" height=\"141\" /><b id=\"AngelinaCardona\">Angelina Cardona</b>,<b id=\"AngelinaCardona\"> </b>Yale School of Management Student\r\n\r\nAngelina Cardona is currently a first-year MBA student at the Yale School of Management. She formerly worked as a Technical Recruiter for Google and for the Office of Alcohol Policy &amp; Education at Stanford University as an Assistant Director and Community Engagement Manager where she founded and implemented “Cardinal Nights” – an initiative to change campus alcohol culture. Originally from Sparks, Nevada, Cardona earned her B.A. in International Relations from Stanford University in 2011. During her senior year, she was elected the Student Body President.\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<b id=\"KalaChapman\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1383\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/10295458_10103190012326533_8529739021541976129_o1-320x421.jpg\" alt=\"10295458_10103190012326533_8529739021541976129_o\" width=\"103\" height=\"136\" />Kala Chapman</b>, Google\r\n\r\nKala Chapman currently works as a Product Marketing Manager at Google, focusing on their Play Store efforts, where she has been since 2011. Before Google, she worked as an Associate for Entrepreneurial Services at Keiretsu Forum, a small private equity group operating out of the Bay Area. She first discovered a passion for the intersection of technology and social entrepreneurship as a Summer Associate for Samasource, a non-profit technology startup providing tech-based jobs to impoverished women and youth throughout India and Sub-Saharan Africa. She hails from Loomis, California and holds a B.A. from UC Berkeley in International Relations &amp; Global Poverty. When she’s not working, Kala enjoys trail running, baking and reading in the various parks San Francisco has to offer.\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<b id=\"LisaAnneChung\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1585\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/D4F2683-684x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"103\" height=\"154\" />Lisa-Anne Chung</b>, Upwork\r\n\r\nLisa-Anne is currently a Sr. Product Manager at Upwork and recently finished her MBA at UC Berkeley - Haas. At Upwork, a freelancer market place, she owns the Collaboration platform which recently successfully built and launched a new communication system. Prior to Upwork, she spent seven years at Intuit in various roles across Finance, Operations, Mobile Product Management, Customer Service Design, and Product Management. She is passionate about creating awesome customer experiences, improving existing processes, and finding more efficient and effective solutions to create delight for all stakeholders. Her undergraduate degree was in Management Science from the University of California, San Diego.\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1592\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/juliaduncan.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"103\" height=\"154\" /><b id=\"JuliaDuncan\">Julia Duncan</b>, U.S. Department of State\r\n\r\nJulia Duncan is a founding member and former chair of the IVSN NextGen Advisory Board. Duncan currently works on issues related to global food security at the State Department. Previously, she has worked at Google in the Finance Department, in the White House in the Office of Presidential Personnel, and on Capitol Hill as an aide. Additionally, she served on the 2008 Presidential Inaugural Committee and helped execute the MLK National Day of Service. Duncan holds her BA in Government and History from the University of Virginia and her MA in Public Management from Johns Hopkins University.\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-705\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/espinoza.png\" alt=\"espinoza\" width=\"103\" height=\"141\" /><b id=\"CasandraEspinoza\">Casandra Espinoza</b>, Share Ave\r\n\r\nCasandra Espinoza is a founding member of the IVSN NextGen Advisory Board. She recently started Share Ave, a way for parents to hire early childhood specialists, not babysitters. She previously worked at Greylock Partners, a venture firm that focuses on consumer and enterprise investments. Casandra also participated in the Kauffman Fellows Program as a member of Class 16. Upon completion of the Kauffman program, she was the recipient of a peer selected award for class leadership. She holds a BA in Public Policy from Stanford University.\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1589\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Marshall-Fisher1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"103\" height=\"140\" /><b id=\"MarshallFisher\">Marshall Fisher</b>, Cambridge Associates\r\n\r\nMarshall Fisher is an Associate Investment Director in Cambridge Associates’ Menlo Park office, where he works with non-profit endowments to help them invest so they can fulfill their missions. He also volunteers as a tutor at Eastside College Preparatory School, an organization committed to opening new doors for students underrepresented in higher education. He is a 2011 graduate from Claremont McKenna College, where he majored in Economics, Environmental Science, and Political Science, and was a four-year member and two-year captain of the Men’s Varsity Soccer Team. Marshall is originally from Des Moines, Iowa, and in his free time enjoys the outdoors, bocce, piano, and film.\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1588\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/29456661.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"103\" height=\"139\" /><b id=\"AllenHe\">Allen He</b>, NetApp\r\n\r\nComing from Houston, Texas, Allen received a degree in Business Administration from UC Berkeley. IVSN is the first non-profit organization he is involved in on a professional level. He enjoys playing basketball, supporting the Houston Rockets, and snowboarding. He currently works in corporate strategy at NetApp, a data management and storage company in the bay area.\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<b id=\"WillLindemann\"><b id=\"WillLindemann\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1379\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Lindemann-Headshot.png\" alt=\"Lindemann Headshot\" width=\"103\" height=\"112\" /></b></b>\r\n\r\n<b id=\"WillLindemann\"><b id=\"WillLindemann\">Will Lindemann</b></b>, Branch Metrics\r\n\r\nWill enjoys working at a local level with IVSN’s NextGen board, in addition to work he does with Children International, a global nonprofit. He\'s an ex-Googler who worked on the Chromecast team before leaving Google to join Branch Metrics, as Director of Growth. He holds a B.A. in Human Biology and a minor in English from Stanford University. In his spare time Will goes to Stanford games, hunts for interesting coffee shops and enjoys local and international adventures.\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<b id=\"PromeetMansata\">Promeet Mansata</b>, @WalmartLabs<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1376\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Promeet-320x416.jpg\" alt=\"Promeet\" width=\"103\" height=\"134\" />\r\n\r\nPromeet Mansata currently works at @WalmartLabs as a Product Manager. He holds an MBA from the Haas School of Business at UC Berkeley and a Bachelor of Commerce and Master of Commerce from Bangalore University, India. He was one of the 15 winners of the LinkedIn Transformation Grant in 2014 and served as a coach for the 2105 grants cycle at LinkedIn. Promeet has also been a volunteer at Second Harvest Food bank since 2008. He is an avid runner and loves reading.\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1590\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/headshot_kind_of2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"103\" height=\"153\" /><b id=\"StefanMoser\">Stefan Moser</b>, Amyris Inc.\r\n\r\nStefan grew up in Switzerland and moved to San Mateo when he was 10, spending most of his youth on the Peninsula. He graduated from UCSD in 2011 and promptly moved back to the bay area to pursue opportunities in the biotech industry. Since his move back, he has moved around from San Mateo to San Francisco until finally settling in North Berkeley, where he works at Amyris Biotech, which specializes in producing alternatives to petroleum based products via a synthetic biology technology platform. Stefan is passionate about supporting IVSN and its mission to aid and support the homeless in the bay area.\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<b id=\"MattPesko\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1377\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Matt-Pesko-320x401.jpg\" alt=\"Matt Pesko\" width=\"103\" height=\"129\" />Matt Pesko</b>,<b id=\"MattPesko\"> </b>Stanford Hospital and the Veteran\'s Administration Hospital\r\n\r\nMatt Pesko is currently a resident physician in the Stanford Department of Psychiatry working at Stanford Hospital and the Veteran\'s Administration Hospital. He completed medical school at Harvard University and a received a B.S. from the University of Wisconsin-Madison. His interest in combating homelessness started during a year of volunteer service through the Jesuit Volunteer Corps in which he worked with homeless individuals with mental illness and substance dependence in Portland, Maine. Pesko is originally from northern Wisconsin. In his free time, he enjoys reading and following professional baseball. He and his wife are also regular volunteers at the St. Anthony\'s Padua Dining Room in Redwood City.\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-710\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/taube.png\" alt=\"taube\" width=\"103\" height=\"141\" /><b id=\"SeanTaube\">Sean Taube</b>,<b id=\"SeanTaube\"> </b>Wilson Sonsini Goodrich &amp; Rosati\r\n\r\nSean Taube is a founding member of the IVSN NextGen Advisory Board. Sean Taube is an attorney at Wilson Sonsini Goodrich &amp; Rosati. Prior to law school, Sean worked as an investment associate for several real estate investment firms. Sean also serves on the Taube Foundation for Jewish Life and Culture Advisory Board. Sean holds a BA from the University of California, Santa Barbara and a JD from University of San Francisco School of Law. Sean is a native of the Peninsula.\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-712\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/woodson.png\" alt=\"woodson\" width=\"103\" height=\"141\" /><b id=\"ElizabethWoodson\">Elizabeth Woodson</b>,<b id=\"ElizabethWoodson\"> </b>Stanford University Student\r\n\r\nElizabeth Woodson is currently serving as Student Body President of Stanford University, where she is studying Science, Technology and Society. She is a Mayfield Fellow, and is pursuing research on women and leadership in the non-profit sector. In addition to being Social Impact Manager for the student government, Woodson serves on the Board of Trustees\' Committee on Development and writes an opinions column for the Stanford Daily. Joining the IVSN NextGen Advisory Board is an exciting opportunity for Woodson, who spent three years facilitating weekly Theatre of the Oppressed sessions with women at New Haven\'s largest homeless shelter.','NextGen','','publish','closed','open','','nextgen','','','2015-11-03 14:56:02','2015-11-03 22:56:02','',6,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=665',54,'page','',0),(666,12,'2014-02-03 15:12:41','2014-02-03 23:12:41','','nextgen_web','','inherit','closed','open','','nextgen_web','','','2014-02-03 15:12:41','2014-02-03 23:12:41','',665,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/nextgen_web.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(667,12,'2014-02-03 15:17:30','2014-02-03 23:17:30','','NextGen Board','','publish','closed','open','','nextgen-board','','','2014-07-08 15:19:40','2014-07-08 22:19:40','',6,'http://www.ivsn.org/?p=667',4,'nav_menu_item','',0),(668,12,'2014-02-06 10:25:13','2014-02-06 18:25:13','<h1>CEO Intern<a href=\"http://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/interns/index.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignright\" alt=\"apply internship button\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/apply-internship-button.png\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a></h1>\r\n<strong>Location</strong>: IVSN Administrative Office, 181 Constitution Drive, Menlo Park, CA 94025\r\n\r\n<strong>Time Commitment: </strong>10 weeks: June 16th – August 15th, Full or Part Time\r\n<h2>Description</h2>\r\nInnVision Shelter Network (IVSN), the largest homeless service provider in Northern California, has a Ph.D. psychologist that leads our Direct Client Services, so our CEO, a Harvard MBA, runs the business side of the organization and is managing the second year in integrating two merged non-profit organizations. The CEO Intern at IVSN will be able to shadow the CEO in meetings, help with action items, and learn how to balance strategy and tactics at the executive level. The Intern can participate in a variety of executive projects that will give him/her hands-on experience for leading a nonprofit.\r\n<h2>Responsibilities</h2>\r\nComplete special projects for the CEO as assigned, which may include:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Collaborating with the VP of Strategy and Technology on internal change management for information workflow</li>\r\n	<li>Collaborating with outside leadership consultants on improving organizational culture</li>\r\n	<li>Collaborating with the VP of Programs to grow client service offerings</li>\r\n	<li>Balancing the budget in a revenue growth year</li>\r\n	<li>Increasing public relations exposure</li>\r\n	<li>Leveraging social media and the NextGen Board to expand donor base</li>\r\n	<li>Engaging in government relations to match the scope and size of the organization</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2> Position Requirements/Preferred Skills</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>HS Diploma and some college</li>\r\n	<li>Demonstrated interest in leadership of a non-profit organization</li>\r\n	<li>Flexibility and the ability to thrive in an environment of rapid change and growth</li>\r\n	<li>Very strong communication skills</li>\r\n	<li>Experience in leadership positions, preferably related to serving homeless or underprivileged groups</li>\r\n	<li>Diligent work ethic, positive attitude, and desire to learn about InnVision Shelter Network and the work of a Chief Executive</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\r\nThis opportunity is rare, as one of our CEO’s top initiatives is bringing young talent into the organization, giving them ambitious projects, independence in decision making, and impactful deliverables. Consequently, the results/deliverables for this internship are flexible as to the student’s strengths, desires and abilities.\r\n\r\n<strong>Compensation</strong>: Unpaid\r\n\r\n<strong>Supervisor</strong>: Karae Lisle, Chief Executive Officer\r\n\r\n<strong>Application Deadline</strong>: March 31, 2014\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/interns/index.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-678 alignleft\" alt=\"apply internship button\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/apply-internship-button.png\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a>','CEO Intern','','publish','closed','open','','ceo-intern','','','2014-02-06 10:36:45','2014-02-06 18:36:45','',632,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=668',52,'page','',0),(669,12,'2014-02-04 10:03:47','2014-02-04 18:03:47','<h1>Assistant Children\'s Services Coordinator</h1>\r\n<h2>Qualifications</h2>\r\nBA in Child Development, Child Psychology or related experience. Two years experience working with children and parents, preferably at-risk, low-income. Conflict resolution, group facilitation, and excellent communication skills essential.  Knowledge of child development, parenting issues, curriculum development and area resources important. Bilingual Spanish preferred, teaching experience helpful. Automobile and valid driver’s license preferred.  <b>Spanish Speaking Preferred. </b>\r\n<h2>Responsibilities</h2>\r\nThe Assistant Children’s Services Coordinator is responsible for managing and evaluating a children’s program to provide a safe and supportive educational environment for children within a homeless family program.\r\n<h2>Duties</h2>\r\n1. <b>Intake and Assessment</b>\r\n\r\nConduct interviews, assess individual needs of children to identify special needs and areas of concern; work closely with other staff to develop intervention plan and provide appropriate services or make referrals and link families to other community agencies, schools, or programs as needed. Ensure the delivery of intake, assessment, and referral services in a professional, ethical, and effective manner.\r\n\r\n2. <b>Administration &amp; Management</b>\r\n\r\nPrepare and maintain case files, records, data entry, program statistics, reports and any other necessary documentation as needed. Attend case management meetings, supervision, staff meetings and other meetings as assigned.  Assist in the development of a standardized children’s program policies and procedure manual for family sites. Maintain an inventory of instructional, art, and play materials. Develop monthly calendar of children’s activities.\r\n\r\n3.<b> Community Relations</b>\r\n\r\nDevelop and plan field trips, recreational and summer activities. Develop and maintain positive relationships with service providers, therapists, volunteers, etc. to maximize resources for children and their families. Liaison with local schools to track attendance and progress of students in order to provide any special assistance as needed; facilitate enrollment of children in local schools. Assist in recruiting, training and supervising children’s program volunteers. Assist in educating the community about homelessness and the needs of homeless children. Assist families in obtaining childcare within the community. When needed assist in scheduling workshops, training, etc., for parents and children on relevant topics.\r\n\r\n4. <b>General Duties</b>\r\n\r\nParticipate in All Staff Meetings, program open houses, fundraising events, and other agency-wide functions.  Other duties as assigned.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>','Assistant Children\'s Services Coordinator','','publish','closed','open','','assistant-childrens-services-coordinator-spanish-speaking','','','2014-02-25 12:19:54','2014-02-25 20:19:54','',251,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=669',53,'page','',0),(672,12,'2014-02-05 11:12:37','2014-02-05 19:12:37','<h1><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-674\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/ivsn_summer_camp_counselor.png\" alt=\"ivsn_summer_camp_counselor\" width=\"320\" height=\"231\" />Volunteer as a Camp Counselor</h1>\r\n<h2>Thank you for your interest in volunteering at IVSN’s Summer Camp!</h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/services/family-services/summer-camp/\">Summer Adventure Camp</a> is an on-site camp for children at InnVision Shelter Network’s shelters for homeless families. Campers engage in fun, educational activities on-site and take weekly field trips to national parks, museums, and theatrical performances.\r\n<h2>Time Commitment</h2>\r\n8:30am-3:30pm, Monday through Friday for 3 weeks. Weeks may be non-consecutive.\r\n\r\n<strong>Camp dates are June 22 – August 6, 2015.</strong>\r\n<h2>Qualifications</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Experience working with children in an active group setting is preferred</li>\r\n	<li>Positive attitude and willingness to take direction from the Camp Director and other IVSN staff members</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to work independently</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Responsibilities</h2>\r\nCamp Counselors are responsible for the guidance, safety and well-being of program participants in InnVision Shelter Network\'s Summer Adventure Camp. Responsibilities include:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Assist in organizing and implementing activities, crafts, and games during the program.</li>\r\n	<li>Keep the all children safe and accounted for at all times.</li>\r\n	<li>Maintain general order and consistency during the program.</li>\r\n	<li>Work effectively with other counselors, volunteers, and children.</li>\r\n	<li>Help ensure the safety of children while on field trips.</li>\r\n	<li>Report to Summer Camp Director regarding all issues and problems.</li>\r\n	<li>Ensure parents sign their children in and out in a timely manner.</li>\r\n	<li>Enforce appropriate program discipline and rules.</li>\r\n	<li>Assist in preparing lunchtime meal and afternoon snack for participating children.</li>\r\n	<li>Establish friendly relationships with parents as they drop off/pick up their children.</li>\r\n	<li>Communicate effectively with Summer Camp Director and IVSN regarding any behavioral issues that arise with the participating children.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Locations</h2>\r\nSummer Camps are held at four of IVSN’s family shelters.\r\n\r\n<em>Thank you for your interest, we are no longer taking volunteers at any of our locations.</em>\r\n<h2>Participation Fee</h2>\r\nPlease consider donating a participation fee of $150.00 per volunteer to help IVSN cover the cost of admissions, field trips, and food for your child.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The cost to provide Summer Adventure Camp to all of the children at IVSN\'s seven shelters for homeless families is approximately $500 per camper. Please let us know if you would like to sponsor the cost of a child (or children) attending IVSN’s Summer Adventure Camp. Over 250 children are expected to participate this summer.</p>\r\n\r\n<address>Please send to:</address><address>IVSN Summer Adventure Camp</address><address><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">181 Constitution Drive</span></address><address>Menlo Park, CA 94025</address>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-size: 1.5em; line-height: 1.5em;\">Apply</span></h2>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/form58/index.html\" target=\"_blank\">Click here to complete the Summer Camp Counselor application.</a>','Camp Counselor','','publish','closed','open','','camp-counselor','','','2015-06-30 18:06:56','2015-07-01 01:06:56','',187,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=672',51,'page','',0),(673,12,'2014-02-05 11:14:41','2014-02-05 19:14:41','','ivsn_summer_adventure_camp_web','','inherit','closed','open','','ivsn_summer_adventure_camp_web','','','2014-02-05 11:14:41','2014-02-05 19:14:41','',68,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ivsn_summer_adventure_camp_web.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(674,12,'2014-02-05 11:20:24','2014-02-05 19:20:24','','ivsn_summer_camp_counselor','','inherit','closed','open','','ivsn_summer_camp_counselor','','','2014-02-05 11:20:24','2014-02-05 19:20:24','',672,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/ivsn_summer_camp_counselor.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(678,12,'2014-02-06 10:23:44','2014-02-06 18:23:44','','apply internship button','','inherit','closed','open','','apply-internship-button','','','2014-02-06 10:23:44','2014-02-06 18:23:44','',668,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/apply-internship-button.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(679,12,'2014-02-06 10:35:29','2014-02-06 18:35:29','<h1>Client Experience Intern<a href=\"http://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/interns/index.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-678\" alt=\"apply internship button\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/apply-internship-button.png\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a></h1>\r\n<strong>Location</strong>: Montgomery Street Inn, 358 N. Montgomery Street, San Jose, CA 95110\r\n\r\n<strong>Time Commitment</strong>: 10 weeks: June 16th – August 15th, Part time (minimum 12-15 hours/week), Flexible scheduling\r\n<h2>Description</h2>\r\nMontgomery Street Inn (MSI) provides a shelter with programming designed to assist homeless men with securing sustainable employment and housing. Our objective is to break the cycle of homelessness by providing shelter and comprehensive support programs while treating each participant with dignity and respect. The intern will work with current staff to identify programming and job development needs and design program features based on best practices research.\r\n<h2>Responsibilities</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Improve job development services</li>\r\n	<li>Assist clients through the resume and interview preparation process</li>\r\n	<li>Improve client savings plan program</li>\r\n	<li>Complete special projects and provide organizational support as assigned</li>\r\n	<li>Attend weekly meetings with intern supervisor and monthly meetings with program director</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Position Requirements/Preferred Skills</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>HS Diploma and some college</li>\r\n	<li>Comfort working with the homeless community</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to effectively communicate both in individual and group settings</li>\r\n	<li>Strong boundaries</li>\r\n	<li>Very strong writing and proofreading skills</li>\r\n	<li>Attention to detail</li>\r\n	<li>Diligent work ethic, positive attitude, and desire to learn about homelessness</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Hands-on engagement in case management services and programming for one of the largest and most effective non-profit agencies serving homeless populations in the SF Bay Area</li>\r\n	<li>Insight into barriers to employment that affect the homeless community</li>\r\n	<li>How to communicate effectively in a professional setting</li>\r\n	<li>Networking opportunities for career development with InnVision Shelter Network staff and partner agencies</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Compensation</strong>: Unpaid\r\n\r\n<strong>Supervisor</strong>: Allison Robinson, MSI Program Development Coordinator\r\n\r\n<strong>Application Deadline</strong>: March 31, 2014\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/interns/index.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-678\" alt=\"apply internship button\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/apply-internship-button.png\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a>','Client Experience Intern','','publish','closed','open','','client-experience-intern','','','2014-02-06 13:11:45','2014-02-06 21:11:45','',632,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=679',50,'page','',0),(680,12,'2014-02-06 10:44:30','2014-02-06 18:44:30','<img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-678\" alt=\"apply internship button\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/apply-internship-button.png\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" />\r\n<h1>Community Engagement Intern</h1>\r\n<strong>Two Locations</strong>:\r\nIVSN Administrative Office, 181 Constitution Drive, Menlo Park, CA 94025\r\nFamily Crossroads, 50 Hillcrest Dr, Daly City, CA 94014\r\n\r\n<strong>Time Commitment</strong>: 10 weeks: June 16th – August 15th, Flexible scheduling\r\n<h2>Description</h2>\r\nEngaging with community partners is critical to the success of the mission of InnVision Shelter Network. The Community Engagement interns will build the base of community partners for the development team and the agency as a whole by working on hands-on engagement projects and heading into the field to meet with potential partners.\r\n<h2>Responsibilities</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Reach out to past volunteer groups and donors from both InnVision and Shelter Network in order to reconnect them with post-merger InnVision Shelter Network</li>\r\n	<li>Present IVSN’s mission to various local businesses and community or faith-based groups</li>\r\n	<li>Research and gather information for the donor and volunteer databases (will also include some data entry)</li>\r\n	<li>Complete special projects and provide organizational support as assigned</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Position Requirements/Preferred Skills</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Interest in community relationship building</li>\r\n	<li>Strong written and communication skills</li>\r\n	<li>A team player attitude</li>\r\n	<li>Highly organized</li>\r\n	<li>Proficient in Microsoft Office, specifically, Excel, Word, and Outlook Calendaring</li>\r\n	<li>Analytical and tech savvy</li>\r\n	<li>Flexibility</li>\r\n	<li>Humor and wit</li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">This role will require the use of a private vehicle</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Gain an excellent overview of community relationship building</li>\r\n	<li>Develop a deep understanding of a non-profit  through first-hand interactions and collaboration with members of various departments</li>\r\n	<li>Grow strong cross departmental communication skills</li>\r\n	<li>Build your understanding of the issue of homelessness and the need for community engagement</li>\r\n	<li>Networking opportunities for career development with InnVision Shelter Network staff and partner agencies</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Compensation:</b> Unpaid, but associated costs (driving) will be reimbursed\r\n\r\n<b>Supervisor:\r\n</b>Menlo Park Intern: Chris Berry, Annual Fund Manager and Eric Welsh, Volunteer Programs Associate\r\nDaly City Intern: Lynnelle Bilsey, Senior Manager of Volunteer Programs\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/interns/index.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-678 alignleft\" alt=\"apply internship button\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/apply-internship-button.png\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a>','Community Engagement Intern','','publish','closed','open','','community-engagement-intern','','','2014-02-06 10:45:07','2014-02-06 18:45:07','',632,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=680',49,'page','',0),(681,12,'2014-02-06 10:48:39','2014-02-06 18:48:39','<h1>Development Intern<a href=\"http://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/interns/index.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-678\" alt=\"apply internship button\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/apply-internship-button.png\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a></h1>\r\n<strong>Location:</strong> IVSN Administrative Office, 181 Constitution Drive, Menlo Park, CA 94025\r\n\r\n<strong>Time Commitment</strong>: 10 weeks: June 16th – August 15th, Full or Part Time (minimum 10 hours/week)\r\n<h2>Description</h2>\r\nInnVision Shelter Network (IVSN) is dedicated to helping homeless families and individuals across Silicon Valley and the San Francisco Peninsula return to permanent housing and self-sufficiency. We are looking for a dynamic and enthusiastic intern to support the agency’s donor cultivation and stewardship efforts. The Development Intern will be responsible for creating and distributing content to spread awareness of InnVision Shelter Network’s mission and solicit financial donations from current and potential donors, volunteers, and community partners.\r\n<h2>Responsibilities</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Draft information sheets on our work and issue areas</li>\r\n	<li>Mail approved letters to donors soliciting financial donations</li>\r\n	<li>Analyze donor records to determine whom to send mailings and online communications</li>\r\n	<li>Research community organizations that could be cultivated as donor prospects</li>\r\n	<li>Coordinate with Marketing to ensure messaging is consistent with agency branding</li>\r\n	<li>Complete special projects and provide organizational support as assigned</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Position Requirements/Preferred Skills</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>HS Diploma and some college</li>\r\n	<li>Very strong writing and proofreading skills</li>\r\n	<li>Profound attention to detail</li>\r\n	<li>Proficiency in MS Office Suite, particularly Outlook, Word, Excel, and PowerPoint</li>\r\n	<li>Familiarity with various social media platforms, and an aptitude for learning new ones</li>\r\n	<li>Diligent work ethic, positive attitude, and desire to learn</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Hands-on engagement in donor relationship management for one of the largest and most effective non-profit agencies serving homeless populations in the SF Bay Area</li>\r\n	<li>Insight into strategic decisions affecting the agency’s short and long-term growth</li>\r\n	<li>Networking opportunities for career development with InnVision Shelter Network staff, donors, volunteers, board members, and partner agencies</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Compensation:</b> Unpaid\r\n\r\n<b>Supervisor: </b>Chris Berry, Annual Fund Manager\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/interns/index.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-678 alignleft\" alt=\"apply internship button\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/apply-internship-button.png\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a>','Development Intern','','publish','closed','open','','development-intern','','','2014-02-06 10:48:39','2014-02-06 18:48:39','',632,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=681',48,'page','',0),(682,12,'2014-02-06 10:53:07','2014-02-06 18:53:07','<h1>Donor Research Intern<a href=\"http://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/interns/index.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-678\" alt=\"apply internship button\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/apply-internship-button.png\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a></h1>\r\n<strong>Location</strong>: IVSN Administrative Office, 181 Constitution Drive, Menlo Park, CA 94025\r\n\r\n<strong>Time Commitment</strong>: 10 weeks: June 16th – August 15th, Full or Part Time (minimum 20 hours/week)\r\n<h2>Description</h2>\r\nInnVision Shelter Network (IVSN) is dedicated to helping homeless families and individuals across Silicon Valley and the San Francisco Peninsula return to permanent housing and self-sufficiency. The Donor Research Intern will work in the Development/Fundraising Department, specifically with the Database Management Team. He/she is responsible for helping grow IVSN’s presence with local businesses, corporations, and our in-kind donors by improving our depth of donor insight and information accuracy.\r\n<h2>Responsibilities</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Research current and prospective corporate and local business donors</li>\r\n	<li>Analyze indicators for in-kind donors giving financially</li>\r\n	<li>Update/clean-up donor records in Raiser’s Edge with information from above research</li>\r\n	<li>Provide general staff support for the Data Management/Fundraising Team</li>\r\n	<li>Complete special projects and provide organizational support as assigned</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Position Requirements/Preferred Skills</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>HS Diploma and some college</li>\r\n	<li>Interest in refining/re-engaging our corporate and in-kind donor relationships</li>\r\n	<li>Commitment to agency mission</li>\r\n	<li>Resourcefulness</li>\r\n	<li>Attention to detail</li>\r\n	<li>Highly organized</li>\r\n	<li>Raiser’s Edge database experience is a plus</li>\r\n	<li>Basic proficiency in Microsoft Office</li>\r\n	<li>Diligent work ethic, positive attitude, and desire to learn about non-profits and/or development</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Hands-on learning of database management and the importance of data in running an organization</li>\r\n	<li>Working knowledge of a development department and how to develop and maintain relationships with donors</li>\r\n	<li>Gain a deeper understanding of a large non-profit through first-hand interactions and collaboration with members of various departments</li>\r\n	<li>Networking opportunities for career development with InnVision Shelter Network staff and partner agencies</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Compensation:</b> Unpaid\r\n\r\n<b>Supervisor: </b>Paula Martin, Donor Records Manager\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/interns/index.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-678 alignleft\" alt=\"apply internship button\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/apply-internship-button.png\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a>','Donor Research Intern','','publish','closed','open','','donor-research-intern','','','2014-02-06 10:53:28','2014-02-06 18:53:28','',632,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=682',47,'page','',0),(683,12,'2014-02-06 10:58:09','2014-02-06 18:58:09','<h1>Grants Intern<a href=\"http://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/interns/index.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-678\" alt=\"apply internship button\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/apply-internship-button.png\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a></h1>\r\n<strong>Location</strong>: IVSN Administrative Office, 181 Constitution Drive, Menlo Park, CA 94025\r\n\r\n<strong>Time Commitment</strong>: 10 weeks: June 16th – August 15th, Part Time (12-15 hours/week), Flexible scheduling\r\n<h2>Description</h2>\r\nInnVision Shelter Network (IVSN) is dedicated to helping homeless families and individuals across Silicon Valley and the San Francisco Peninsula return to permanent housing and self-sufficiency. Fundraising efforts are essential to supporting activities and programs so that we can fulfill our mission and do social good.  The Grants Intern will be deeply involved in the inner-workings of the agency’s Development/Fundraising Department, which supports our mission to end homelessness. They will assist with a broad range of tasks and work in a casual and fun office environment.  We are looking for a dynamic and enthusiastic intern to support the agency’s Grants Department.\r\n<h2>Responsibilities</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Participate in grant planning efforts</li>\r\n	<li>Assist in writing and organizing grant proposals and applications</li>\r\n	<li>Research new funding opportunities</li>\r\n	<li>Update and manage foundation/grants database</li>\r\n	<li>Collaborate with Grants Team, V.P. of Development, Executive Director, V.P. of Programs and others to compile, document, and prepare organizational data and accomplishments for grant use.</li>\r\n	<li>Help report on existing grants</li>\r\n	<li>Complete special projects and provide organizational support as assigned</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Position Requirements/Preferred Skills</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>HS Diploma and some college</li>\r\n	<li>Very strong writing and proofreading abilities</li>\r\n	<li>Profound attention to detail and excellent organizational skills</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to adapt to high work volume and specific deadlines</li>\r\n	<li>Proficiency in MS Office Suite, particularly Outlook, Word, and Excel</li>\r\n	<li>Experience in Raiser’s Edge (Preferred)</li>\r\n	<li>Basic familiarity with grants and strong interest in gaining experience with grant proposals. Prior grant writing experience desired, but not required</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to work within both in a team and independently</li>\r\n	<li>Humor and wit</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Hands-on engagement in grants and contracts for one of the largest and most effective non-profit agencies serving homeless populations in the SF Bay Area</li>\r\n	<li>Insight into executive-level strategic decisions affecting the agency’s short and long-term growth</li>\r\n	<li>Networking opportunities for career development with InnVision Shelter Network staff, donors and volunteers, board members, and partner agencies</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Compensation:</b> Unpaid\r\n\r\n<b>Supervisor:</b> Rena Davis, Grants Manager and Ellis Beier, Grant Writer\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/interns/index.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-678 alignleft\" alt=\"apply internship button\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/apply-internship-button.png\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a>','Grants Intern','','publish','closed','open','','grants-intern','','','2014-02-06 10:58:09','2014-02-06 18:58:09','',632,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=683',46,'page','',0),(684,12,'2014-02-06 11:01:49','2014-02-06 19:01:49','<img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-678\" alt=\"apply internship button\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/apply-internship-button.png\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" />\r\n<h1>Health Care for the Homeless Intern</h1>\r\n<b>Location:</b> The Vendome, 415 E. 2nd Avenue, San Mateo, CA (easy to access via train from San Francisco or San Jose\r\n\r\n<b>Time Commitment:</b> 10 weeks: June 16th – August 15th, Part time (minimum 15 hours/week), likely two days a week with flexible scheduling\r\n<h2>Description</h2>\r\nThe Health Care for the Homeless (HCH) program works to ensure access to health insurance and services and assists homeless clients through the complex social security disability process. The intern will work with current case managers to evaluate and design program features based on best practices research. All InnVision Shelter Network interns will participate in regularly scheduled events and activities that will introduce interns to each other, senior leadership, the Bay Area, homelessness, and various programs in the agency.\r\n<h2>Responsibilities</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Conference planning assistance (logistics, proposals, and marketing)</li>\r\n	<li>Draft research paper for potential submission to national conference</li>\r\n	<li>Assist in social security disability benefits claim preparation</li>\r\n	<li>Schedule and coordinate primary and behavioral health appointments for clients</li>\r\n	<li>Assist in health insurance outreach and education events</li>\r\n	<li>Administrative data input and reporting</li>\r\n	<li>Complete special projects and provide organizational support as assigned</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Position Requirements/Preferred Skills</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>HS Diploma and some college; bachelor’s degree preferred</li>\r\n	<li>Comfort working with the homeless community</li>\r\n	<li>Experience conducting self-directed qualitative research</li>\r\n	<li>Very strong writing and proofreading skills</li>\r\n	<li>Attention to detail</li>\r\n	<li>Diligent work ethic, positive attitude, and desire to learn about health care for the homeless</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Hands-on engagement in case management services for one of the largest and most effective non-profit agencies serving homeless populations in the SF Bay Area</li>\r\n	<li>Insight into public health policy and processes including social security and health care at the federal, state and county levels</li>\r\n	<li>Networking opportunities for career development with InnVision Shelter Network staff and partner agencies</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Compensation: </b>Unpaid\r\n\r\n<b>Supervisor:</b> Katie Dahlinghaus, Lead Case Manager, Health Care for the Homeless\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/interns/index.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-678 alignleft\" alt=\"apply internship button\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/apply-internship-button.png\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a>','Health Care for the Homeless Intern','','publish','closed','open','','health-care-for-the-homeless-intern','','','2014-02-06 11:06:15','2014-02-06 19:06:15','',632,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=684',44,'page','',0),(685,12,'2014-02-06 11:05:32','2014-02-06 19:05:32','<h1><a href=\"http://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/interns/index.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-678\" alt=\"apply internship button\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/apply-internship-button.png\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a>Housing Strategy Intern</h1>\r\n<b>Location: </b>Menlo Park Warehouse Offices, 190 Independence Avenue, Menlo Park, CA 94025\r\n\r\n<b>Time Commitment: </b>10 weeks: June 16th – August 15th, Full time\r\n<h2>Description</h2>\r\nThe Housing Strategy intern will work closely with the Senior Director of Housing Services on a variety of high-impact projects, with a special focus on improving the quality of life of IVSN clients in supportive housing programs by bringing in resources and community-building activities. Other major activities will include program evaluation, best-practices research, and community-engagement activities.\r\n<h2>Responsibilities</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Design and implement community-building projects for residents of IVSN housing programs, with a special focus on Atherton Court Apartments</li>\r\n	<li>Plan community events for residents with the goal of fostering a sense of community, ownership, and pride amongst supportive housing residents</li>\r\n	<li>Build relationships with local service providers and community partners to bring in services, activities, and educational opportunities for residents</li>\r\n	<li>Conduct program evaluations and best-practices research to make strategic recommendations for improving client outcomes in supportive housing programs</li>\r\n	<li>Present results and recommendations to Senior Staff</li>\r\n	<li>Track IVSN’s progress in meeting the objectives set forth in government contracts for Supportive Housing, and working with program staff to advise on how IVSN can best meet these goals</li>\r\n	<li>Complete special projects and provide organizational support as assigned</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Position Requirements/Preferred Skills</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>HS Diploma and some college (Bachelor’s degree/Graduate student preferred)</li>\r\n	<li>Highly motivated self-starter</li>\r\n	<li>Comfort working with all different types of people (including frustrated clients, clients with mental health challenges, clients struggling with substance abuse issues, etc.)</li>\r\n	<li>Strong analytical skills, comfort with light statistical analysis</li>\r\n	<li>Strong interest in issues surrounding homelessness and poverty</li>\r\n	<li>Very strong writing and proofreading skills</li>\r\n	<li>Diligent work ethic, positive attitude, and a desire to learn about InnVision Shelter Network’s mission to end homelessness</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Experience with community outreach, building strategic relationships</li>\r\n	<li>Experience working in a top notch non-profit organization</li>\r\n	<li>Experience in program evaluation, testing, and research</li>\r\n	<li>An understanding of federal, state and local government contracts</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Compensation:</b> Unpaid\r\n\r\n<b>Supervisor:</b> Eli Latimerlo, Case Manager and Life Coach\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/interns/index.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-678 alignleft\" alt=\"apply internship button\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/apply-internship-button.png\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a>','Housing Strategy Intern','','publish','closed','open','','housing-strategy-intern','','','2014-02-06 11:05:32','2014-02-06 19:05:32','',632,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=685',45,'page','',0),(686,12,'2014-02-06 11:09:23','2014-02-06 19:09:23','<h1><a href=\"http://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/interns/index.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-678\" alt=\"apply internship button\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/apply-internship-button.png\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a>Leadership Giving Intern</h1>\r\n<strong>Location</strong>: IVSN Administrative Office, 181 Constitution Drive, Menlo Park, CA 94025\r\n\r\n<strong>Time Commitment</strong>: 10 weeks: June 16th – August 15th, Full or Part Time, Flexible scheduling\r\n<h2>Description</h2>\r\nAt InnVision Shelter Network, our objective is to break the cycle of homelessness by providing shelter and comprehensive support programs while treating each participant with dignity and respect. The Leadership Giving Intern will work with the Major Gifts staff on high-level fundraising and strategy in order to fund that objective.\r\n<h2>Responsibilities</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Complete donor research on current and prospective donors</li>\r\n	<li>Create and update current and prospective donor profiles in database</li>\r\n	<li>Assist the Leadership Giving team with meeting preparation: call sheets, donor biographies, Raiser’s Edge record notes, etc.</li>\r\n	<li>Assist with Development events logistics including emails, invitations, and other materials</li>\r\n	<li>Assist on site at Leadership Giving events with registration, set up, etc.</li>\r\n	<li>Complete special projects and provide organizational support as assigned</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Position Requirements/Preferred Skills</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>HS Diploma and some college</li>\r\n	<li>Interest in learning about Major Gift fundraising</li>\r\n	<li>Interest in advocacy for the homeless</li>\r\n	<li>Professional and responsible demeanor</li>\r\n	<li>Strong writing and communication skills</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to multitask</li>\r\n	<li>Resourcefulness</li>\r\n	<li>Highly organized</li>\r\n	<li>Basic proficiency in Microsoft Office</li>\r\n	<li>Experience with project management</li>\r\n	<li>Humor and wit</li>\r\n	<li>Flexibility</li>\r\n	<li>Database experience is a plus (Raiser’s Edge)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Gain an excellent overview of Major Gifts fundraising</li>\r\n	<li>Gain a deeper understanding of a large non-profit through first-hand interactions and collaboration with members of various departments</li>\r\n	<li>Observe how a Development department uses varied income streams to meet a multi-million dollar budget</li>\r\n	<li>Learn how issues addressing the homeless are messaged to high level donors</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Compensation:</b> Unpaid\r\n\r\n<b>Supervisor:</b> Cory Ervin-Stewart, Leadership Gifts Director\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/interns/index.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-678 alignleft\" alt=\"apply internship button\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/apply-internship-button.png\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a>','Leadership Giving Intern','','publish','closed','open','','leadership-giving-intern','','','2014-02-06 11:09:23','2014-02-06 19:09:23','',632,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=686',43,'page','',0),(687,12,'2014-02-06 11:12:14','2014-02-06 19:12:14','<h1><a href=\"http://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/interns/index.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-678\" alt=\"apply internship button\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/apply-internship-button.png\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a>Marketing Intern</h1>\r\n<strong>Location</strong>: IVSN Administrative Office, 181 Constitution Drive, Menlo Park, CA 94025\r\n\r\n<strong>Time Commitment</strong>: 10 weeks: June 16th – August 15th, Full or Part Time, Flexible scheduling\r\n<h2>Description</h2>\r\nEver wonder how Apple, Nike, and the Red Cross become internationally-recognized brands? Nonprofit branding and marketing are essential to gaining supporters so that nonprofits can fulfill their mission and do social good.\r\n\r\nIVSN’s summer marketing intern will be deeply involved in the inner-workings of the agency’s Marketing Department. They will assist with a broad range of marketing activities, communications, public relations, social media, digital/online marketing, branding and collateral. The Marketing Intern will be responsible for supporting consistent branding and messaging, and spreading awareness of InnVision Shelter Network’s mission to current and potential donors, volunteers, and community partners.\r\n<h2>Responsibilities</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Draft articles for quarterly newsletter and weekly blog posts</li>\r\n	<li>Draft daily posts and monitor activity on Facebook and Twitter</li>\r\n	<li>Manage messaging across social media profiles, website, and collateral</li>\r\n	<li>Edit press releases and manage media articles</li>\r\n	<li>Apply standard graphics and formatting to documents and PowerPoint presentations</li>\r\n	<li>Monitor consistent use of collateral and signage at shelter locations</li>\r\n	<li>Complete special projects and provide organizational support as assigned</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Position Requirements/Preferred Skills</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>HS Diploma and some college</li>\r\n	<li>Very strong writing and proofreading skills</li>\r\n	<li>Profound attention to detail</li>\r\n	<li>Proficiency in MS Office Suite, particularly Outlook, Word, Excel, and PowerPoint</li>\r\n	<li>(Preferred) Experience with Adobe Creative Suite: Illustrator, InDesign, Photoshop</li>\r\n	<li>Diligent work ethic, positive attitude, and desire to learn about InnVision Shelter Network’s marketing strategies and business management techniques</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Hands-on engagement in marketing/communications for one of the largest and most effective non-profit agencies serving homeless populations in the SF Bay Area</li>\r\n	<li>Insight into executive-level strategic decisions affecting the agency’s short and long-term growth</li>\r\n	<li>Networking opportunities for career development with InnVision Shelter Network staff, donors and volunteers, board members, and partner agencies</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Compensation:</b> Unpaid\r\n\r\n<b>Supervisor:</b> Marketing Communications Manager\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/interns/index.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-678 alignleft\" alt=\"apply internship button\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/apply-internship-button.png\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a>','Marketing Intern','','publish','closed','open','','marketing-intern','','','2014-02-06 11:12:14','2014-02-06 19:12:14','',632,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=687',42,'page','',0),(688,12,'2014-02-06 11:15:55','2014-02-06 19:15:55','<h1><a href=\"http://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/interns/index.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-678\" alt=\"apply internship button\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/apply-internship-button.png\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a>Research Intern</h1>\r\n<strong>Location</strong>: IVSN Administrative Office, 181 Constitution Drive, Menlo Park, CA 94025\r\n\r\nNote: This position may also require visiting sites in the field throughout the San Francisco Peninsula and Silicon Valley\r\n\r\n<strong>Time Commitment</strong>: 10 weeks: June 16th – August 15th, Full or Part Time, Flexible scheduling\r\n<h2>Description</h2>\r\nInnVision Shelter Network is a large provider of shelter and ancillary services to homeless individuals and families in Silicon Valley. The Vice President of Programs at InnVision Shelter Network oversees 18 site-based homeless shelters and housing programs. The Research to Clinical Practice intern will have the opportunity to discuss and plan research opportunities with the agency’s Programs and IT Departments.\r\n<h2>Responsibilities</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Review database (and possibly peer review literature) to suggest areas for research and evaluation</li>\r\n	<li>Create a plan and meet with academics in order to encourage graduate students to do more research with IVSN</li>\r\n	<li>Assist the VP of Programs and serving as a liaison to site-based programs</li>\r\n	<li>Complete special projects and provide organizational support as assigned</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Position Requirements/Preferred Skills</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>HS Diploma and some college</li>\r\n	<li>Leadership experience amongst peers</li>\r\n	<li>Interest in homeless issues</li>\r\n	<li>Interest in research</li>\r\n	<li>Creative planning and activity design, with excellent follow through</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to work collaboratively and professionally with teen volunteers, donors, vendors, and clients</li>\r\n	<li>Pro-active self-starter, ability to work with minimal supervision</li>\r\n	<li>Diligent work ethic, positive attitude, and desire to learn about InnVision Shelter Network’s mission of ending homelessness</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Experience writing and researching collaboratively</li>\r\n	<li>Knowledge of how to examine complex databases in order to reflect on research possibilities</li>\r\n	<li>Exploration of the relationship between homeless programming, budgeting, contracting, and outcomes</li>\r\n	<li>Exposure to senior staff and insight into the operation of leading a nonprofit organization</li>\r\n	<li>Networking opportunities for career development with InnVision Shelter Network staff and partner agencies</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Compensation:</b> Unpaid, but associated costs (driving) will be reimbursed\r\n\r\n<b>Supervisor: </b>Brian Greenberg, Vice President of Programs\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/interns/index.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-678 alignleft\" alt=\"apply internship button\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/apply-internship-button.png\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a>','Research Intern','','publish','closed','open','','research-intern','','','2014-02-06 11:15:55','2014-02-06 19:15:55','',632,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=688',41,'page','',0),(689,12,'2014-02-06 11:22:22','2014-02-06 19:22:22','<h1><a href=\"http://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/interns/index.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-678\" alt=\"apply internship button\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/apply-internship-button.png\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a>Technology Innovation Intern</h1>\r\n<strong>Location</strong>: IVSN Administrative Office, 181 Constitution Drive, Menlo Park, CA 94025\r\n\r\n<strong>Time Commitment</strong>: 10 weeks: June 16th – August 15th, Full or Part Time, Flexible scheduling\r\n<h2>Description</h2>\r\nInnVision Shelter Network (IVSN) is focused on strategic improvement of processes and technology in order to better utilize our resources and better serve homeless individuals and families. Technology is rapidly advancing all around us, so the Technology Innovation Intern will help the agency move more quickly into the future. The Intern will work closely with the VP of Strategy and Technology, along with the Compliance and Tech team, to find ways to utilize technology in a way that optimizes outcomes for our clients.\r\n<h2>Responsibilities</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Identify opportunities for greater synergy and efficiency using technology</li>\r\n	<li>Make strategic recommendations for consolidation, improvement of services to improve IVSN staff efficiency</li>\r\n	<li>Conduct research as necessary to support technology assessment</li>\r\n	<li>Consult with intern supervisor to choose a specific technology innovation project to see through to implementation</li>\r\n	<li>Complete special projects and provide organizational support as assigned</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Position Requirements/Preferred Skills</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>HS Diploma and some college</li>\r\n	<li>Strong technology background and interest</li>\r\n	<li>Strong analytical and problem-solving skills</li>\r\n	<li>(Preferred) Experience with systems analysis and design, user-interface design, Salesforce administration/development, and/or database concepts</li>\r\n	<li>Diligent work ethic, positive attitude, and desire to learn about InnVision Shelter Network’s technology innovations and data/compliance systems</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Hands-on engagement in technology/compliance for one of the largest and most effective non-profit agencies serving homeless populations in the SF Bay Area</li>\r\n	<li>Insight into executive-level strategic decisions affecting the agency’s short and long-term growth</li>\r\n	<li>Networking opportunities for career development with InnVision Shelter Network staff, donors and volunteers, board members, and partner agencies</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Compensation:</b> Unpaid\r\n\r\n<b>Supervisor:</b> Dwight Powery, Vice President of Strategy and Technology\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/interns/index.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-678 alignleft\" alt=\"apply internship button\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/apply-internship-button.png\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a>','Technology Innovation Intern','','publish','closed','open','','technology-innovation-intern','','','2014-02-06 11:22:22','2014-02-06 19:22:22','',632,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=689',40,'page','',0),(690,12,'2014-02-06 11:25:12','2014-02-06 19:25:12','<h1><a href=\"http://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/interns/index.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-678\" alt=\"apply internship button\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/apply-internship-button.png\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a>Volunteer Programs Intern</h1>\r\n<strong>Location</strong>: IVSN Administrative Office, 181 Constitution Drive, Menlo Park, CA 94025\r\n\r\n<strong>Time Commitment</strong>: 10 weeks: June 16th – August 15th, Full or Part Time, Flexible scheduling\r\n<h2>Description</h2>\r\nThe Volunteer Programs Intern will be part of the IVSN Volunteer team and will be responsible for developing the materials necessary to train and equip IVSN staff and key volunteers to provide site tours to the community, corporate and individual donors, and donor prospects.\r\n<h2>Responsibilities</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Design and produce a site tour tutorial for each of IVSN’s sites\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Communicate what populations and how many people are served</li>\r\n	<li>Highlight how the community has supported the site</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>Train site staff and other staff on how to give a tour</li>\r\n	<li>Work with Volunteer Programs to package donor and prospective volunteer tours at each IVSN shelter</li>\r\n	<li>Meet with program directors and shelter staff to develop meaningful and concise talking points for tours</li>\r\n	<li>Complete special projects and provide organizational support as assigned</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Position Requirements/Preferred Skills</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>HS Degree and some college</li>\r\n	<li>Comfort working independently and taking ownership over a project</li>\r\n	<li>Interest in community relationship building</li>\r\n	<li>Strong written and communication skills</li>\r\n	<li>A team player attitude</li>\r\n	<li>Highly organized</li>\r\n	<li>Proficient in Microsoft Office, specifically, Excel, Word, and Outlook Calendaring</li>\r\n	<li>Analytical and tech savvy</li>\r\n	<li>Flexibility</li>\r\n	<li>Humor and wit</li>\r\n	<li>Tour guiding or customer service experience preferred</li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">This role will require the use of a private vehicle</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Gain an excellent overview of community relationship building</li>\r\n	<li>Develop a deep understanding of a non-profit through first-hand interactions and collaboration with members of various departments</li>\r\n	<li>Grow strong cross departmental communication skills</li>\r\n	<li>Build your understanding of the issue of homelessness and the need for community engagement</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Compensation:</b> Unpaid, but associated costs (driving) will be reimbursed\r\n\r\n<b>Supervisors: </b>Eric Welsh, Volunteer Programs Associate\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/interns/index.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-678 alignleft\" alt=\"apply internship button\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/apply-internship-button.png\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a>','Volunteer Programs Intern','','publish','closed','open','','volunteer-programs-intern','','','2014-02-06 11:25:12','2014-02-06 19:25:12','',632,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=690',39,'page','',0),(693,12,'2014-02-06 13:27:08','2014-02-06 21:27:08','<h1><a href=\"http://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/interns/index.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-678\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/apply-internship-button.png\" alt=\"apply internship button\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a>Summer Camp Director Internship</h1>\r\n<h2>InnVision Shelter Network is looking for Children’s Summer Camp Directors at different camp locations in Santa Clara and San Mateo Counties for Summer Adventure Camp!</h2>\r\nWe are looking for dynamic and enthusiastic Camp Directors over the course of 9 weeks, to develop, launch, and manage the children’s summer camps at InnVision Shelter Network (IVSN), a leading Bay Area nonprofit providing homeless services and shelters.\r\n\r\nIVSN’s Summer Camps provide homeless and extremely low-income children living in shelters with an engaging, fun, and educational summer experience. Summer Camp is an important component of InnVision Shelter Network’s “Beyond the Bed” supportive services that help families break the cycle of homelessness and return to self-sufficiency. In providing opportunities homeless children might not otherwise have access to, the Camp supports each child’s growth and education, while allowing parents to continue work or to search for permanent housing during the summer months.\r\n\r\nEach IVSN family shelter and drop-in center operates a camp for school-aged children, ages 5-14. Camp activities are organized around weekly themes, such as outer space, sports, water, etc, which are designed to provide children with a range of educational opportunities and highlight new skills and career paths. The Camp Director is responsible for designing and overseeing all camp programming.\r\n\r\nAll IVSN Camp Directors will participate in regularly scheduled events and activities that will introduce them to the rest of their intern class, IVSN Senior Leadership, the Bay Area, homelessness, and various programs in the agency.\r\n\r\nTo learn more, check out our <a href=\"http://ivsnsummercamp.wordpress.com/\" target=\"_blank\">blog</a> from last summer’s camp!\r\n<h2>Time Commitment</h2>\r\n9 weeks: June 15th – August 14th, Monday – Friday 8am to 4pm\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>First week is orientation and introductions for all interns (June 15-19)</li>\r\n	<li>8 weeks of Summer Adventure Camp (June 22-August 14)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Locations</h2>\r\nIVSN is seeking 1-2 Camp Directors for each of our 6 shelters and drop-in centers.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><del>Family Crossroads, Daly City, 1 Camp Director </del> (Not Available 2015)</li>\r\n	<li>First Step for Families, San Mateo, 2 Camp Directors</li>\r\n	<li>Redwood Family House, Redwood City, 1 Camp Director</li>\r\n	<li>Haven Family House, Menlo Park, 2 Camp Directors</li>\r\n	<li>Opportunity Services Center, Palo Alto, 2 Camp Directors</li>\r\n	<li>Commercial Street Inn, San Jose, 2 Camp Directors</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Responsibilities</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Plan and oversee camp activities that are fun, engaging, and highlight new skills or career paths</li>\r\n	<li>Manage a staff of 5-15 high school aged volunteers</li>\r\n	<li>Arrange weekly field trips</li>\r\n	<li>Develop and manage a summer budget for all activities and supplies</li>\r\n	<li>Create food plan and order all necessary supplies, assign volunteers to prepare food</li>\r\n	<li>Carefully document and track paperwork and receipts from purchases</li>\r\n	<li>Help create a camp blog documenting daily camp activities to be distributed to an audience of parents, donors, and supporters</li>\r\n	<li>Lead weekly meetings with colleagues and camp staff at other sites.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Position Requirements/Preferred Skills</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>HS Diploma and 2+ years of college</li>\r\n	<li>Experience working with school age children</li>\r\n	<li>Leadership experience amongst peers</li>\r\n	<li>Creative planning and activity design, with excellent follow through</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to work collaboratively and professionally with teen volunteers, donors, vendors, and clients</li>\r\n	<li>Pro-active self-starter, ability to work with minimal supervision</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to enforce rules to keep children safe</li>\r\n	<li>Diligent work ethic, positive attitude, and desire to learn about InnVision Shelter Network’s mission of ending homelessness</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Experience managing finance, vendor relationships, a full staff, and clients</li>\r\n	<li>Experience designing programming for at-risk children, and seeing it through to implementation</li>\r\n	<li>Exposure to senior staff and insight into the operation of leading a nonprofit organization</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Compensation: </b>Unpaid\r\n\r\n<b>Supervisors:</b> The Children’s Services Coordinator and Program Director at the specific site\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/interns/index.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-678 alignleft\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/apply-internship-button.png\" alt=\"apply internship button\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a>','Summer Camp Director','','publish','closed','open','','summer-camp-director','','','2015-02-23 11:33:08','2015-02-23 19:33:08','',632,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=693',35,'page','',0),(701,12,'2014-02-12 11:37:06','2014-02-12 19:37:06','','duncan','','inherit','closed','open','','duncan','','','2014-02-12 11:37:06','2014-02-12 19:37:06','',665,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/duncan.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(702,12,'2014-02-12 11:37:26','2014-02-12 19:37:26','','nagaraj','','inherit','closed','open','','nagaraj','','','2014-02-12 11:37:26','2014-02-12 19:37:26','',665,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/nagaraj.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(703,12,'2014-02-12 11:37:41','2014-02-12 19:37:41','','carrol keeley','','inherit','closed','open','','carrol-keeley','','','2014-02-12 11:37:41','2014-02-12 19:37:41','',665,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/carrol-keeley.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(704,12,'2014-02-12 11:38:15','2014-02-12 19:38:15','','cardona','','inherit','closed','open','','cardona','','','2014-02-12 11:38:15','2014-02-12 19:38:15','',665,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/cardona.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(705,12,'2014-02-12 11:38:29','2014-02-12 19:38:29','','espinoza','','inherit','closed','open','','espinoza','','','2014-02-12 11:38:29','2014-02-12 19:38:29','',665,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/espinoza.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(706,12,'2014-02-12 11:38:39','2014-02-12 19:38:39','','headley','','inherit','closed','open','','headley','','','2014-02-12 11:38:39','2014-02-12 19:38:39','',665,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/headley.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(707,12,'2014-02-12 11:38:55','2014-02-12 19:38:55','','klein','','inherit','closed','open','','klein','','','2014-02-12 11:38:55','2014-02-12 19:38:55','',665,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/klein.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(708,12,'2014-02-12 11:39:05','2014-02-12 19:39:05','','mcdougall','','inherit','closed','open','','mcdougall','','','2014-02-12 11:39:05','2014-02-12 19:39:05','',665,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/mcdougall.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(709,12,'2014-02-12 11:39:16','2014-02-12 19:39:16','','stewart','','inherit','closed','open','','stewart','','','2014-02-12 11:39:16','2014-02-12 19:39:16','',665,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/stewart.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(710,12,'2014-02-12 11:39:27','2014-02-12 19:39:27','','taube','','inherit','closed','open','','taube','','','2014-02-12 11:39:27','2014-02-12 19:39:27','',665,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/taube.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(711,12,'2014-02-12 11:39:37','2014-02-12 19:39:37','','valencia','','inherit','closed','open','','valencia','','','2014-02-12 11:39:37','2014-02-12 19:39:37','',665,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/valencia.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(712,12,'2014-02-12 11:39:50','2014-02-12 19:39:50','','woodson','','inherit','closed','open','','woodson','','','2014-02-12 11:39:50','2014-02-12 19:39:50','',665,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/woodson.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(717,12,'2014-03-03 11:51:35','2014-03-03 19:51:35','<img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-666\" alt=\"nextgen_web\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/nextgen_web.png\" width=\"320\" height=\"231\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>MENLO PARK, CA</strong> - InnVision Shelter Network (IVSN) is excited to announce the creation of its NextGen Advisory Board. This new initiative brings together young professional leaders in the Bay Area who are socially conscious and striving to make an impact. The NextGen Advisory Board will drive strategic and tactical innovation by leveraging their knowledge of technology and social media tools. The Board will also focus on increasing awareness within the young professional population of Silicon Valley about the severity of homelessness and the successful methods IVSN employs to tackle homelessness in our community.\r\n\r\nThe founding cohort of twelve Board members has strong professional and academic backgrounds and includes professionals from large tech companies, emerging growth companies, venture capital firms and social sector organizations. InnVision Shelter Network CEO Karae Lisle said, “It’s important to recognize and foster the commitment of the millennial generation to homelessness and nonprofit leadership. There are new and innovative ideas about how to tackle poverty and we are thrilled to have a diverse group committed to using their skills and experience to further IVSN’s mission of ending homelessness.”\r\n\r\n<strong>Julia Duncan</strong> (Co-Chair), Google\r\n<strong>Sunil Nagaraj</strong> (Co-Chair), Bessemer Venture Partners\r\n<strong>Austin Carroll Keeley</strong>, The Stanford Fund\r\n<strong>Angelina Cardona</strong>, Google (via Nelson)\r\n<strong>Casandra Espinoza</strong>, Most recently at Greylock Partners\r\n<strong>Michael Headley</strong>, Google\r\n<strong>Adam Klein</strong>, InnVision Shelter Network\r\n<strong>Ryan McDougall</strong>, Zynga\r\n<strong>Jeremy Stewart</strong>, Oakland Raiders\r\n<strong>Sean Taube</strong>, Wilson Sonsini Goodrich &amp; Rosati\r\n<strong>Daniel Valencia</strong>, Academix Direct\r\n<strong>Elizabeth Woodson</strong>, Stanford University Student\r\n\r\nCONTACT: Mila Zelkha\r\n650-518-0040, <a href=\"mailto:mzelkha@ivsn.org\">mzelkha@ivsn.org</a>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">###</p>\r\nInnVision Shelter Network is dedicated to helping homeless families and individuals in San Mateo and Santa Clara counties return to permanent housing and self-sufficiency. IVSN operates 18 sites from San Jose to Daly City, serving thousands of homeless clients annually through its “Beyond the Bed” services—a proven model that delivers a 90% success rate in transitional program graduates to permanent housing and self-sufficiency. For further information on IVSN and the NextGen Advisory Board, please visit <a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/about/nextgen\">www.ivsn.org/about/nextgen</a>','InnVision Shelter Network Creates Young Community Leaders Board to Tackle Local Homelessness','','publish','closed','open','','innvision-shelter-network-creates-young-community-leaders-board-to-tackle-local-homelessness','','','2014-03-03 11:52:12','2014-03-03 19:52:12','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/?p=717',23,'post','',0),(719,12,'2014-01-07 11:58:17','2014-01-07 19:58:17','<strong><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-720\" alt=\"charity navigator image\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/charity-navigator-image.png\" width=\"320\" height=\"231\" />MENLO PARK, CA</strong> – InnVision Shelter Network (ivsn.org), the leading nonprofit serving homeless families and individuals across Silicon Valley and the San Francisco Peninsula, has been awarded Charity Navigator’s top 4-star rating for the sixth consecutive year.\r\n\r\nThe 4-star rating acknowledges charities that have achieved sound fiscal management and commitment to accountability and transparency. Of the 7,000 organizations evaluated by Charity Navigator, <strong>only 3% have received the 4-star rating for six years in a row, placing InnVision Shelter Network among the highest-rated charities in the country.</strong>\r\n\r\n“Receiving the 4-star rating from Charity Navigator is a testament to the strength of our efficient programming and our board of directors’ fiscally conservative guidance,” said Karae Lisle, CEO of Shelter Network. “We are honored to receive this distinguished rating for a sixth year, and will continue to strive for the highest standard of excellence in serving our homeless clients.”\r\n\r\n<em>Forbes, Business Week,</em> and <em>Kiplinger\'s Financial Magazine</em>, among others, have profiled and celebrated Charity Navigator’s unique method of applying data-driven analysis to rate the fiscal effectiveness of organizations in the nonprofit sector. They evaluate ten times more charities than their nearest competitor and currently attract more web visitors researching charitable organizations than all other charity rating groups combined, thus making them the leading charity evaluator in America. It is estimated that last year, Charity Navigator influenced approximately $10 billion in philanthropic giving.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/Charity-Navigator-Letter-2013.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Read InnVision Shelter Network’s 4-star award letter from Charity Navigator.</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.charitynavigator.org/index.cfm?bay=search.summary&amp;orgid=8790#.UrhoAfRDsp-\" target=\"_blank\">View InnVision Shelter Network’s profile on Charity Navigator’s website.</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>CONTACT</strong>: Maria Duzon, Associate Director of Marketing\r\n650-248-6766 | <a href=\"mailto:mduzon@ivsn.org\" target=\"_blank\">mduzon@ivsn.org</a>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">###</p>\r\nInnVision Shelter Network (IVSN) is the leading provider of shelter/housing and supportive services across Silicon Valley and the San Francisco Peninsula. IVSN operates 18 sites from San Jose to Daly City, providing emergency, transitional, and permanent supportive housing, along with a vast array of supportive resources to help clients secure a place to call ‘home.’\r\n\r\nIVSN serves thousands of homeless clients annually through its “Beyond the Bed” service model – a proven methodology that has historically delivered a 90% success rate in returning program graduates to permanent housing and self-sufficiency. Through community support – including financial contributions, in-kind donations, and volunteerism – IVSN empowers those in our community struggling with poverty and homelessness to gain valuable skills that lead to long-term self-sufficiency. <a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org\">www.ivsn.org</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','InnVision Shelter Network receives top 4-star Charity Navigator rating  for sixth consecutive year','','publish','closed','open','','innvision-shelter-network-receives-top-4-star-charity-navigator-rating-for-sixth-consecutive-year','','','2014-03-03 12:04:27','2014-03-03 20:04:27','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/?p=719',25,'post','',0),(720,12,'2014-03-03 12:01:45','2014-03-03 20:01:45','','charity navigator image','','inherit','closed','open','','charity-navigator-image','','','2014-03-03 12:01:45','2014-03-03 20:01:45','',719,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/charity-navigator-image.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(721,12,'2014-03-03 12:01:48','2014-03-03 20:01:48','','charity navigator thumbnail','','inherit','closed','open','','charity-navigator-thumbnail','','','2014-03-03 12:01:48','2014-03-03 20:01:48','',719,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/charity-navigator-thumbnail.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(722,12,'2014-02-11 12:05:43','2014-02-11 20:05:43','<h2>Investing in Nutritious Food for Homeless People Served</h2>\r\n<strong>MENLO PARK, CA</strong> – InnVision Shelter Network (IVSN), a nonprofit organization serving homeless families and individuals throughout Silicon Valley and the San Francisco Peninsula, is launching a plan to enhance the food services it provides for homeless and low-income individuals. Calling it an “essential investment,” the agency is proud to announce an important step forward by hiring Mark Farhat as its first Food Innovation Manager. Hiring Mr. Farhat is a critical element in the agency’s overall strategy to improve the nutritional quality of the food it provides, to increase their clients’ access to nutritious food, to enhance efficiencies and cost effectiveness, and to continue to deepen its long-standing food delivery and service partnerships with community volunteers.\r\n\r\nThe addition of Food Innovation Manager demonstrates IVSN’s commitment to its core food service programs, resulting from a six-month analysis of its legacy food programs. Mr. Farhat will collaborate with IVSN’s clinical staff and skill-based volunteers, including licensed dieticians and nutritionists, to implement more nutritional education elements to the overall service the agency provides. Mr. Farhat will also work closely with the many dedicated volunteers and donors throughout the community who have worked consistently for over 30 years to provide healthy and nutritious meals every day.\r\n\r\nThe funding for Mr. Farhat’s position is made possible by a generous gift from an anonymous donor. “Good nutrition is an issue near and dear to my heart,” writes the donor. “I am pleased to sponsor this key role at InnVision Shelter Network, and I am looking forward to the benefits that will be derived by their clients as a result.”\r\n\r\n“We are deeply grateful for the tradition of active support from the community to help our staff provide good nutrition for our clients. By working together, we continue to fulfill our mission to help homeless families and individuals break the cycle of homelessness and return to a place they can call home,” said Karae Lisle, CEO of InnVision Shelter Network. “Mark Farhat will help us coordinate more closely with our existing partners and expand our network of community collaborators to make an even greater impact. We are continually seeking innovative ways to leverage resources that will improve the lives of the homeless individuals and families we serve.”\r\n\r\nIVSN expects to spend approximately $250,000 to provide nutritious food services this year. It will continue to work in close partnership with Second Harvest Food Bank, their primary food partner, and with corporate sponsors, faith-based and community volunteer organizations, and countless individuals to generate financial and volunteer support for the food services program, that is a critical part of their “Beyond the Bed” service model.\r\n\r\n<strong>CONTACT:</strong> Mila Zelkha, Director of Strategic Relations\r\n650-518-0040 | <a href=\"mailto:mzelkha@ivsn.org\" target=\"_blank\">mzelkha@ivsn.org</a>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">###</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">InnVision Shelter Network (IVSN) is the leading provider of shelter/housing and supportive services across Silicon Valley and the San Francisco Peninsula. IVSN operates 18 sites from San Jose to Daly City, providing preventative, emergency, interim, and permanent supportive housing solutions, along with other supportive resources to help clients find a place to call ‘home.’</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>IVSN recently received a top 4-star Charity Navigator rating for the sixth consecutive year.</strong></p>\r\nIVSN serves thousands of homeless clients annually through its “Beyond the Bed” service model – a proven methodology that has historically delivered a 90% success rate in returning program graduates to permanent housing and self-sufficiency. Through community support – including financial contributions, in-kind donations, and volunteerism – IVSN empowers those in our community struggling with poverty and homelessness to gain valuable skills that lead to long-term self-sufficiency. <a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org\">www.ivsn.org</a>','InnVision Shelter Network Appoints Food Innovation Manager','','publish','closed','open','','innvision-shelter-network-appoints-food-innovation-manager','','','2014-03-03 12:09:16','2014-03-03 20:09:16','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/?p=722',24,'post','',0),(728,12,'2014-03-07 10:52:15','2014-03-07 18:52:15','','Annual Report 2013 thumbnail','','inherit','closed','open','','annual-report-2013-thumbnail','','','2014-03-07 10:52:15','2014-03-07 18:52:15','',250,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Annual-Report-2013-thumbnail.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(729,12,'2014-03-07 11:06:29','2014-03-07 19:06:29','','fall 2013 newsletter thumbnail','','inherit','closed','open','','fall-2013-newsletter-thumbnail','','','2014-03-07 11:06:29','2014-03-07 19:06:29','',250,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/fall-2013-newsletter-thumbnail.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(730,12,'2014-03-07 11:06:33','2014-03-07 19:06:33','','spring 2013 newsletter thumbnail','','inherit','closed','open','','spring-2013-newsletter-thumbnail','','','2014-03-07 11:06:33','2014-03-07 19:06:33','',250,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/spring-2013-newsletter-thumbnail.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(731,12,'2014-03-07 11:06:36','2014-03-07 19:06:36','','fall 2012 newsletter thumbnail','','inherit','closed','open','','fall-2012-newsletter-thumbnail','','','2014-03-07 11:06:36','2014-03-07 19:06:36','',250,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/fall-2012-newsletter-thumbnail.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(732,12,'2014-03-07 11:15:03','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<h1>Publications</h1>\r\n<h2>Annual Reports</h2>\r\nAnnual Report 2012-2013 - Coming Soon!\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-728\" alt=\"Annual Report 2013 thumbnail\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Annual-Report-2013-thumbnail.png\" width=\"150\" height=\"194\" />\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/IVSN-Annual-Report-2013_donorlist.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">