014-09-02 11:53:52','2014-09-02 18:53:52','',738,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Meal-Provider-Volunteer-Manual-9-2-14.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(975,12,'2014-09-09 16:19:28','2014-09-09 23:19:28','','HolidayLogo','','inherit','closed','open','','holidaylogo','','','2014-09-09 16:19:28','2014-09-09 23:19:28','',216,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/HolidayLogo.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(976,12,'2014-09-09 16:38:26','2014-09-09 23:38:26','','Holiday-Logo2','','inherit','closed','open','','holiday-logo2','','','2014-09-09 16:38:26','2014-09-09 23:38:26','',216,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Holiday-Logo2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(977,12,'2014-09-10 13:57:59','2014-09-10 20:57:59','','ivsn_newsletter_fall_2014','','inherit','closed','open','','ivsn_newsletter_fall_2014','','','2014-09-10 13:57:59','2014-09-10 20:57:59','',179,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ivsn_newsletter_fall_2014.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(979,12,'2014-09-11 16:53:09','2014-09-11 23:53:09','','Diana','','inherit','closed','open','','diana','','','2014-09-11 16:53:09','2014-09-11 23:53:09','',18,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Diana.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(984,12,'2014-09-15 09:19:47','2014-09-15 16:19:47','<h1>Case Manager, Villa</h1>\r\n<strong>SUPERVISOR:                     </strong>Program Director\r\n\r\n<strong>LOCATION:                         </strong>Villa\r\n\r\n<strong>HOURS:                                 </strong>Monday – Friday (could include weekends/evenings as needed)\r\n\r\n<strong>STATUS:                               </strong>Full-time, non-exempt\r\n\r\n<strong>SALARY:                              </strong>DOE\r\n\r\n<strong>Qualifications:                        </strong>\r\n\r\nBachelor’s degree in social work or related field preferred. Prefer a minimum two years experience in serving homeless families in crisis. Excellent interpersonal skills and ability to collaborate with other agencies. Experience working with dually diagnosed clients/and the chronically homeless. Understanding of the issues faced by disenfranchised populations. Bi-lingual capabilities are preferred but not necessary.\r\n\r\n<strong>Responsibilities:                     </strong>\r\n\r\nThe Case Manager will provide a full array of case management services to homeless individuals in a shelter environment. Meet weekly with program staff to coordinate delivery of services. Meet regularly with Program Director for supervision. Participate in meetings with other agency staff and community agencies. Fill other reasonable requests as made by supervisor, including assistance across program lines.\r\n\r\n<strong>Duties:</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Case Management</strong>\r\n\r\nCase management services include but are not limited to intakes, assessments, crisis intervention, community referrals, and regular appointments to assist participants meet their goals. Provide information, referral, and crisis intervention as needed. Keep case files and all other record keeping up-to-date, thorough, and accurate.\r\n\r\n<strong>Program Development</strong>\r\n\r\nAssist Program Director in designing, planning and implementing program services. Emphasis on building accountability process for program participants as they strive to move forward in their lives.\r\n\r\n<strong>Facilities</strong>\r\n\r\nAssist Program Director to ensure the health and safety of program participants’ thorough management of the physical plant. This includes safety, hygiene, appearance and overall aesthetic of the facility. Must be prepared to respond to emergencies with cleat thinking and swift action.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nTo apply, please e-mail a resume and a brief cover letter with the JOB TITLE in the subject line to: <strong>jobs@ivsn.org</strong>\r\n\r\nNO PHONE CALLS PLEASE. Thank you in advance to all applicants for their interest, time, and effort.\r\n\r\nInnVision Shelter Network is an Equal Opportunity Employer (EOE).','Case Manager, Villa','','publish','closed','open','','case-manager-villa','','','2015-01-13 11:38:36','2015-01-13 19:38:36','',251,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=984',19,'page','',0),(985,12,'2014-09-15 09:21:15','2014-09-15 16:21:15','<h1>Housing Developer, Montgomery Street Inn</h1>\r\nSTATUS:                                Part-time, non-exempt\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Our Agency: </strong>\r\n\r\nInnVision Shelter Network (IVSN) is one of the largest and most effective providers of shelter/housing and\r\n\r\nsupportive services across Silicon Valley and the San Francisco Peninsula. IVSN operates over 18 major\r\n\r\nsites from San Jose to Daly City, providing emergency, transitional, and permanent supportive housing,\r\n\r\nalong with a breadth of supportive resources to help clients secure a place to call home. The organization\r\n\r\nserves thousands of homeless clients annually through its \"Beyond the Bed\" service model -- a proven\r\n\r\nmethodology that has historically delivered a 90% success rate in returning program graduates to permanent\r\n\r\nhousing and self-sufficiency.\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Qualifications:                        </strong>\r\n\r\nBachelor’s degree in social work or related field preferred. Prefer a minimumtwo years experience in\r\n\r\nserving homeless individuals in crisis. The ideal candidate will possess excellent interpersonal skills and\r\n\r\nability to collaborate with other agencies. Experience working with dually diagnosed clients/and the\r\n\r\nchronically homeless. Understanding of the issues faced by disenfranchised populations.\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Responsibilities:                     </strong>\r\n\r\nThe Housing Developer will work with IVSN Case Managers and IVSN clients to identify and secure stable\r\n\r\nhousing. The Housing Developer will be responsible for collecting and reporting all data on clients\r\n\r\nparticipating in the program and will generate both statistical and narrative reports when needed.\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Duties:                                    </strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Work with IVSN clients</li>\r\n	<li>Build relationships with landlords</li>\r\n	<li>Conduct Housing 101 Workshops</li>\r\n	<li>Assist clients in filling out rental applications</li>\r\n	<li>Teach clients landlord interviewing skills</li>\r\n	<li>Teach clients the attributes of a responsible tenant</li>\r\n	<li>Must be able to have a reliable form of transportation</li>\r\n	<li>Build relationships with IVSN Case Managers to meet the needs of the clients</li>\r\n	<li>Negotiate with landlords to establish fair rent for clients</li>\r\n	<li>Collect and store statistical data on clients served and generate reports as needed per PATH data requirements</li>\r\n	<li>Spanish speaking a plus</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nTo apply, please e-mail a resume and a brief cover letter with the JOB TITLE in the subject line to: <strong>jobs@ivsn.org</strong>\r\n\r\nNO PHONE CALLS PLEASE. Thank you in advance to all applicants for their interest, time, and effort.\r\n\r\nInnVision Shelter Network is an Equal Opportunity Employer (EOE).','Housing Developer, Montgomery Street Inn','','publish','closed','open','','housing-developer-montgomery-street-inn','','','2014-09-15 09:22:13','2014-09-15 16:22:13','',251,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=985',20,'page','',0),(994,12,'2014-10-13 15:18:24','2014-10-13 22:18:24','<h1>Outreach Case Manager<strong> </strong></h1>\r\nTitle: Citywide Outreach Case Manager\r\n\r\nSupervisor: Associate Director of Housing Services\r\n\r\nLocation: Downtown San Jose\r\n\r\nHours: Varies\r\n\r\nStatus: Full Time, Non-Exempt\r\n\r\nInnVision Shelter Network (IVSN) is one of the largest and most effective providers of shelter/housing and supportive services across Silicon Valley and the San Francisco Peninsula. IVSN operates over 18 major sites from San Jose to Daly City, providing emergency, transitional, and permanent supportive housing, along with a breadth of supportive resources to help clients secure a place to call home. The organization serves thousands of homeless clients annually through its \"Beyond the Bed\" service model -- a proven methodology that has historically delivered a 90% success rate in returning program graduates to permanent housing and self-sufficiency.\r\n\r\nInnVision Shelter Network is looking for an energetic self-starter who works diligently with compassion, both alone and in small groups. Possess a take charge attitude to meet and exceed goals with client populations. Candidate needs to have experience in working with homeless populations. Minimum two years in direct service to homeless individuals in crisis, Bachelor’s degree in social work or related field preferred. A thorough understanding of the issues facing chronically homeless individuals in needed, as well as the energy and enthusiasm to help others with those challenges. Prior experience in outreach a plus. Spanish Speaking preferred. Automobile, valid driver’s license and clean driving record required. Must be computer literate and proficient in Microsoft Office Suite.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe Outreach Case Manager will work in targeted areas of San Jose to provide services to unsheltered homeless persons. The Outreach Case Manager will be in the field 70% of the time, working to engage homeless people living in places not suitable for human habitation. The remainder of time will be spent on case notes and coordination meetings with colleagues and community partners.\r\n\r\n1. <strong>Outreach Case Management: </strong>Provide outreach and case management services to unsheltered homeless individuals in San Jose. Identify target population and perform screening assessments and ongoing case management to assist participants to meet their goals. Provide information, referrals and crisis intervention as needed. Keep case files up-to-date, thorough, and accurate. Assist in compiling program statistics.\r\n\r\n2. <strong>Meetings: </strong>Meet weekly with program staff to coordinate delivery of services. Meet weekly with supervisor for supervision. Participate in meetings with other community agencies. Fill other requests as made by supervisor, including assistance across program lines.\r\n\r\n3. <strong>Job Development: </strong>Assess client’s work readiness, make referrals, and provide job search skills training. Create and maintain job listings. Develop contacts with potential employers. Maintain professional relationships with referral agencies.\r\n\r\n4. <strong>Housing Readiness:</strong> The Outreach Case Manager will work will homeless individuals to transition them quickly to permanent housing. In some cases this will require referrals to shelter while individuals conduct housing searches. Provide housing counseling. Create and maintain working relationships with local landlords and leasing agencies.   Provide follow-up case management as needed to housed clients\r\n\r\n5. <strong>Other: </strong>Assist in maintaining a clean and safe work environment. Carry IVSN cell phone as necessary. Other related duties as assigned.\r\n\r\nTo apply, please e-mail a resume and a brief cover letter with the JOB TITLE in the subject line to jobs@ivsn.org.\r\n\r\nNO PHONE CALLS PLEASE. Thank you in advance to all applicants for their interest, time, and effort.\r\n\r\nInnVision Shelter Network is an Equal Opportunity Employer (EOE).','San Jose Outreach Case Manager','','publish','closed','open','','san-jose-outreach-case-manager','','','2014-10-13 15:21:34','2014-10-13 22:21:34','',251,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=994',18,'page','',0),(997,12,'2014-10-16 12:22:30','2014-10-16 19:22:30','<h2>VIDEO HIGHLIGHTS</h2>\r\nThank you to Reza Tabesh for this 5.5 minute highlight video of our 2014 Benefit Breakfast. Enjoy:\r\n\r\n[embed]http://vimeo.com/110104401[/embed]\r\n<h2>Gina Berryhill, Client Speaker</h2>\r\nGina, a graduate of InnVision Shelter Network, tells her story of how IVSN helped her family in their journey from homelessness to self-sufficiency.\r\n\r\n[embed]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TUv_sVZYMvE[/embed]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_999\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"314\"]<img class=\"wp-image-999\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/DSC_7038_2-320x288.jpg\" alt=\"DSC_7038_2\" width=\"314\" height=\"283\" /> Client Speaker Gina Berryhill with her \"math whiz\" daughter at the Benefit Breakfast[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1005\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"320\" class=\" \"]<img class=\"wp-image-1005 size-medium\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/Gina-Berryhill-320x213.jpg\" alt=\"Gina Berryhill\" width=\"320\" height=\"213\" /> Gina stands alongside IVSN CEO Karae Lisle as she receives a standing ovation following her speech. Photo by Tom Jung/San Mateo Daily Journal[/caption]\r\n<h2>Karae Lisle, CEO</h2>\r\nKarae Lisle, CEO of InnVision Shelter Network, shares about the reality of homelessness on the Peninsula and in Silicon Valley, and illustrates IVSN\'s \"Beyond the Bed\" services that work to permanently end homelessness.\r\n\r\n[embed]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=x4MgQ9FRoFU[/embed]\r\n\r\n<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-1003 aligncenter\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/DSC_6967-320x320.jpg\" alt=\"DSC_6967\" width=\"320\" height=\"320\" />\r\n<h2>Congresswoman Jackie Speier</h2>\r\nCongresswoman Jackie Speier inspires event guests to support IVSN\'s programs to end homelessness with a strong call-to-action. Heed her call and <a title=\"Donate\" href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/donate/\" target=\"_blank\">make a donation today</a>. \"You can change lives.\"\r\n\r\n[embed]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OwRnLxJQRkc[/embed]\r\n\r\n<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-1002 aligncenter\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/DSC_6917_2-320x280.jpg\" alt=\"DSC_6917_2\" width=\"320\" height=\"280\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/Speier-You-Can-Change-Lives.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-1004\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/Speier-You-Can-Change-Lives-320x213.jpg\" alt=\"Speier You Can Change Lives\" width=\"320\" height=\"213\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Regis Philbin, Keynote Address</h2>\r\nKeynote speaker Regis Philbin deliveres a charming and heartfelt message of support for the mission of InnVision Shelter Network as only Regis can. He shares (and sings) stories from his past of how a little kindness and mentorship can transform a person’s life.\r\n\r\nCongresswoman Jackie Speier introduces Regis, who takes the stage at minute 2:35.\r\n\r\n[embed]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bzvnn0_QAKY[/embed]\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-1001 aligncenter\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/DSC_6964_2-320x241.jpg\" alt=\"DSC_6964_2\" width=\"320\" height=\"241\" />\r\n<h2><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/DSC_6963.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-998 aligncenter\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/DSC_6963-320x349.jpg\" alt=\"DSC_6963\" width=\"320\" height=\"349\" /></a></h2>\r\n<strong>Thank you to all who attended the 2014 IVSN Benefit Breakfast. To make a difference today, please <a title=\"Donate\" href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/donate/\" target=\"_blank\">Donate Now</a>.</strong>','Benefit Breakfast 2014: Photos and Videos','','publish','closed','open','','benefit-breakfast-2014-photos-and-videos','','','2014-10-27 17:01:57','2014-10-28 00:01:57','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/?p=997',11,'post','',0),(998,12,'2014-10-15 01:07:34','2014-10-15 08:07:34','','DSC_6963','','inherit','closed','open','','dsc_6963','','','2014-10-15 01:07:34','2014-10-15 08:07:34','',997,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/DSC_6963.jpg',0,'attachment'