tachment','image/jpeg',0),(1055,11,'2014-11-14 22:13:26','2014-11-15 06:13:26','','RTEH Hat Cut-Out','','inherit','closed','open','','rteh-hat-cut-out-2','','','2014-11-14 22:13:26','2014-11-15 06:13:26','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/RTEH-Hat-Cut-Out1.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1059,12,'2014-11-17 16:02:00','2014-11-18 00:02:00','','Ride to End Homelessness','','inherit','closed','open','','eric-welsh','','','2014-11-17 16:02:23','2014-11-18 00:02:23','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Eric-Welsh.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1066,11,'2014-11-17 20:51:07','2014-11-18 04:51:07','','DSC_7315','','inherit','closed','open','','dsc_7315','','','2014-11-17 20:51:07','2014-11-18 04:51:07','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/DSC_7315.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1069,12,'2014-11-18 14:04:05','2014-11-18 22:04:05','','The Ride to End Homelessness Flyer','','inherit','closed','open','','the-ride-to-end-homelessness-flyer','','','2014-11-18 14:04:05','2014-11-18 22:04:05','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/The-Ride-to-End-Homelessness-Flyer.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(1071,11,'2014-11-18 18:04:39','2014-11-19 02:04:39','[one_half]\r\n<h2 class=\"p2\"><span class=\"s1\"><b>Study: 1 in 30 U.S. Kids Were Homeless During 2013</b></span></h2>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Study authors say nearly 2.5 million American children experienced homelessness last year.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">The number of homeless children in the United States surged by 8% in 2013 to nearly 2.5 million, according to a new study that attributes the record-breaking figure to a shortage of affordable housing and the lingering effects of a jobless economic recovery.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">The report published Monday by the National Center on Family Homelessness combined the U.S. Department of Education’s existing estimate of homelessness among school-age children, 1.5 million, with independent tallies for younger children not yet at school. The revised total suggests that one in every 30 children in the U.S. experienced homelessness in 2013.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">The study authors attribute the elevated rates of homelessness to a sluggish economic recovery, compounded by a housing market that has priced out unemployed and low income families. California, in particular, was hard hit with 527,000 homeless children, accounting for one-fifth of the national total. </span></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">-Comment by Dan Kedmey, Time.com</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 class=\"p1\"><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Report-on-Child-Homelessness-Nov-2014.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Click here to read the full report.</a>[/one_half][one_half_last]</h4>\r\n<h2 class=\"p1\"><strong>Holiday Appeal: Change the life of a homeless child in our community today! </strong></h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>Give to the IVSN Holiday Appeal. Help us reach our goal of $3,750,000 by December 31, 2014.</h3>\r\n<a href=\"https://14345.thankyou4caring.org/sslpage.aspx?pid=392\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1078\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Donate-Now-button-320x72.png\" alt=\"Donate Now button\" width=\"302\" height=\"68\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Holiday-Appeal-2014.pdf\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1079\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Download-HA-Button-320x72.png\" alt=\"Download HA Button\" width=\"300\" height=\"68\" /></a>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n<h4><a href=\"#appeal\">Appeal from the CEO, Karae Lisle</a></h4>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<h4><a href=\"#tiffany\">Tiffany\'s Story</a></h4>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<h4><a href=\"#more\">More Lives Changed</a></h4>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<h4><a href=\"#about\">About InnVision Shelter Network </a></h4>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1082 size-medium\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/DSC_7321-320x476.jpg\" alt=\"DSC_7321\" width=\"320\" height=\"476\" />\r\n\r\n[/one_half_last]\r\n\r\n[full_width]\r\n\r\n<a name=\"appeal\"></a>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #eb9122;\">Appeal from the CEO, Karae Lisle</span></h2>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">November 2014</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Dear Friend,</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><b>We have a problem.</b> Last night, almost 7,000 men, women, and children in our community were unsheltered – homeless – sleeping in unsafe conditions, doubled up with relatives or friends, on the street, or in places not meant for human habitation. Many are employed and hardworking, but still can’t find affordable housing on modest incomes. They are families struggling financially after an illness. They are veterans trying to return to civilian life. They are us.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><b>But, there is good news. </b>Unlike so many social problems that seem to have no solution, homelessness can be solved in our community with your support. By combining our Beyond the Bed services with temporary housing, we provide intensive, individualized counseling in a safe living environment with the expectation that our clients will succeed in overcoming homelessness.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><b>Our model works.</b> More than 90% of the families, and 70% of the individuals, who graduate from our programs return to permanent housing and self-sufficiency. InnVision Shelter Network clients attain success quickly, graduating to permanent housing in an average of 163 days, compared to a national average of 230 days.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><b>Transformational initiatives like ours require significant resources.</b> With your financial contribution we provide:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li class=\"p3\">Professional case managers, mental health specialists, and advocates to coach and counsel our clients on a 1-on-1 basis</li>\r\n	<li class=\"p3\">Educational life skills classes including job preparation and financial literacy workshops to give our clients the skills to succeed in the long term</li>\r\n	<li class=\"p3\">Housing facilities from Daly City to San Jose operating at capacity to help 1,000 people every day</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Your generous gift is urgently needed to meet our goal of $3,750,000 by December 31, 2014.</b>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Investing in the solution to homelessness has a spectacular return on the health of our community. Please consider creating positive change in the lives of your neighbors by giving to InnVision Shelter Network this holiday season.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Warmest regards,</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-333\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/karae-sig.jpg\" alt=\"karae-sig\" width=\"123\" height=\"61\" /></p><br>\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: left;\">Karae Lisle</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: left;\">CEO</p>\r\n<a name=\"tiffany\"></a>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h2 class=\"p1\"><span style=\"color: #eb9122;\">A life changed: Meet Tiffany\'s Family</span></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1066 size-large\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/DSC_7315-1024x687.jpg\" alt=\"DSC_7315\" width=\"550\" height=\"368\" />\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Tiffany is a U.S. veteran who served in the Air Force. She was raising her three children, Russel, Victoria, and Mary, when she became a victim of domestic violence. She fled with her children and lived with different family members while she struggled to find the stability to get back on track.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Fortunately, the Veteran\'s Administration referred Tiffany to InnVision Shelter Network\'s First Step for Families transitional shelter. \"The name suits the place very well. First Step for Families felt like a home to us,\" Tiffany says. \"We were safe there.\"</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">The family\'s case manager, Andrea, guided Tiffany and her children every step of the way back to self-sufficiency. Tiffany worked tirelessly. She was employed full-time, raising her three children, and constantly applying for housing opportunities. Her kids benefited from attending our Summer Adventure Camp, which provides children with access to field trips and educational STEM programs they may not have otherwise enjoyed.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">With the support of our dedicated staff, the family was able to able to graduate from our program and move into a townhome in Sunnyvale. \"It\'s nice to feel comfortable and grounded again,\" she explains. \"We have a nice landlord, our own rooms, and space,\" Tiffany beamed.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Tiffany has been working at Michael\'s, the craft store, for a year and a half, beginning as a sales associate, moving up to the position of cashier, and then earning a promotion to assistant manager. She also owns a jewelry business, complete with an online shop to showcase her handmade jewelry. She is working to grow her business and eventually become a vendor at craft fairs and festivals.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Tiffany\'s story sheds light on InnVision Shelter Network\'s success in changing lives in our community. Her success story is just one of thousands made possible by our effective model. Over 90% of the families and 70% of the individuals who graduate from our transitional housing programs return to permanent housing and ongoing self-sufficiency.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 class=\"p1\"><strong>Please make a difference this holiday season by making a <a href=\"https://14345.thankyou4caring.org/sslpage.aspx?pid=392\">personal investment</a> to change lives.</strong></h2>\r\n<a name=\"more\"></a>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #eb9122;\">More Lives Changed</span></h2>\r\n<h4>Meet Odie</h4>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1072\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/odie2_website-320x308.jpg\" alt=\"odie2_website\" width=\"304\" height=\"284\" />\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li class=\"p1\">Odie was homeless and had been living on the streets for 10 years. Even with stable employment as a food service worker at Stanford University, low and garnished wages kept him from finding affordable housing.</li>\r\n	<li class=\"p1\">Outreach case manager, Roberto, found Odie on the streets and, over time, convinced him that he could secure housing. With Roberto\'s help, Odie recently moved into transitional housing.</li>\r\n	<li class=\"p1\">Now, Odie participates in life-skills workshops and is moving quickly towards self-sufficiency. He can\'t wait to have a permanent home where his children and grandchildren can visit him.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #751b53;\"><b><i>\"InnVision Shelter Network gives me hope. They help me remain focused and motivate me to reach my goals. For that I am truly grateful.\" - Odie</i></b></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Meet the McEvoy Family</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li class=\"p1\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1073\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/McEvoy_IC-edits-320x209.jpg\" alt=\"McEvoy_IC edits\" width=\"331\" height=\"223\" />Angela and Jose became homeless when Jose\'s hours were drastically cut and Angela went on maternity leave to have their son, Julian.</li>\r\n	<li class=\"p1\">With the help of her case manager, Angela enrolled in De Anza College and is earning a certificate in Medical Billing and Coding. The McEvoy family\'s determination is helping them succeed.</li>\r\n	<li class=\"p1\">The McEvoy\'s graduated from our program and now live in an apartment in Redwood City. Angela works as a Senior Care Provider with Senior Helpers, and Jose has regained his hours as a truck driver.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #751b53;\"><b><i>\"We thank InnVision Shelter Network for giving us the opportunity for a fresh start.\" - Jose</i></b></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h4 class=\"p1\"> Meet Vannessa\'s Family</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li class=\"p1\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1074\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Vanessa_Website.jpg\" alt=\"Vanessa_Website\" width=\"251\" height=\"252\" />Vannessa and her daughter, Athina, became homeless at the end of a tumultuous family break-up; without a second income, Vannessa could no longer afford rent in San Mateo County.</li>\r\n	<li class=\"p1\">As part of our program, Vannessa was required to save 50% of her income. She worked hard at Starbucks and saved nearly $10,000.</li>\r\n	<li class=\"p1\">Vannessa and Athina have now graduated from our program and live in an apartment in San Mateo. Vannessa is working towards earning a degree in Early Childhood Development, with plans to pursue a career in Social Work.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #751b53;\"><b><i>\"You never know what life can bring. InnVision Shelter Network\'s program has made me stay in the present and stay grounded for my daughter.\" - Vannessa</i></b></span></p>\r\n<a name=\"about\"></a>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #eb9122;\">About InnVision Shelter Network</span></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1077\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Holiday-Appeal_online-info-page1-823x1024.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"650\" height=\"808\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><strong>Follow our Progress</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/InnVisionShelterNetwork\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-98 size-full\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/facebook.png\" alt=\"facebook\" width=\"22\" height=\"21\" /></a> <a href=\"http://www.facebook.cominnvisionshelternetwork\">innvisionshelternetwork</a> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/InnVisShelter\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-100 size-full\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/twitter.png\" alt=\"twitter\" width=\"22\" height=\"21\" /></a> <a href=\"http://www.twitter.com/InnVisShelter\">@InnVisShelter</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">[/full_width]</p>','1 in 30 U.S. Kids Were Homeless During 2013. Change the life of a homeless child in our community today; Donate to IVSN’s Holiday Appeal','','publish','closed','open','','holiday-appeal-2014','','','2014-11-20 18:05:45','2014-11-21 02:05:45','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/?p=1071',10,'post','',0),(1072,11,'2014-11-18 16:35:29','2014-11-19 00:35:29','','odie2_website','','inherit','closed','open','','odie2_website','','','2014-11-18 16:35:29','2014-11-19 00:35:29','',1071,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/odie2_website.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1073,11,'2014-11-18 16:40:32','2014-11-19 00:40:32','','McEvoy_IC edits','','inherit','closed','open','','mcevoy_ic-edits','','','2014-11-18 16:40:32','2014-11-19 00:40:32','',1071,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/McEvoy_IC-edits.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1074,11,'2014-11-18 16:45:22','2014-11-19 00:45:22','','Vanessa_Website','','inherit','closed','open','','vanessa_website','','','2014-11-18 16:45:22','2014-11-19 00:45:22','',1071,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Vanessa_Website.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1076,11,'2014-11-18 16:53:52','2014-11-19 00:53:52','','Holiday Appeal_online info page','','inherit','closed','open','','holiday-appeal_online-info-page','','','2014-11-18 16:53:52','2014-11-19 00:53:52','',1071,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Holiday-Appeal_online-info-page.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1077,11,'2014-11-18 17:03:26','2014-11-19 01:03:26','','Holiday Appeal_online info page cropped','','inherit','closed','open','','holiday-appeal_online-info-page-2','','','2014-11-18 17:03:43','2014-11-19 01:03:43','',1071,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Holiday-Appeal_online-info-page1.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1078,11,'2014-11-18 17:42:52','2014-11-19 01:42:52','','Donate Now button',