6,11,'2014-11-18 18:30:36','2014-11-19 02:30:36','','IMG_5207','IVSNers, Eli, Eric, and Dwight ','inherit','closed','open','','img_5207','','','2014-11-18 18:30:53','2014-11-19 02:30:53','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/IMG_5207.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1087,11,'2014-11-18 18:36:01','2014-11-19 02:36:01','<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Thank you for joining us for the 2014 Ride to End Homelessness! Sign up now for 2015!\r\n</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1146 size-large\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/DSC_7637-1024x685.jpg\" alt=\"DSC_7637\" width=\"550\" height=\"367\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"http://14345.thankyou4caring.org/ivsn/ride-to-end-homelessness-2015\"><img class=\"wp-image-1083 size-medium aligncenter\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Join-Us-button-320x72.png\" alt=\"Join Us button\" width=\"320\" height=\"72\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1086\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"320\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1086 size-medium\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/IMG_5207-320x365.jpg\" alt=\"IVSNers, Eli, Eric, and Dwight \" width=\"320\" height=\"365\" /> Left to right: IVSNers, Eli, Eric, and Dwight[/caption]\r\n\r\n<strong>What: </strong>\r\n\r\nBrainchild of IVSN staff members, Eli Latimerlo, Director of Corporate Partnerships, Eric Welsh, Associate Manager of Donor Records, and Dwight Powery, VP of Strategy, Technology, and Compliance, to combine their passion for their work at IVSN with their passion for cycling!\r\n\r\n<strong>On Saturday, 12/13/14 </strong>professional and amateur cyclists joined together for the 1<sup>st</sup> Edition of InnVision Shelter Network’s “Ride to End Homelessness”. This first-ever ride of its kind in the Bay Area is intended to promote awareness of – and solutions for – homelessness. It is a reminder to our community that every night in San Mateo and Santa Clara Counties, 7,000 people are unsheltered.\r\n\r\nInnVision Shelter Network’s “Ride to End Homelessness” is a 55-mile untimed bike ride beginning at InnVision Shelter Network’s Family Crossroads facility for homeless families in Daly City, and ending at Montgomery Street Inn for homeless adults in San Jose. Riders make two rest stops along the way to rest, eat, and engage with supporters.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1124 \" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/IVSN-Ride-Route-Map2-320x253.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"339\" height=\"268\" />Space for the 1<sup>st</sup> Edition was very limited, but the ride will expand in future years. Riders should feel comfortable riding a long distance on all surfaces and conditions; rain or shine.\r\n\r\n<strong>When: </strong>\r\n\r\n9:00am, Saturday, December 13, 2014\r\n\r\n<strong>Where:</strong>\r\n\r\nInnVision Shelter Network’s Family Crossroads, an interim shelter and services for homeless families. Address: <strong>50 Hillcrest Drive, Daly City, CA 94014</strong>\r\n\r\nPark at nearby Daly City BART station, ride over to Start. Transportation for bicycles and riders from San Jose back to BART in Daly City is provided.<img class=\"alignright wp-image-1055\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/RTEH-Hat-Cut-Out1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"164\" height=\"137\" align=\"middle\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Who: </strong>\r\n\r\nIVSN staff, volunteers, friends and supporters from the community.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><em><span class=\"s1\"><i>Riders received a free \"I Ride to End Homelessness\" cycling cap!</i></span></em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>The 2014 Ride is now over. </strong>Use the links below to see complete details about last year\'s ride, and sign up to ride or volunteer in 2015!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"> <a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Ride-to-End-Homelessness-Flyer.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1084\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Complete-ride-Dets-button-320x72.png\" alt=\"Complete ride Dets button\" width=\"150\" height=\"34\" /></a>  <a href=\" http://14345.thankyou4caring.org/ivsn/ride-to-end-homelessness-2015\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1108\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Volunteer-button-320x72.png\" alt=\"Volunteer button\" width=\"150\" height=\"34\" /> </a><a href=\"http://14345.thankyou4caring.org/ivsn/ride-to-end-homelessness-2015\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1083\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Join-Us-button-320x72.png\" alt=\"Join Us button\" width=\"150\" height=\"34\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">Rider Profiles</h2>\r\n<strong><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-1107\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Eli-Riding-320x425.png\" alt=\"Eli Riding\" width=\"320\" height=\"425\" />Name of Rider:</strong>\r\n\r\nEli Latimerlo\r\n\r\n<strong>I am riding to end homelessness because...</strong>\r\n\r\n“Everyday, IVSN is making a profound difference in the lives of a thousand of the most vulnerable citizens of San Mateo and Santa Clara Counties. I’ve experienced it first hand. The work IVSN is doing is disruptive to the patterns of homelessness. It’s a cause that I believe in.”\r\n\r\n<strong>Message to Others:</strong>\r\n\r\nThe Ride to End Homelessness is a bike ride. It is one thing that many of us can do to make a difference in the lives of the very poorest of our neighbors. It needn’t be the cause that drives you to realize your purpose in this life, but it could be. Join us, and make a small step in the direction of your calling.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1116\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"320\"]<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-1116\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Rider-Charlie-320x228.jpg\" alt=\"I found this shelter during a crossing of the United States on bicycle. Protected from the rain, I found solace in rock \'n\' roll! Whatever it takes, right?\" width=\"320\" height=\"228\" /> I found this shelter during a crossing of the United States on bicycle. Protected from the rain, I found solace in rock \'n\' roll! Whatever it takes, right?[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong><span class=\"s1\"><b>Name of the Rider:</b></span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Charlie Walker</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><strong>I am riding to end homelessness because...</strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">I am riding to help those in need of shelter. Nothing in life is more basic than finding a safe haven, protected from the elements, guarded against the unknown, and getting nurtured to carry on.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong><span class=\"s1\"><b>Message to Others:</b></span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Good people need to stick together, at all times! That is what InnVision Shelter Network is all about. Come join us if you can, cheer us on from afar, or just pray for us as we brave the elements. Thank you for your support.</span></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-1126\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/image001-320x240.jpg\" alt=\"image001\" width=\"320\" height=\"240\" />\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><b>Name of Rider:</b></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Eric Welsh</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><b>I am riding to end homelessness because….</b></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">We live in one of the richest areas in the country.  It is a crime that so many people go unhoused each night.  I want to bring this issue to the forefront of the cycling communities minds.     </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><b>Message to others:</b></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">To all my riding brethren out on the road: We are extremely lucky to have the means and opportunity to ride in such an amazing area!  This really is a mecca for cycling.  Sometimes we take this for granted and do not realize so many people here are struggling to feed and shelter themselves.  I hope you can all take a moment and read more about the wonderful work InnVision Shelter Network does to help end this problem!    </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-1130\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Sara-Headley-TIBCO-indiv.-320x339.jpg\" alt=\"Sara Headley - TIBCO indiv.\" width=\"320\" height=\"339\" /></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><strong>Name of Rider:</strong> Sara Headley</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong><span class=\"s1\"><b>I am riding to end homelessness because...</b></span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">I want to increase awareness of the families and individuals in need, especially during the holiday season. Taking the time out of our busy schedules is the least we can do to show our support. As a professional rider, it is refreshing to ride for a cause much bigger than my daily training ride. It adds a special glimmer of hope to my life, but more importantly, to those we are representing on that day. If we can gather others interested in helping IVSN fight homelessness, we have accomplished something very special indeed. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong><span class=\"s1\"><b>Message to Others: </b></span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Bicycles have the magical power to bring people together in fun and fitness. Pictures from the event will show how people joining together in a healthy activity can create a flow of ideas and determination to fight homelessness in the Bay Area. No matter how young or old, rich or poor, one can always find joy on 2 wheels!</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><b><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-1136\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/IMG_5560-320x426.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_5560\" width=\"320\" height=\"426\" /></b></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><b>Name of Rider:</b></span><span class=\"s2\"><b> </b>Dwight Powery</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p3\"><span class=\"s3\"><b>I am riding to end homelessness because….</b></span><span class=\"s1\"><b> </b>I want to bring awareness to the homelessness situation in one of the richest areas in the country.  Many of us are not aware that over 7,000 people </span>(including children) live in homelessness every night and we have a responsibility to fight for what is a basic human right.  IVSN is at the forefront of not only bringing that awareness, but also bringing a solution to those in need.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p3\"><span class=\"s3\"><b>Message to others:</b></span><span class=\"s1\"> Homelessness takes on many forms within our community – from those that we see to those that we don’t see.  When you cycle, you pass a little slower by the pockets that you miss when you drive. Will you join InnVision Shelter Network in bringing the voice to those that we don’t see?</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><em>And many more... Thank you to all 2014 riders!\r\n</em></p>','Ride to End Homelessness','','private','closed','closed','','ride-to-end-homelessness-2014','','','2015-10-18 22:02:38','2015-10-19 05:02:38','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/?post_type=event&#038;p=1087',4,'event','',0),(1105,11,'2014-11-20 21:37:01','2014-11-21 05:37:01','','IVSN\'s Ride To End Homelessness Press Release','','inherit','closed','open','','ivsns-ride-to-end-homelessness-press-release','','','2014-11-20 21:37:01','2014-11-21 05:37:01','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/IVSNs-Ride-To-End-Homelessness-Press-Release.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(1107,11,'2014-11-20 21:41:09','2014-11-21 05:41:09','','Eli Riding','','inherit','closed','open','','eli-riding','','','2014-11-20 21:41:09','2014-11-21 05:41:09',