-content/uploads/2014/11/IMG_5560.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1142,12,'2014-12-29 18:50:55','2014-12-30 02:50:55','<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">Meet the Cervantes Family</h1>\r\n[embed]http://youtu.be/tfLnf2uIIhE[/embed]\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">For more stories of success, read our <a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/holiday-appeal-2014/\">Holiday Appeal</a>.</h1>\r\n<a href=\"https://14345.thankyou4caring.org/sslpage.aspx?pid=392\"><img class=\"wp-image-452 size-full aligncenter\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/donate_button.png\" alt=\"donate_button\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a>','Meet the Cervantes Family','','publish','closed','open','','cervantes-family','','','2014-12-29 18:50:55','2014-12-30 02:50:55','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=1142',16,'page','',0),(1146,12,'2015-01-06 16:22:11','2015-01-07 00:22:11','','DSC_7637','','inherit','closed','open','','dsc_7637','','','2015-01-06 16:22:11','2015-01-07 00:22:11','',1087,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/DSC_7637.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1149,12,'2015-01-08 12:48:26','2015-01-08 20:48:26','','Interns2014','','inherit','closed','open','','interns2014','','','2015-01-08 12:48:26','2015-01-08 20:48:26','',632,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/Interns2014.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1153,12,'2015-01-13 11:44:29','2015-01-13 19:44:29','<h1>Manager, Corporate Partnership</h1>\r\n<strong>JOB DESCRIPTION</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>TITLE:</strong><strong>                   Manager, Corporate Partnership Program </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>SUPERVISOR:     Director, Corporate Development</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>STATUS:              Full Time, Non-Exempt</strong>\r\n\r\nInnVision Shelter Network  is a social enterprise committed to providing housing and support services that create opportunities for homeless families and individuals to re-establish their self-sufficiency and find a rapid return to housing. Since 1987, our methodology for success has delivered consistent results for homeless families and individuals. Over 90 percent of families and 70 percent of individuals graduating from IVSN interim housing programs return to permanent housing.  InnVision Shelter Network is an innovative, cutting-edge non-profit organization embodies the entrepreneurial energy of an emerging growth company. The executive team is committed to employee satisfaction and the ongoing development of a work culture and environment that increases and maintains morale, productivity, engagement, and the attraction and retention of superior people.\r\n\r\n<strong>PRIMARY DUTIES</strong>\r\n\r\nInnVision Shelter Network is looking for a driven, engaged, and flexible self-starter. This individual will help both raise money for, and awareness of, InnVision Shelter Network within the Silicon Valley and San Francisco Peninsula Communities. This position reports to the Director of Corporate Partnership, and is responsible for their own fund-raising goal (donor portfolio) and for supporting all strategy and related activities for this program. We are looking for someone who thrives in a fast-paced environment, enjoys new challenges, and is committed to learning and growing. The annual fund-raising goal for this role is $500K.\r\n\r\nThe person in this role is responsible to develop new, and to deepen existing, Corporate and business relationships that result in financial donations to the organization’s general operating fund.\r\n\r\nPrimary activities will include, but are not limited to: communications, project management, donor/customer acquisition and retention, donor data management and reporting, and administrative duties.\r\n\r\n<strong>Additional Responsibilities</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><b><strong>Communications</strong></b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nCompose and edit internal and external correspondence, create donor profile briefs and conduct research for donor prospects and existing donors; draft business plans, preparation of letters, emails, proposals and reports. Assist with correspondence and periodic mailings and invitations.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><b><strong>Project Management</strong></b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHelp to organize and manage successful completion of projects. Examples include but are not limited to: special events, mass mailings, research projects, forecasting and strategic plan creation, and organizing Quarterly Business Reviews (QBRs).\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><b><strong>Donor/Customer Acquisition &amp; Retention</strong></b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAbility to use available database, the internet, and third party tools and methods to find more information about current donors, and to create pipeline lists of prospective donors. To learn more about current trends in corporate and business donor behavior and how those trends can assist IVSN in raising more money from that sector.\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Research, initiate, and develop new prospects and opportunities</li>\r\n	<li>Secure new revenue (investment in IVSN programs) and solicit sponsorships (special events)</li>\r\n	<li>Retain and deepen relationships with existing contributors year/year</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><b><strong>Data Management and Reporting</strong></b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nBecome familiar with, and responsible for, querying IVSN donor database to extract meaningful reports to track fund-raising progress. Learn to create targeted lists of donors for mailings and invitations to events.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><b><strong>Administrative Activities</strong></b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSchedule appointments, help prepare for site/tour visits with relevant materials for corporate and business donors and donor prospects. Support the Corporate Partnership team and the Development Team in the planning and execution of events. Specific duties may include creating invitation lists and managing event follow-up.\r\n\r\n<strong>Qualifications<em>:</em></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Excellent organization and written communication skills</li>\r\n	<li>Excellent verbal (in-person and telephone-based) skills needed to successfully communicate IVSN mission and value proposition</li>\r\n	<li>Exceptional persistence, attention to detail and follow-through</li>\r\n	<li>Strong analytical skills and research abilities</li>\r\n	<li>Performance-driven attitude, with high standards and a proven ability to cultivate and close</li>\r\n	<li>Self-starter with positive energy, emotional resilience and ability to produce consistent results</li>\r\n	<li>Proven track record in exceeding revenue goals, and in delighting clients/customers</li>\r\n	<li>Technically skilled with Microsoft Office suite and CRM software (Raisers Edge 7 or Salesforce )</li>\r\n	<li>”Can-do”, “roll-up-your-sleeves”, creative approach to closing new business and delivering on forecast</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Education and Experience</strong>:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Bachelor’s degree strongly preferred</li>\r\n	<li>Experience in both customer retention and in closing new business and/or creating new partnerships in the private and/or non-profit sectors</li>\r\n	<li>2+ years in business development, direct fundraising or sales/relationship management experience</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b><strong>The ideal candidate will be:</strong></b>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>An InnVision Shelter Network ambassador who embodies the organization’s core mission and values</li>\r\n	<li>Donor/customer focused; passionate and honest</li>\r\n	<li>Deadline-oriented and skilled at managing to a revenue forecast</li>\r\n	<li>Able to take initiative, work independently, and also perform as a team player</li>\r\n	<li>Flexible – ability to work nights and weekends as required for relationship-building (Note: there is no travel required outside of the Bay Area)</li>\r\n	<li>An appetite to take on new roles and responsibilities as opportunities arise</li>\r\n	<li>Good judgment and the ability to move forward in ambiguous situations</li>\r\n	<li>Respect for individuals’ diverse experiences and the ability to work effectively with people from a variety of backgrounds</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Application process:</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease email: <a href=\"mailto:sbennett@ivsn.org\">sbennett@ivsn.org</a> with a custom cover letter telling us about yourself, your salary requirements or history, and your resume, with \"Manager, Corporate Partnership Program @ InnVision Shelter Network\" in the subject line. No phone calls, please.','Manager, Corporate Partnership','','publish','closed','open','','manager-corporate-partnership','','','2015-01-13 11:44:29','2015-01-13 19:44:29','',251,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=1153',11,'page','',0),(1160,12,'2015-01-28 13:19:52','0000-00-00 00:00:00','&nbsp;\n<blockquote>January 13, 2015\n\nTo Whom It May Concern:\n\nMy name is Marvin Bryant. I am a proud U.S. Army Veteran and an InnVision Shelter Network client. I feel compelled to write this letter to simply express my immense gratitude and thanks for all the help and care that IVSN freely provided to me during a very challenging and exciting time in my life.\n\nAfter completing a six month chemical dependency treatment program and changing my homelessness status, I recently set out to begin my new lease on life as an independent and sober individual. InnVision Shelter Network was there for me and allowed me to benefit from some of the great programs you offer. A company is only as good as their employees, and the representative that stands-out as most exemplary of IVSN’s noble mission would be Dawn Hollie<strong>.</strong> As my Case manager, she treated me with sincere care and respect and as the consummate professional she is, she always made sure I received what I needed.  She is clearly indispensable and a huge asset to your organization.\n\nTo sum it all up, I had a very positive experience with InnVision Shelter Network and would definitely encourage anybody to seek your assistance. You have all demonstrated a strong commitment to excellence and towards our great nation’s Veterans. Thank you again.\n\nSincerely,\n\nMarvin L. Bryant</blockquote>','U.S. Veteran Marvin Shares his Gratitude','','draft','closed','open','','','','','2015-01-28 13:19:52','2015-01-28 21:19:52','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=1160',10,'page','',0),(1161,12,'2015-01-28 13:15:56','2015-01-28 21:15:56','','Marvin veteran playing guitar','','inherit','closed','open','','marvin-veteran-playing-guitar','','','2015-01-28 13:15:56','2015-01-28 21:15:56','',1160,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Marvin-veteran-playing-guitar.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1162,12,'2015-01-28 14:32:38','2015-01-28 22:32:38','<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1161 size-large\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Marvin-veteran-playing-guitar-1024x937.jpg\" alt=\"Marvin veteran playing guitar\" width=\"550\" height=\"503\" />\r\n<blockquote>January 13, 2015\r\n\r\nTo Whom It May Concern:\r\n\r\nMy name is Marvin. I am a proud U.S. Army Veteran and an InnVision Shelter Network client. I feel compelled to write this letter to simply express my immense gratitude and thanks for all the help and care that IVSN freely provided to me during a very challenging and exciting time in my life.\r\n\r\nAfter completing a six month chemical dependency treatment program and changing my homelessness status, I recently set out to begin my new lease on life as an independent and sober individual. InnVision Shelter Network was there for me and allowed me to benefit from some of the great programs you offer. A company is only as good as their employees, and the representative that stands-out as most exemplary of IVSN’s noble mission would be Dawn Holley<strong>.</strong> As my Case manager, she treated me with sincere care and respect and as the consummate professional she is, she always made sure I received what I needed.  She is clearly indispensable and a huge asset to your organization.\r\n\r\nTo sum it all up, I had a very positive experience with InnVision Shelter Network and would definitely encourage anybody to seek your assistance. You have all demonstrated a strong commitment to excellence and towards our great nation’s Veterans. Thank you again.\r\n\r\nSincerely,\r\n\r\nMarvin</blockquote>\r\n<a href=\"https://14345.thankyou4caring.org/sslpage.aspx?pid=392\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-451 size-full\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/donate_button_purple.png\" alt=\"donate_button_purple\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.twitter.com/InnVisShelter\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-427 size-full\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/twitter_button.png\" alt=\"twitter_button\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/InnVisionShelterNetwork\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-425 size-full\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/facebook_button.png\" alt=\"facebook_button\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a>','U.S. Veteran Shares his Gratitude','','publish','closed','open','','marvin','','','2015-02-18 14:26:06','2015-02-18 22:26:06','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/?p=1162',8,'post','',0),(1165,12,'2015-02-04 09:35:25','2015-02-04 17:35:25','','Meal Provider Volunteer Manual','','inherit','closed','open','','meal-provider-volunteer-manual-020415','','','2015-02-04 09:36:48','2015-02-04 17:36:48','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/Meal-Provider-Volunteer-Manual-020415.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(1167,12,'2015-02-05 10:59:52','2015-02-05 18:59:52','<h1>Operations Assistant</h1>\r\n<section>InnVision Shelter Network (IVSN) is one of the largest and most effective providers of shelter/housing and supportive services across Silicon Valley and the San Francisco Peninsula. IVSN operates over 18 major sites from San Jose to Daly City, providing emergency, transitional, and permanent supportive housing, along with a breadth of supportive resources to help clients secure a place to call home. The organization serves thousands of homeless clients annually through its \"Beyond the Bed\" service model -- a proven methodology that has historically delivered a 90% success rate in returning program graduates to permanent housing and self-sufficiency.</section><section></section><section>Title: Operations Assistant</section><section id=\"postingbody\">Supervisor: Senior Operations Manager\r\nLocation: Administration\r\nHours: 8:30 AM-5:30 PM, Monday -- Friday</section><section></section><section><strong> Qualifications</strong>:</section><section>Minimum two years of experience in office/administrative work environment.</section><section>Ability to relate to a variety of people (clients, staff, donors, volunteer &amp; Board of Directors).</section><section>Well-organized, Proficient in Microsoft Office, Spanish speaking preferred.</section><section></section><section><strong>Office Administration Responsibilities:</strong>\r\n1. Act as the first point of contact for the Administrative site: Manage the front desk, meet and greet visitors, answer incoming calls and transfer them appropriately.\r\n2. Greet visitors and respond to initial requests for assistance.\r\n3. Answer incoming calls and deliver messages for both clients and staff.\r\n4. Transfer potential clients to the appropriate referral agency (north and south counties).\r\n5. Maintain and update office calendars through extensive Outlook use\r\n6. Provide administrative support such as copying, faxing, assembly as needed for the Administrative Office.\r\n7. Maintain conference room calendars and ensure staff keeps rooms tidy\r\n8. Admin site liaison for maintenance tickets via Salesforce\r\n9. Keep gift card inventory and track outgoing expenditures\r\n10. Keep accurate records of deposits and withdrawals in savings program. Keep forms in logbook up-to-date.\r\n11. Process all correspondence and distribute mail within the office.\r\n12. Provide administrative support to other programs aids and shelter workers.\r\n13. Provides callers with information such as company address, fax and phone number, directions to various locations, company website and other related information.\r\n14. Assists in the ordering, receiving, stocking and distribution of office supplies.\r\n15. Assists with other related clerical duties such as photocopying, faxing, filing and collating and maintaining printers, copiers and postage machine. Understand admin fire alarm, security and thermostat. Call for repair and issues.\r\n16. Keep registrations database up-to-date.\r\n17. Assist w/event planning In-Kind Responsibilities:\r\n1. Keep accurate records of donated items: monetary and in-kind.\r\n2. Receives and forwards donations of products and services to reduce IVSN expenses and enhance the services offered by the organization.\r\n3. Check in-kind donation e-mail and phone line.\r\n4. Field calls regarding donations to appropriate locations and determine if there is a need.\r\n5. Schedule donation pick-ups for our maintenance team\r\n6. Stay current on the donation needs of the sites\r\n7. Assist w/Parka pick-ups at Administrative building as needed.</section><section></section><section>Application Process:\r\nTo apply, please respond to this post with your resume and brief cover letter including your salary requirements with \"Operations Assistant\" in the subject line of the e-mail. Please send your resume and cover letter as attachments, do not paste them into the body of your email. PDF or Word preferred. Email: jobs@ivsn.orgThank you in advance to all applicants for your interest, time, and effort.\r\n\r\nNO PHONE CALLS PLEASE.\r\n\r\nInnVision Shelter Network is an Equal Opportunity Employer (EOE). Applicants are considered for employment without regard to age, race, color, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, gender identity and gender expression, disability or veteran status.\r\n\r\n</section>&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Operations Assistant','','publish','closed','open','','operations-assistant','','','2015-02-05 11:12:48','2015-02-05 19:12:48','',251,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=1167',9,'page','',0),(1171,12,'2015-02-05 11:17:02','2015-02-05 19:17:02','<h1 id=\"postingbody\">Senior Grant Writer</h1>\r\n<section>SUPERVISOR: Sr. Director, Grants, Contracts, &amp; Donor Database</section><section>\r\nSTATUS: Full-time, Exempt\r\n\r\nInnVision Shelter Network (IVSN) is a social enterprise committed to providing interim housing (shelter) and support services that create opportunities for homeless families and individuals to re-establish self-sufficiency and to return to permanent homes. Since 1987, our methodology for success has delivered consistent results for homeless families and individuals. Over 90 percent of transitional family graduates return to permanent housing.\r\n\r\nIVSN is an innovative, cutting-edge, non-profit organization which embodies the entrepreneurial energy of an emerging growth company. The executive team is committed to employee satisfaction and the on-going development of a work culture and environment that increases and maintains morale, productivity, engagement, and the attraction and retention of superior people.\r\n\r\nPRIMARY DUTIES\r\nThe successful Sr. Grant Writer is a motivated, positive, team-oriented individual responsible for leading all IVSN grant and contract applications and submissions. The Sr. Grant Writer works closely with the Development, Finance, Program, and Compliance Teams to pursue and achieve the fundraising goals of IVSN\'s operating and strategic plans. This is a full-time, exempt position; some evenings and weekends required. Specific duties include:\r\n• Identify, cultivate, secure, and renew public and private grant and contract funding streams\r\n• Review all public and private RFA and RFP solicitations and recommend application strategies and approaches\r\n• Attend public and private RFA and RFP information sessions\r\n• Build and maintain expert knowledge of IVSN programs and research economic and labor market indicators and policies/theories concerning homelessness and homeless service providers to prepare accurate, comprehensive, and persuasive funding requests and reports\r\n• Lead writing, preparation, and submission of all public and private Letters of Intent and proposals, including drafting creative, engaging cases for support incorporating relevant, current research for organization operating funds and specific programs and projects\r\n• Facilitate cross-functional communication and collaboration with Program and Compliance Teams to develop specific, relevant, achievable goals and objectives for each funding prospect\r\n• Coordinate with Finance Team to present accurate budgets\r\n• Assemble and submit high-quality grant and contract proposals\r\n• Maintain accurate and complete grant records in Raiser\'s Edge, and in electronic and paper formats\r\n• Assist with public and private grant and contract updates and reporting\r\n• Maintain grant and contract submissions calendar and provide regular updates of grant activity and deadlines\r\n• Organize and facilitate weekly Grants Team meeting with cross-functional organization representation\r\n• Provide regular updates of grant and contract activity, deadlines, and awards/declines\r\n• Participate in strategic planning, development team, and quarterly business review meetings\r\n• Co-supervise Associate Grant Writer\r\n\r\nQUALIFICATIONS\r\n• BA degree\r\n• Experience writing and editing grant and contract Letters of Intent and proposals\r\n• Exceptional organizational, analytical, critical-thinking, and prioritization skills\r\n• Excellent, proactive communication skills\r\n• Performance-driven attitude, with high standards and a proven ability to achieve established goals and milestones\r\n• Proven ability work independently with multiple deadlines in fast-paced environment\r\n• Raiser\'s Edge experience preferred\r\n• English fluency required\r\n• Strong technical skill with Microsoft Office suite\r\n• Reliable transportation and access to personal vehicle required\r\n• Commitment to IVSN mission and values\r\n\r\n\r\nApplication Process:\r\nTo apply, please respond to this post with your resume and brief cover letter including your salary requirements with \"Senior Grant Writer\" in the subject line of the e-mail. Please send your resume and cover letter as attachments, do not paste them into the body of your email. PDF or Word preferred. Email: jobs@ivsn.org\r\n\r\nThank you in advance to all applicants for your interest, time, and effort.\r\n\r\nNO PHONE CALLS PLEASE.\r\n\r\nInnVision Shelter Network is an Equal Opportunity Employer (EOE). Applicants are considered for employment without regard to age, race, color, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, gender identity and gender expression, disability or veteran status.</section>&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Senior Grant Writer','','publish','closed','open','','senior-grant-writer','','','2015-02-05 11:17:02','2015-02-05 19:17:02','',251,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=1171',8,'page','',0),(1172,12,'2015-02-05 11:21:44','2015-02-05 19:21:44','<h1 id=\"postingbody\">Associate Grant Writer</h1>\r\n<section>SUPERVISOR: Sr. Director, Grants, Contracts, &amp; Donor Database AND Sr. Grant Writer</section><section>\r\nSTATUS: Full-time, Exempt\r\n\r\nInnVision Shelter Network (IVSN) is a social enterprise committed to providing interim housing (shelter) and support services that create opportunities for homeless families and individuals to re-establish self-sufficiency and to return to permanent homes. Since 1987, our methodology for success has delivered consistent results for homeless families and individuals. Over 90 percent of transitional family graduates return to permanent housing.\r\n\r\nIVSN is an innovative, cutting-edge, non-profit organization which embodies the entrepreneurial energy of an emerging growth company. The executive team is committed to employee satisfaction and the on-going development of a work culture and environment that increases and maintains morale, productivity, engagement, and the attraction and retention of superior people.\r\n\r\nPRIMARY DUTIES\r\nThe successful Associate Grant Writer is a motivated, positive, team-oriented individual. Under the direction of the Sr. Director, Grants, Contracts, &amp; Donor Database AND Senior Grant Writer, the Associate Grant Writer writes significant portions of IVSN\'s public and private grant and contract Letter of Inquiry, proposals, and reports. The person in the role works closely with the Development Team to pursue and achieve the fundraising goals of IVSN\'s operating and strategic plans. This is a full-time, exempt position; some evenings and weekends required. Specific duties include:\r\n• Grant Writing &amp; Reporting\r\no Develop, prepare, and edit grant proposals and reports for foundations, corporations, and government funders\r\no Develop expert knowledge of IVSN programs and service to prepare accurate, comprehensive, and persuasive funding requests and reports\r\no Collaborate with staff across the organization to obtain data, information, and materials for proposals and attachments\r\no Prepare multiple, simultaneous, high-quality proposals and reports for on-time submission under tight and shifting deadlines\r\n• Grants Management\r\no Maintain Raiser\'s Edge calendar of public and private grant proposals and reports to ensure on-time submission of all proposals and reports\r\no Work with Finance, Program, and Compliance Departments to ensure organization\'s accountability to all funders\r\no Participate in organizing and facilitating weekly Grants Team meeting with representation from all organization departments\r\n• Research\r\no Identify, research, and evaluate funding requirements for new, potential public and private funding sources and opportunities\r\no Attend bidders\' conferences and funder information sessions\r\no Conduct research to develop and maintain knowledge of and expertise in policies and theories concerning homelessness and homeless service providers\r\no Conduct research to provide supporting information for grant proposals, including labor market and economic indicators\r\n• Donor Database &amp; Records\r\no Maintain accurate and complete grant records in Raiser\'s Edge, and in electronic and paper records\r\n\r\nQUALIFICATIONS\r\n• BA degree\r\n• Experience writing engaging proposals\r\n• Exceptional organizational, analytical, critical-thinking, and prioritization skills\r\n• Excellent, proactive communication skills\r\n• Performance-driven attitude, with high standards and a proven ability to achieve established goals and milestones\r\n• Strong technical skill with Microsoft Office suite\r\n• Reliable transportation and access to personal vehicle required\r\n• Commitment to IVSN mission and values\r\n• Excellent grant writing skills with ability to write clear and concise proposals and reports\r\n• Proven ability to balance and manage multiple and shifting deadlines and projects\r\n• Demonstrated ability to exercise sound judgment, and to analyze and resolve problems\r\n• Attention to detail and superb organizational skills, with consistent ability to follow-through\r\n• Highly-motivated self-starter with demonstrated ability to work independently and efficiently, learn quickly, and easily establish expertise in subject area and internal processes\r\n• Strong interpersonal skills, with ability to communicate professionally and collaborate effectively with a wide variety of individuals within and outside the organization, including staff, funders, volunteers, and the general public\r\n• Strong computer skills and database management experience including MS Office\r\n• Raiser\'s Edge experience preferred\r\n• Reliable transportation required\r\n\r\nApplication Process:\r\nTo apply, please respond to this post with your resume and brief cover letter including your salary requirements with \"Associate Grant Writer\" in the subject line of the e-mail. Please send your resume and cover letter as attachments, do not paste them into the body of your email. PDF or Word preferred.\r\n\r\nThank you in advance to all applicants for your interest, time, and effort.\r\n\r\nNO PHONE CALLS PLEASE.\r\n\r\nInnVision Shelter Network is an Equal Opportunity Employer (EOE). Applicants are considered for employment without regard to age, race, color, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, gender identity and gender expression, disability or veteran status.</section>&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Associate Grant Writer','','publish','closed','open','','associate-grant-writer','','','2015-02-05 11:21:44','2015-02-05 19:21:44','',251,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=1172',7,'page','',0),(1176,12,'2015-02-05 13:05:06','2015-02-05 21:05:06','','The Villa Donation Wish List 2015','','inherit','closed','open','','the-villa-donation-wish-list-2015','','','2015-02-05 13:05:06','2015-02-05 21:05:06','',210,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/The-Villa-Donation-Wish-List-2015.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(1177,12,'2015-02-05 13:05:08','2015-02-05 21:05:08','','CSI Donation Wish List 2015','','inherit','closed','open','','csi-donation-wish-list-2015','','','2015-02-05 13:05:08','2015-02-05 21:05:08','',210,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/CSI-Donation-Wish-List-2015.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(1178,12,'2015-02-05 13:05:10','2015-02-05 21:05:10','','Donation Wish List 1-15-15','','inherit','closed','open','','donation-wish-list-1-15-15','','','2015-02-05 13:05:10','2015-02-05 21:05:10','',210,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Donation-Wish-List-1-15-15.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(1179,12,'2015-02-05 13:05:12','2015-02-05 21:05:12','','First Step for Families Donation Wish List 2015','','inherit','closed','open','','first-step-for-fami