a leading provider of shelter and supportive services to assist homeless families and individuals in San Mateo and Santa Clara counties – announced today that Bruce Ives has been selected as Chief Executive Officer of the organization, effective March 30.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\">Mr. Ives is an accomplished executive with extensive management and leadership experience gained during 19 years at Hewlett-Packard where he held diverse positions of increasing management responsibility overseeing large teams and budgets. While at Hewlett-Packard, Mr. Ives also founded and led the legal team’s pro bono program, helping countless tenants, veterans, and women facing domestic violence, as well as others who need but can’t afford legal services. Under Mr. Ives’ guidance, the effort has grown to over 600 volunteers worldwide.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\">“We conducted an extensive search for a CEO with a successful track record in leading teams, strong strategic capability and fund raising skills, and who is a passionate advocate for people in need,” said Rod Ferguson, Chair of the InnVision Shelter Network Board of Directors. “Bruce’s lifetime commitment to community service and extensive business leadership experience make him the ideal person to manage this vital community organization.”</p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\">When asked what attracted him to the leadership role at InnVision Shelter Network, Mr. Ives said, “InnVision Shelter Network has a highly respected team with a proven track record for getting results. For decades, they have successfully provided the resources needed to help families and individuals break the cycle of homelessness. I am honored to be chosen to lead an organization where I can put my community values and business skills to best use.”</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Mr. Ives’ commitment to public service began with his first job out of college at an inner-city school district. After law school, he joined the Los Angeles Public Defender’s office.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">He went on to be the District Director for Congresswoman Anna Eshoo in San Mateo and Santa Clara counties. A resident of Menlo Park, he was an elected Trustee of the Menlo Park School District and currently serves on the Board of Directors of Public Advocates, a public interest law firm that works on issues of housing and education equity. He also serves as Treasurer for Congregation Beth Am in Los Altos Hills.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Mr. Ives earned a Bachelor of Arts degree from Harvard University, and a Juris Doctor degree from the University of California, Berkeley.</p>','Bruce Ives Named Chief Executive Officer at InnVision Shelter Network','','publish','closed','open','','bruce-ives-named-chief-executive-officer-at-innvision-shelter-network','','','2015-07-28 21:59:20','2015-07-29 04:59:20','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/?p=1212',7,'post','',0),(1221,11,'2015-02-26 12:17:34','2015-02-26 20:17:34','','Bruce Ives _Page_1','','inherit','closed','open','','bruce-ives-_page_1','','','2015-02-26 12:17:34','2015-02-26 20:17:34','',240,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Bruce-Ives-_Page_1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1235,11,'2015-03-18 17:10:15','2015-03-19 00:10:15','','How-to-Manage-a-Drive-for-IVSN2015','','inherit','closed','open','','how-to-manage-a-drive-for-ivsn2015','','','2015-03-18 17:10:15','2015-03-19 00:10:15','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/How-to-Manage-a-Drive-for-IVSN2015.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(1236,15,'2015-03-19 15:03:19','2015-03-19 22:03:19','','Data Quality and Training Intern POST','','inherit','closed','open','','data-quality-and-training-intern-post','','','2015-03-19 15:03:19','2015-03-19 22:03:19','',632,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/Data-Quality-and-Training-Intern-POST.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(1239,18,'2015-04-09 09:45:28','2015-04-09 16:45:28','On May 5, 2015, the Silicon Valley Community Foundation will host Silicon Valley Gives, a 24-hour day of online giving for our community. <a title=\"SVGives2015\" href=\"http://svgives.razoo.com/story/Ivsn\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Make an online gift</strong></a> on Tuesday, May 5th! Your donation could qualify for matching dollars and cash prizes that will give InnVision Shelter Network much-needed funding support and visibility for our successful programs.\r\n<h5>Take a look at why our staff, volunteers, and donors give to end homelessness!</h5>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n[one_half]\r\n<div style=\"width: 115%; margin-left: -2%;\">[new_royalslider id=\"2\"]</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><a href=\"http://svgives.razoo.com/story/Ivsn\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1317\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/SVGives-logo-lrg-320x246.jpg\" alt=\"SVGives logo lrg\" width=\"284\" height=\"218\" /></a></div>\r\n[/one_half][one_half_last]\r\n<div id=\"razoo_donation_widget\" style=\"padding-left: 12%;\"><a href=\"http://svgives.razoo.com/\">Donate online</a> to <a href=\"http://svgives.razoo.com/story/Ivsn\">InnVision Shelter Network</a> at Razoo</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<script type=\"text/javascript\">// <![CDATA[\r\nvar r_params = {\"title\":\"InnVision Shelter Network\",\"short_description\":\"Give to end homelessness.\",\"long_description\":\"InnVision Shelter Network helps homeless families and individuals return to self-sufficiency and permanent housing. Last night, 7,000 men, women and children in our community were unsheltered and homeless.  But, there is good news. Unlike so many social problems that seem to have no solution, homelessness can be solved in our community with your support Our model works. More than 90% of the families, and 82% of the individuals, who graduate from our programs return to permanent housing and self-sufficiency. And they do it quickly, in an average of 163 days, compared to a national average of 230 days.  Please make a gift and join this community-wide effort to end homelessness. Thank you for partn