fe-Barrett-USE.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1344,18,'2015-04-13 10:58:47','2015-04-13 17:58:47','','DianeOSC','','inherit','closed','open','','dianeosc','','','2015-04-13 10:58:47','2015-04-13 17:58:47','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/DianeOSC.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1349,11,'2015-04-28 08:02:10','2015-04-28 15:02:10','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Neighborhood Builders grant supports innovative and effective programming to help end homelessness for families and individuals in Santa Clara and San Mateo Counties</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>MENLO PARK, CA</strong> –InnVision Shelter Network (IVSN)– a leading provider of shelter and supportive services to homeless families and individuals in San Mateo and Santa Clara counties – announced today that Bank of America has awarded the organization a Neighborhood Builders® grant.</p>\r\nInnVision Shelter Network has received a grant for $200,000 in unrestricted funding for its programs and for leadership training as a part of the Bank of America Neighborhood Builder Program, which is now in its 10th year.\r\n\r\n“We started Neighborhood Builders to promote the leadership potential and the operational capacity of high-impact nonprofits like InnVision Shelter Network, empowering them to meet the changing needs in their community,” said Raquel Gonzàlez, Silicon Valley Market President at Bank of America. “We are proud to make this two-year investment in the innovative and successful work that IVSN is doing to help end homelessness in San Mateo and Santa Clara Counties.”\r\n\r\nInnVision Shelter Network will use the funding to support its “Skills to Succeed” financial literacy and job preparedness educational programs. This program provides critical life skills training for clients which supports a rapid return to long-term housing and self-sufficiency. In total, 1000 people per night are sheltered in IVSN facilities-based programs. Many more are served through non-site based programs and a significant number of people assisted through IVSN program are homeless Veterans.\r\n\r\n“We are honored to receive the generous Neighborhood Builders grant from Bank of America which recognizes high-performing organizations making significant impacts in their communities,” said Bruce Ives, CEO, InnVision Shelter Network. He added, “Our financial literacy and job preparedness workshops are highly effective for our clients. By the time they graduate from our programs, our clients are much better prepared to manage their income and personal debt. They’ve also learned the power of establishing savings. These abilities dramatically increase their likelihood of remaining self-sufficient and retaining their housing.”','InnVision Shelter Network Receives Grant and Executive Training from Bank Of America','','publish','closed','open','','innvision-shelter-network-receives-grant-and-executive-training-from-bank-of-america-2','','','2015-05-06 15:03:39','2015-05-06 22:03:39','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/?p=1349',6,'post','',0),(1351,11,'2015-04-28 08:07:23','2015-04-28 15:07:23','','Press_Release BofA IVSN Donation','','inherit','closed','open','','press_release-bofa-ivsn-donation','','','2015-04-28 08:07:23','2015-04-28 15:07:23','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Press_Release-BofA-IVSN-Donation-.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(1352,11,'2015-04-28 08:07:36','2015-04-28 15:07:36','','Press_Release BofA IVSN Donation','','inherit','closed','open','','press_release-bofa-ivsn-donation-2','','','2015-04-28 08:07:36','2015-04-28 15:07:36','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Press_Release-BofA-IVSN-Donation-1.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(1355,12,'2015-04-29 17:12:58','2015-04-30 00:12:58','','FullSizeRender','','inherit','closed','open','','fullsizerender-2','','','2015-04-29 17:12:58','2015-04-30 00:12:58','',240,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/FullSizeRender.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1359,18,'2015-05-04 19:05:48','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/veteran-dad.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1361\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/veteran-dad-320x479.jpg\" alt=\"veteran dad\" width=\"234\" height=\"350\" /></a>\r\n<blockquote>May 6, 2015\r\n\r\nDear InnVision Shelter Network,\r\n\r\nMy name is Tim Case and I\'m a Navy Veteran.  About five months ago I contacted your organization because I was in need of some help to get back on my feet.  I\'m writing this letter to thank you for everything your organization has done for me and tell you how much I appreciate all the hard work my case manager Dawn Holley did.\r\n\r\nYour organization provided me with a Clipper Card for public transportation, an interview outfit, help with repairs to my vehicle, work boots and work clothes, paid my security deposit, purchased me a bed with lined, utensils, cookware and a wonderful case manager who orchestrated it all.  In the past eleven months I have had the opportunity to work with a few case managers.  Dawn is by far the best one that I have had the privilege to work with.  She is caring, compassionate and motivated when it came to working with me..  She did ask for one thing, to keep in touch with her weekly.  At first I thought this was a little unnecessary, but it turned out to a very useful tool.  By communicating with her weekly she was able to coach me on what services were available and which ones she thought I might need.\r\n\r\nBecause of your organization and Dawn, I\'m back on my feet again and consider myself to be a success.  I now have a vehicle, a one bedroom apartment and a job with the Veteran Administration as a Boiler Operator in Menlo Park.  I feel very strongly that this wouldn\'t have been possible without your help.  If there\'s anything I can do to help your organization, please have Dawn contact me.  Thank you again for all your support.\r\n\r\nSincerely,\r\n\r\nTim</blockquote>\r\n<a href=\"https://14345.thankyou4caring.org/sslpage.aspx?pid=392\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-451 size-full\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/donate_button_purple.png\" alt=\"donate_button_purple\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.twitter.com/InnVisShelter\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-427 size-full\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/twitter_button.png\" alt=\"twitter_button\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/InnVisionShelterNetwork\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-425 size-full\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/facebook_button.png\" alt=\"facebook_button\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a>','A piece of gratitude from U.S. Veteran, Tim Case','','draft','closed','open','','tim','','','2015-05-04 19:05:48','2015-05-05 02:05:48','',8,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=1359',6,'page','',0),(1360,18,'2015-05-04 16:10:56','2015-05-04 23:10:56','','veteran with flag','','inherit','closed','open','','veteran-with-flag','','','2015-05-04 16:10:56','2015-05-04 23:10:56','',1359,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/veteran-with-flag.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1361,18,'2015-05-04 16:11:22','2015-05-04 23:11:22','','veteran dad','','inherit','closed','open','','veteran-dad','','','2015-05-04 16:11:22','2015-05-04 23:11:22','',1359,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/veteran-dad.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1364,11,'2015-05-06 14:01:25','2015-05-06 21:01:25','<a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/TimC.jpeg\"><img class=\"  wp-image-1366 aligncenter\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/TimC-320x427.jpeg\" alt=\"TimC\" width=\"308\" height=\"411\" /></a>\r\n<blockquote>January, 2015\r\n\r\nDear InnVision Shelter Network,\r\n\r\nMy name is Tim and I\'m a Navy Veteran.  About five months ago I contacted your organization because I was in need of some help to get back on my feet.  I\'m writing this letter to thank you for everything your organization has done for me and tell you how much I appreciate all the hard work my case manager Dawn Holley did.\r\n\r\nYour organization provided me with a Clipper Card for public transportation, an interview outfit, help with repairs to my vehicle, work boots and work clothes, paid my security deposit, purchased me a bed with linens, utensils, cookware and a wonderful case manager who orchestrated it all.  In the past eleven months I have had the opportunity to work with a few case managers.  Dawn is by far the best one that I have had the privilege to work with.  She is caring, compassionate and motivated when it came to working with me. She did ask for one thing, to keep in touch with her weekly.  At first I thought this was a little unnecessary, but it turned out to a very useful tool.  By communicating with her weekly she was able to coach me on what services were available and which ones she thought I might need.\r\n\r\nBecause of your organization and Dawn, I\'m back on my feet again and consider myself to be a success.  I now have a vehicle, a one bedroom apartment and a job with the Veteran Administration as a Boiler Operator in Menlo Park.  I feel very strongly that this wouldn\'t have been possible without your help.  If there\'s anything I can do to help your organization, please have Dawn contact me.  Thank you again for all your support.\r\n\r\nSincerely,\r\n\r\nTim</blockquote>\r\n<a href=\"https://14345.thankyou4caring.org/sslpage.aspx?pid=392\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-451 size-full\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/donate_button_purple.png\" alt=\"donate_button_purple\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.twitter.com/InnVisShelter\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-427 size-full\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/twitter_button.png\" alt=\"twitter_button\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/InnVisionShelterNetwork\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-425 size-full\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/facebook_button.png\" alt=\"facebook_button\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a>','A letter of gratitude from Tim, a U.S. Veteran.','','publish','closed','open','','tim','','','2015-05-06 15:44:40','2015-05-06 22:44:40','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/?p=1364',5,'post','',0),(1366,18,'2015-05-05 17:08:27','2015-05-06 00:08:27','','TimC','','inherit','closed','open','','timc','','','2015-05-05 17:08:27','2015-05-06 00:08:27','',1364,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/TimC.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1373,12,'2015-05-06 16:12:43','2015-05-06 23:12:43','','OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA','','inherit','closed','open','','olympus-digital-camera','','','2015-05-06 16:12:43','2015-05-06 23:12:43','',665,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Sarah-Boisseree.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1374,12,'2015-05-06 16:13:49','2015-05-06 23:13:49','','Picture1 (2)','','inherit','closed','open','','picture1-2','','','2015-05-06 16:13:49','2015-05-06 23:13:49','',665,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Picture1-2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1376,12,'2015-05-06 16:16:45','2015-05-06 23:16:45','','Promeet','','inherit','closed','open','','promeet','','','2015-05-06 16:16:45','2015-05-06 23:16:45','',665,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Promeet.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1377,12,'2015-05-06 16:17:25','2015-05-06 23:17:25','','Matt Pesko','','inherit','closed','open','','matt-pesko','','','2015-05-06 16:17:25','2015-05-06 23:17:25','',665,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Matt-Pesko.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1378,12,'2015-05-06 16:17:52','2015-05-06 23:17:52','','Shaun Warren','','inherit','closed','open','','shaun-warren','','','2015-05-06 16:17:52','2015-05-06 23:17:52','',665,'http://www.ivsn.