,0),(1397,11,'2015-05-28 21:04:27','2015-05-29 04:04:27','[caption id=\"attachment_1466\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"130\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1466\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Ted-Robinson-Photo_sm.jpg\" alt=\"Ted Robinson Photo_sm\" width=\"130\" height=\"179\" /> Ted Robinson[/caption]\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">‘Voice of the 49ers’ Ted Robinson in Conversation with 49ers Super Bowl Winner Dennis Brown </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Benefiting homeless families and individuals at InnVision Shelter Network</span></p>\r\n<strong>Thursday, October 8, 2015</strong>\r\n<strong>7:30-9:00am</strong>\r\n<strong>Hyatt Regency Hotel\r\n</strong><strong>1333 Bayshore Hwy, Burlingame</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Corporate-Sponsor-Info-2015_updated-8.20.pdf\"><img class=\" wp-image-1445 size-full alignnone\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/corporate-sponsor-button1.png\" alt=\"corporate sponsor button\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a> <a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Breakfast_Host-a-Table-Info-2015.pdf\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-362 size-full\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/host_a_table.png\" alt=\"host_a_table\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a> <a href=\"#anchor\"><img class=\" wp-image-1483 size-full alignnone\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/this-years-sponsors-button.png\" alt=\"this years sponsors button\" width=\"161\" height=\"51\" /></a>\r\n<h2>About the Benefit Breakfast</h2>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1395\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"160\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1395\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/Dennis-Brown-e1432872010131.png\" alt=\"Keynote Speaker: Dennis Brown\" width=\"160\" height=\"215\" /> Keynote Speaker: Dennis Brown[/caption]\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">This annual event hosted by InnVision Shelter Network (IVSN) increases awareness about homelessness among families and individuals in our community, and raises critically-needed funds to support IVSN high-impact housing programs and “Beyond the Bed” services for homeless families and adults.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Approximately 1,000 guests attending the Breakfast represent the broad base of support for InnVision Shelter Network, including corporations and their employees, individual donors, community and civic leaders, volunteers, and first-time guests.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Keynote Speaker: Dennis Brown</h2>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Dennis Brown is a Bay Area icon who served as an integral part of the 49ers’ Superbowl XXIX Championship Team for which he was the recipient of the Ed Block Courage Award.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Event Program</h2>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">The Benefit Breakfast features inspiring and educational remarks focused on issues of homelessness and the positive impact of philanthropy on ending homelessness in our community, including:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">‘Voice of the 49ers’ Ted Robinson in Conversation with 49ers Super Bowl Winner Dennis Brown Who Will Share His Personal Story of Overcoming Homelessness</span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">An update from CEO Bruce Ives on the InnVision Shelter Network mission to end homelessness</span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">A personal story from a client who has transformed their life through IVSN services</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Media</h2>\r\nFor questions, photos or interviews regarding the Benefit Breakfast, please contact Carolyn Hooper, Marketing and Communications Manager, at (650) 685-5880 ext. 169 or <a href=\"mailto:chooper@ivsn.org\">chooper@ivsn.org</a>.\r\n<a name=\"anchor\"></a>\r\n<h2>Thank You to Our Generous Event Sponsors</h2>\r\n<h2><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1532 size-full\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/sponsor-logos-10.6.15.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1611\" height=\"861\" /></h2>\r\n<h2>Thank you to our Table Hosts</h2>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Marianne Baldrica</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Rachel Perkel and Shawn Becker</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Kristin and John Brew</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Mike and Holly Campbell and Family</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Christina Dickerson</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Michelle and David Ebersman</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Kathleen Egan and Rod Ferguson</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Jill Grossman Family Charitable Fund</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Anna Zornosa-Heymann and Leonard Heymann</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Tiffany and Chin Hong</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Elizabeth and Zachary Hulsey</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Barrett Moore and Bruce Ives</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Mary and Edmond Jennings</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Christine and Jeffrey Krolik</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Laurie Kraus Lacob</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Brian Boisserée and Cathie Lesjak</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Lilli Rey</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Ann and Bill Regan</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Ron and Barbara Reis</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Shellye Archambeau and arence Scott</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Ray Mueller and Kristen Shima</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Congresswoman Jackie Speier</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Matthew Bahls and Jessica Weare</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Amy Wright and Emerick Woods</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Claire Wolfenden</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Thank you to our Community Partners</h2>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Congregational Church of San Mateo – UCC </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">St. Paul’s Episcopal Church of Burlingame</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">First United Methodist Church of Palo Alto</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Valley Presbyterian Church</span></p>\r\n&nbsp;','Benefit Breakfast','','publish','closed','closed','','benefit-breakfast-3','','','2015-10-07 12:33:17','2015-10-07 19:33:17','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/?post_type=event&#038;p=1397',2,'event','',0),(1398,15,'2015-05-29 19:27:05','2015-05-30 02:27:05','','Homeless Outreach Intern Job Description POST','','inherit','closed','open','','homeless-outreach-intern-job-description-post-2','','','2015-05-29 19:27:05','2015-05-30 02:27:05','',632,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/Homeless-Outreach-Intern-Job-Description-POST1.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(1404,11,'2015-06-02 17:23:38','2015-06-03 00:23:38','<h1>VP of Human Resources</h1>\r\n<strong>JOB DESCRIPTION</strong>\r\n\r\nInnVision Shelter Network seeks a VP of Human Resources to join our executive team. The VP of HR works with the leadership team to insure that IVSN attracts and retains leading talent to achieve our mission of returning homeless individuals and families to self-sufficiency and permanent housing,. The position reports directly to the CEO and is based in our Menlo Park, CA headquarters. The VP of HR and his/her team administer all aspects of employment for the organization’s 200+ employees working at 16 facilities across San Mateo and Santa Clara counties. Responsibilities include:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Participate in the development of the organization\'s plans and programs as a strategic partner, particularly from the perspective of the impact on employees.</li>\r\n	<li>Plan, develop, organize, implement, direct and evaluate the organization\'s human resource function and performance.</li>\r\n	<li>Direct and oversee the employment process for the organization. This includes working with hiring managers to develop and implement appropriate recruiting and selection strategies and tactics, and hiring strong performers.</li>\r\n	<li>Develop and maintain appropriate compensation guidelines.</li>\r\n	<li>Manage the employee benefits program. This includes making sure all offerings are competitive and cost effective and of value to employees.</li>\r\n	<li>Conduct full cycle performance review process. Recommend, develop and implement Human Resources policies.</li>\r\n	<li>Ensure compliance with all EEO, employment, benefits, and wage-hour laws.</li>\r\n	<li>Provide training, coaching, and mentoring to managers and leaders on people hiring skills, management and leadership skills and strategies (as appropriate) such as setting clear performance expectations, providing constructive feedback, recognizing positive results, taking correction action (where necessary) and linking compensation to performance.</li>\r\n	<li>Facilitate conflict resolution and handle employee relations issues. This includes working with managers to identify performance issues and develop and implement appropriate measures to provide employees the opportunity to succeed and to take corrective action where necessary.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Education and/or Job Experience</strong>:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>BA in business, Human Resources, or related field.</li>\r\n	<li>8+ years of experience in the field of Human Resources. Prior management experience preferred and non-profit experience a plus.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Special Skills, Abilities, and Requirements</strong>:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Exceptional interpersonal skills.</li>\r\n	<li>Excellent judgment and discretion.</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to communicate effectively, facilitate interactions and resolve conflicts.</li>\r\n	<li>Proven leadership, management, and project management skills.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>HOW TO APPLY</strong>\r\n\r\nInterested candidates should send a cover letter and resume to: <a href=\"mailto:execstaffing@ivsn.org\">execstaffing@ivsn.org</a> and indicate “VP of HR” in the subject line.','VP of Human Resources','','publish','closed','open','','vp-human-resources','','','2015-06-02 17:23:38','2015-06-03 00:23:38','',251,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=1404',12,'page','',0),(1405,11,'2015-06-02 22:41:55','2015-06-03 05:41:55','','ivsn_newsletter_spring 2015','','inherit','closed','open','','ivsn_newsletter_spring-2015','','','2015-06-02 22:41:55','2015-06-03 05:41:55','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/ivsn_newsletter_spring-2015.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(1409,11,'2015-06-02 22:49:49','2015-06-03 05:49:49','','IVSN Spring Newsletter 2015 Cover','','inherit','closed','open','','ivsn-spring-newsletter-2015-cover','','','2015-06-02 22:49:49','2015-06-03 05:49:49','',250,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/IVSN-Spring-Newsletter-2015-Cover.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1411,11,'2015-06-04 19:07:57','2015-06-05 02:07:57','<h1>Chief Financial Officer</h1>\r\n<strong>JOB DESCRIPTION</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>TITLE:</strong><strong>                   Chief Financial Officer</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>SUPERVISOR:     Chief Executive Officer</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>STATUS:              Full Time, Non-Exempt</strong>\r\n\r\nInnVision Shelter Network seeks an executive with outstanding management, financial and business acumen; one who is focused on working collaboratively with colleagues and Board members to help lead the organization in achieving its mission.\r\n\r\nAs a member of the Sr. Leadership Team, the Chief Financial Officer will partner with the CEO, Board members and colleagues to contribute to the overall strategic direction of the organization from a financial, business and operational perspective. The CFO will be responsible for creating and maintaining financial compliance for IVSN’s public and private funding, including the creation and execution of breakeven operating budgets.  Key objectives for the CFO will be to ensure that InnVision Shelter Network’s capital structure, financial systems, and controls support the program strategies and quality expectations for serving Silicon Valley’s homeless population.\r\n\r\nWe seek an experienced hands-on executive who can successfully mentor a team, and engage the Board of Directors and CEO in creating and maintaining smooth accounting and financial systems for compliance and a growth culture.\r\n\r\nThe Chief Financial Officer is responsible for all aspects of financial record keeping, planning and budgeting and supervises the accounting and finance department.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Key responsibilities include</strong>:\r\n\r\nBuild/innovate substantial internal systems capability, to support centralized financial control systems, grant spend-down, program expense details and on-time invoicing and reporting to public funders.\r\n\r\nEffectively communicate the financial and business objectives and strategies, financial performance, and operational metrics of the company to Board of Directors and executive management on a monthly basis.\r\n\r\nCreate and maintain internal controls, systems, and reporting processes in accordance with Non-Profit GAAP and public funder compliance (primarily HUD, CDBG, etc.).\r\n\r\nMaintain productive relationships with peers, mid-level management, while facilitating a customer-oriented philosophy with field personnel.\r\n\r\nDirect and coordinate IVSN’s budget planning and forecasting processes; manage the appropriate use of IVSN’s working capital.\r\n\r\nCollaborate with colleagues and Board members on Real Estate Task management.\r\n\r\nLead the team in daily accounting and financial operations:  Monthly Financial Statements; Accounts Receivable and Grants Management – Spend-down reporting; Cash Flow Forecasting; Audit/A-133 Single Audit/990; Payroll Allocations that comply with public funding grants.\r\n\r\nPreparing financial statements and analyses for the Board Finance Committee and various government and private funding sources for this $18M annual budget nonprofit.\r\n\r\nPlanning and monitoring cash requirements and maintaining adequate cash flow.\r\n\r\nCollaborating with the grants team to provide financial assessment of new/renewal public contract opportunities.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Duties:</strong>\r\n\r\n<em>General Accounting</em>: Lead financial team in daily accounting and financial operations:  Journal Entries; Accounts Receivable/Payable; Grant (Funding) Spend-down reconciliation and reporting.  Responsible for all accounting transactions within GAAP guidelines, funding source regulations, budgetary constraints and compliance with OMB-Circular A-133.\r\n\r\n<em>Financial Reporting</em>: Prepare monthly financial statements, as well as financial reports for internal use and for submission to funding sources. Effectively communicate the agencies’ financial and business objectives and strategies, financial performance, and operational metrics to Board of Directors and Senior Leadership team, on a monthly basis.\r\n\r\n<em>Budgeting</em>: Forecast and prepare fiscal operational budgets. Analyze budgetary variances and review all unplanned expenditures by month for review with CEO. Lead collaboration with (field) managers on their public and private grant(s) spend-down and subsequent reimbursement. Lead monthly budget reporting and monitoring for Senior Leadership team.\r\n\r\n<em>Audit:</em> Supervise preparation of audit schedules. Review and approve audit adjustments, audited financial statements and footnotes. Coordinate and assist internal and external auditors regarding all audit and tax return documents preparation. Participate in BOD Audit Committee meetings.\r\n\r\n<em>Payroll</em>: Supervise payroll staff in all aspects of personnel timekeeping and ADP bi-monthly payroll transactions. Collaborate with HR and Benefit staff on effective financial expenditures.\r\n\r\n<em>Staff Supervision and Development</em>: Hire, train, supervise, and evaluate accounting/financial staff. Provide professional development opportunities to staff to ensure optimum staff retention.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Qualifications:</strong>\r\n\r\nBachelor\'s degree, strong accounting background, CPA certification is a plus.\r\n\r\n15+ years in roles of increasing executive responsibility that have culminated in a CFO role for private sector or non-profit organization(s).\r\n\r\nComfort in a complex organization that offers a portfolio of services across multiple funders and jurisdictions.\r\n\r\nStrong understanding of cost accounting. Experience with Deltek system is a plus.\r\n\r\nExcellent communication skills, and a customer-service orientation.\r\n\r\nA desire to serve as both a financial expert and a superior general manager.\r\n\r\nExperience with government/public grants and grant spend-down processes.\r\n\r\nExperience in hiring, training, evaluating and supervising department staff.\r\n\r\nCommitment to high-quality work in a fast-paced environment.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Personal Attributes:</strong>\r\n\r\nStrong interpersonal skills, operates with highest level of professionalism, mutual respect and integrity.\r\n\r\nA proven leader – humble, confident and willing to roll up sleeves and work hands-on.\r\n\r\nExcellent communication and presentation skills.\r\n\r\nAbility to juggle and manage multiple priorities along with strong organizational and prioritization skills. Desire to innovate with the patience to lead non-profit teams through change management.\r\n\r\n<em>IVSN is an Equal Opportunity Employer (EOE). </em>\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Please send resumes or nominations to</strong>:\r\n\r\nMontie Parker                                                                Janet Monfredini\r\n\r\n<a href=\"mailto:parker@bridgessf.com\">parker@bridgessf.com</a>                                                      <a href=\"mailto:janet@bridgessf.com\">janet@bridgessf.com</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nBridges SF, LLC                                                                  (415) 294-4646 Office/Fax\r\n\r\n220 Montgomery Street, Suite 693                                   <a href=\"http://www.bridgessf.com\">www.bridgessf.com</a>\r\n\r\nSan Francisco, CA 94104','Chief Financial Officer','','publish','closed','open','','chief-financial-officer','','','2015-06-04 19:07:57','2015-06-05 02:07:57','',251,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=1411',13,'page','',0),(1412,11,'2015-06-04 19:11:57','2015-06-05 02:11:57','<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-908 size-full\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/Summer2014.jpg\" alt=\"Summer2014\" width=\"300\" height=\"201\" />\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">We are pleased to present InnVision Shelter Network’s 2015 Summer Camp blog. Thank you to our summer camp interns and volunteers for sharing their site updates and highlights throughout the program!</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">This fun summer camp experience is available for children staying at our family shelters, and provides many unique activities and field trips. Be sure to subscribe to the blog here to stay updated throughout summer.</span></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nClick here to read more on the <a href=\"http://ivsnsummercamp.wordpress.com/\">Summer Adventure Camp Blog</a> or learn more about <a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/services/family-services/summer-camp/\">IVSN\'s Summer Adventure Camp</a>.','Summer Adventure Camp 2015','','publish','closed','open','','summer-adventure-camp-2015','','','2015-06-04 19:11:57','2015-06-05 02:11:57','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/?p=1412',4,'post','',0),(1417,11,'2015-06-14 22:35:34','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<h1>Director of Behavioral Health</h1>\r\n<strong>JOB DESCRIPTION</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Title:</strong>                          Director of Behavioral Health\r\n\r\n<strong>Supervisor:</strong>                Vice President, Programs &amp; Services\r\n\r\n<strong>Hours:                        </strong>Flex/Hours Negotiable (0.6 – 1.0 FTE); Benefits dependent on FTE status\r\n\r\n<strong>Compensation:         </strong>DOE\r\n\r\nInnVision Shelter Network (IVSN) is one of the largest and most effective providers of shelter/housing and supportive services across Silicon Valley and the San Francisco Peninsula. IVSN operates over 18 major sites from San Jose to Daly City, providing emergency, transitional, and permanent supportive housing, along with a breadth of supportive resources to help clients secure a place to call home. The organization serves thousands of homeless clients annually through its \"Beyond the Bed\" service model -- a proven methodology that has historically delivered a 90% success rate in returning program graduates to permanent housing and self-sufficiency\r\n\r\nAs the Director of Behavioral Health, the primary responsibility is overseeing IVSN’s Mental Health Internship Program, which consists of 10-12 practicum students, whom the Director of Behavioral Health must recruit, supervise and train yearly.\r\n\r\n<strong>Responsibilities include:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Individual supervision: </strong>Serve as primary supervisor to 5-10 practicum students.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Group supervision:</strong> Facilitate case conference to 10-12 practicum students.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Didactics and trainings:</strong> Provide weekly didactics to 10-12 practicum students. Provide occasional trainings to Case Managers and Children’s Services Coordinators. In addition, facilitate monthly Brown Bag Training, which focus on specialty topics of Psychology (i.e. Trauma, Child Abuse, Eating Disorders, etc.), to all IVSN Direct Services Staff.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Management:</strong> Evaluate progress and clinical work of practicum students and provide feedback to appropriate schools’ liaisons.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Referrals:</strong> Oversee the therapy and psychological assessment referral process.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Crisis Management:</strong> Provide on-call crisis supervision to all IVSN Direct Services Staff as needed.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Research:</strong> Organize and track data that practicum students use to publish posters for APA and other psychological associations’ conventions.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Recruiting:</strong> Attend practicum fairs, interview prospective practicum students, contract with practicum students and oversee the entire BAPIC match process, as well as the BAPIC Clearinghouse process.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Budgeting:</strong> Oversee a 150-200K budget and have regular communication with IVSN’s Grants Department and Finance Department.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Grant Reporting:</strong> Communicate productivity outcome data to Grants Department and provide feedback on LOI’s, grant applications and grant reviews.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Funding:</strong> Attend occasional donor events.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe job is approximately 50% supervision, 25% teaching/training and 25% administrative.<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Job Requirements: </strong>Applicant must meet the following job requirements:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Licensed Psychologist providing psychological services to low-socio economic or homeless individuals and families.</li>\r\n	<li>Strong leadership and management skills.</li>\r\n	<li>Strong communication, organization, time management and writing skills.</li>\r\n	<li>Capable of overseeing a program that consists of 10-12 practicum students and contracted outside supervisors.</li>\r\n	<li>Familiar with Microsoft Office.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Strongly Preferred Qualifications: </strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Prior supervision experience and teaching experience.</li>\r\n	<li>Prior experience working with a traumatized and substance using population.</li>\r\n	<li>Prior experience providing crisis management to clients, as well as training staff on crisis management interventions.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Theoretical Orientation and Psychological Services</strong>: Applicant must have a strong background in Psychodynamic Therapy and a multitude of experience treating trauma in low-socio economic or homeless individuals and families. Familiarity with psychological testing instruments is necessary but having extensive psychological testing clinical experience is not necessary for the job. Most of the practicum students come from Palo Alto University and Alliant and are interested in learning about psychodynamic therapy.\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Candidates:</strong> The ideal candidate will have an interest in psychodynamic therapy and an interest in working with a homeless population. They should have a strong interest in supervising and be capable of overseeing a training program. In addition, there is some light budgeting and grant writing responsibilities; Individual should be a strong writer and have familiarity with excel. The individual must have experience with and be comfortable conducting CPS/APS reports, as well as working with a traumatized and substance using population. Having experience with testing and research is not necessary, but will be beneficial.\r\n\r\n<strong>How to Apply:            </strong>\r\n\r\nInterested parties should send a cover letter and resume to Dr. Brian Greenberg, <a href=\"mailto:bgreenberg@ivsn.org\">bgreenberg@ivsn.org</a> and Karyna Ha, <a href=\"mailto:kha@ivsn.org\">kha@ivsn.org</a>.','Director of Behavioral Health','','draft','closed','open','','','','','2015-06-14 22:35:34','2015-06-15 05:35:34','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/?p=1417',3,'post','',0),(1418,11,'2015-06-14 22:37:08','2015-06-15 05:37:08','<h1>Director of Behavioral Health</h1>\r\n<strong>JOB DESCRIPTION</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Title:</strong>                          Director of Behavioral Health\r\n\r\n<strong>Supervisor:</strong>                Vice President, Programs &amp; Services\r\n\r\n<strong>Hours:                        </strong>Flex/Hours Negotiable (0.6 – 1.0 FTE); Benefits dependent on FTE status\r\n\r\n<strong>Compensation:         </strong>DOE\r\n\r\nInnVision Shelter Network (IVSN) is one of the largest and most effective providers of shelter/housing and supportive services across Silicon Valley and the San Francisco Peninsula. IVSN operates over 18 major sites from San Jose to Daly City, providing emergency, transitional, and permanent supportive housing, along with a breadth of supportive resources to help clients secure a place to call home. The organization serves thousands of homeless clients annually through its \"Beyond the Bed\" service model -- a proven methodology that has historically delivered a 90% success rate in returning program graduates to permanent housing and self-sufficiency\r\n\r\nAs the Director of Behavioral Health, the primary responsibility is overseeing IVSN’s Mental Health Internship Program, which consists of 10-12 practicum students, whom the Director of Behavioral Health must recruit, supervise and train yearly.\r\n\r\n<strong>Responsibilities include:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Individual supervision: </strong>Serve as primary supervisor to 5-10 practicum students.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Group supervision:</strong> Facilitate case conference to 10-12 practicum students.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Didactics and trainings:</strong> Provide weekly didactics to 10-12 practicum students. Provide occasional trainings to Case Managers and Children’s Services Coordinators. In addition, facilitate monthly Brown Bag Training, which focus on specialty topics of Psychology (i.e. Trauma, Child Abuse, Eating Disorders, etc.), to all IVSN Direct Services Staff.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Management:</strong> Evaluate progress and clinical work of practicum students and provide feedback to appropriate schools’ liaisons.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Referrals:</strong> Oversee the therapy and psychological assessment referral process.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Crisis Management:</strong> Provide on-call crisis supervision to all IVSN Direct Services Staff as needed.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Research:</strong> Organize and track data that practicum students use to publish posters for APA and other psychological associations’ conventions.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Recruiting:</strong> Attend practicum fairs, interview prospective practicum students, contract with practicum students and oversee the entire BAPIC match process, as well as the BAPIC Clearinghouse process.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Budgeting:</strong> Oversee a 150-200K budget and have regular communication with IVSN’s Grants Department and Finance Department.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Grant Reporting:</strong> Communicate productivity outcome data to Grants Department and provide feedback on LOI’s, grant applications and grant reviews.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Funding:</strong> Attend occasional donor events.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe job is approximately 50% supervision, 25% teaching/training and 25% administrative.<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Job Requirements: </strong>Applicant must meet the following job requirements:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Licensed Psychologist providing psychological services to low-socio economic or homeless individuals and families.</li>\r\n	<li>Strong leadership and management skills.</li>\r\n	<li>Strong communication, organization, time management and writing skills.</li>\r\n	<li>Capable of overseeing a program that consists of 10-12 practicum students and contracted outside supervisors.</li>\r\n	<li>Familiar with Microsoft Office.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Strongly Preferred Qualifications:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Prior supervision experience and teaching experience.</li>\r\n	<li>Prior experience working with a traumatized and substance using population.</li>\r\n	<li>Prior experience providing crisis management to clients, as well as training staff on crisis management interventions.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Theoretical Orientation and Psychological Services</strong>: Applicant must have a strong background in Psychodynamic Therapy and a multitude of experience treating trauma in low-socio economic or homeless individuals and families. Familiarity with psychological testing instruments is necessary but having extensive psychological testing clinical experience is not necessary for the job. Most of the practicum students come from Palo Alto University and Alliant and are interested in learning about psychodynamic therapy.\r\n\r\n<strong>Candidates:</strong> The ideal candidate will have an interest in psychodynamic therapy and an interest in working with a homeless population. They should have a strong interest in supervising and be capable of overseeing a training program. In addition, there is some light budgeting and grant writing responsibilities; Individual should be a strong writer and have familiarity with excel. The individual must have experience with and be comfortable conducting CPS/APS reports, as well as working with a traumatized and substance using population. Having experience with testing and research is not necessary, but will be beneficial.\r\n\r\n<strong>How to Apply:           </strong>\r\n\r\nInterested parties should send a cover letter and resume to Dr. Brian Greenberg, <a href=\"mailto:bgreenberg@ivsn.org\">bgreenberg@ivsn.org</a> and Karyna Ha, <a href=\"mailto:kha@ivsn.org\">kha@ivsn.org</a>.','Director of Behavioral Health','','publish','closed','open','','director-of-behavioral-health','','','2015-06-14 22:37:08','2015-06-15 05:37:08','',251,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=1418',14,'page','',0),(1419,11,'2015-06-14 22:39:46','2015-06-15 05:39:46','<h1>Outreach Case Manager</h1>\r\n<strong>JOB DESCRIPTION</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Title: </strong>Outreach Case Manager\r\n\r\n<strong>Supervisor: </strong>Manager, Outreach\r\n\r\n<strong>Salary Range: </strong>DOE\r\n\r\n<strong>Status: </strong>Full Time/Non-Exempt\r\n\r\nAre you a socially conscience individual with a genuine need to serve the homeless community in San Mateo County? Are you looking for hands on job opportunity that takes you outdoors, interacting with homeless individuals in their environment? Do you enjoy helping others in need? If so, then Innvision Shelter Network needs you! InnVision Shelter Network is looking for a motivated individual with a “can do” attitude to fill the role of an outreach case manager.\r\n\r\nInnVision Shelter Network (IVSN) is one of the largest and most effective providers of shelter/housing and supportive services across Silicon Valley and the San Francisco Peninsula. IVSN operates over 18 major sites from San Jose to Daly City, providing emergency, transitional, and permanent supportive housing, along with a breadth of supportive resources to help clients secure a place to call home. The organization serves thousands of homeless clients annually through its \"Beyond the Bed\" service model -- a proven methodology that has historically delivered a 90% success rate in returning program graduates to permanent housing and self-sufficiency\r\n\r\n<strong>Qualifications: </strong>Prefer minimum two years’ experience in conducting outreach or providing similar services to homeless families and/or individuals in crisis. Excellent interpersonal skills and ability to interact effectively with other agencies. Prior experience with outreach responsibilities a plus. Understanding of the issues faced by low-income and unsheltered populations. Spanish-speaking a plus. Automobile, valid driver’s license and ability to meet IVSN’s driving policy. Must be Computer Literate and proficient in Microsoft Office.<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Responsibilities: </strong>The Outreach Case Manager will work throughout San Mateo County and in some cases Santa Clara County to identify and connect with unsheltered homeless persons. The Outreach Case Manager will be in the field 70% of the time.\r\n\r\n<strong>Duties:</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><strong> Outreach Case Management: </strong>Provide outreach and case management services to unsheltered homeless individuals. Identify target population and perform screening assessments and ongoing case management to assist participants to meet their goals. Provide information, referrals and crisis intervention as needed. Keep case files up-to-date, thorough, and accurate. Assist in compiling program statistics.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol start=\"2\">\r\n	<li><strong> Meetings: </strong>Meet weekly with program staff to coordinate delivery of services. Meet weekly with supervisor for supervision. Participate in meetings with other community agencies. Other duties may be assigned by supervisor.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol start=\"3\">\r\n	<li><strong> Travel: </strong>The position requires considerable travel in an IVSN vehicle. OCM must be willing to drive to various locations in the Bay Area as needed.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<strong>How to Apply:            </strong>\r\n\r\nInterested parties should send a cover letter and resume to <a href=\"mailto:jobs@ivsn.org\">jobs@ivsn.org</a>','Outreach Case Manager','','publish','closed','open','','case-manager-outreach','','','2015-06-14 22:45:17','2015-06-15 05:45:17','',251,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=1419',15,'page','',0),(1425,18,'2015-07-13 15:52:12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<h2><span style=\"color: #800080;\"><strong>Welcome to the Monthly Giving Circle!</strong></span></h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Happy-campers.jpg\"><img class=\"  wp-image-1426 aligncenter\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Happy-campers-320x268.jpg\" alt=\"Happy campers\" width=\"379\" height=\"318\" /></a>\r\n\r\nWhen you <a href=\"https://14345.thankyou4caring.org/sslpage.aspx?pid=392\">give monthly</a> to InnVision Shelter Network, your ongoing support helps us plan, allocating resources to ensure out clients have the tools they need to regain housing and self-sufficiency for the long-term, breaking the cycle of poverty and homelessness.\r\n<h5><span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>$10/month provides a birthday party to all grade school children born in a given month.</strong></span></h5>\r\n<h5><span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>$25/month can help one student with the cost of college applications</strong></span></h5>\r\n<h5><span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>$50/month can send a child to Summer Adventure Camp</strong></span></h5>\r\n<h5><span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>$100/month can educate 30 clients on interview and resume skills</strong></span></h5>\r\n<h5><span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>$150/month can provide mental health services to 15 clients</strong></span></h5>\r\n<h5><span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>$200/month can provide case management services for a family of four.</strong></span></h5>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #800080;\"><a style=\"color: #800080;\" href=\"https://14345.thankyou4caring.org/sslpage.aspx?pid=392\">Save time while changing lives!</a></span></h3>\r\n<h4>Become a monthly donor today and enjoy:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Hassle-free automatic monthly donations.</li>\r\n	<li>Annual statements in February for tax preparation.</li>\r\n	<li>Flexibility to adjust your donation at any time.</li>\r\n	<li>Email communications to connect you with the stories of our clients and their successes.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Don\'t forget to choose \"recurring gift\" and select your preferred giving date each month. </strong></span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Monthly Giving','','draft','closed','open','','monthly-giving','','','2015-07-13 15:52:12','2015-07-13 22:52:12','',43,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=1425',5,'page','',0),(1426,18,'2015-06-19 14:06:18','2015-06-19 21:06:18','','Happy campers','','inherit','closed','open','','happy-campers','','','2015-06-19 14:06:18','2015-06-19 21:06:18','',1425,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/upl