',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(1448,11,'2015-07-27 21:05:52','2015-07-28 04:05:52','','Sponsor Recognition 2015','','inherit','closed','open','','sponsor-recognition-2015','','','2015-07-27 21:05:52','2015-07-28 04:05:52','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Sponsor-Recognition-2015.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(1449,11,'2015-07-27 21:07:50','2015-07-28 04:07:50','','Host a Table Info 2015','','inherit','closed','open','','host-a-table-info-2015','','','2015-07-27 21:07:50','2015-07-28 04:07:50','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Host-a-Table-Info-2015.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(1450,11,'2015-07-27 21:09:01','2015-07-28 04:09:01','','Corporate Sponsor Info 2015','','inherit','closed','open','','corporate-sponsor-info-2015','','','2015-07-27 21:09:01','2015-07-28 04:09:01','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Corporate-Sponsor-Info-2015.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(1451,11,'2015-07-28 21:26:11','2015-07-29 04:26:11','','Breakfast_Host a Table Info 2015','','inherit','closed','open','','breakfast_host-a-table-info-2015','','','2015-07-28 21:26:11','2015-07-29 04:26:11','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Breakfast_Host-a-Table-Info-2015.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(1456,11,'2015-07-28 21:41:16','2015-07-29 04:41:16','','Breakfast_Corporate Sponsor Info 2015','','inherit','closed','open','','breakfast_corporate-sponsor-info-2015','','','2015-07-28 21:41:16','2015-07-29 04:41:16','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Breakfast_Corporate-Sponsor-Info-2015.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(1457,11,'2015-07-28 21:58:45','2015-07-29 04:58:45','<em>Event will feature ‘Voice of the 49ers’ Ted Robinson in Conversation with 49ers Super Bowl Winner Dennis Brown Who Will Share His Personal Story of Overcoming Homelessness</em><strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>MENLO PARK, CA</strong>– InnVision Shelter Network (IVSN), a leading provider of housing and supportive services for homeless families and individuals in Santa Clara and San Mateo Counties, will host its annual Benefit Breakfast on Thursday, October 8<sup>th</sup> from 7:30am to 9:00am at the Hyatt Regency Hotel in Burlingame.\r\n\r\nProgram highlights will include:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>An update on the programs of InnVision Shelter Network from CEO Bruce Ives</li>\r\n	<li>The personal story of an IVSN client</li>\r\n	<li>Fundraising opportunities for IVSN programs that assist over 10,000 homeless people each year</li>\r\n	<li>An engaging keynote address designed as a ‘fireside chat’ between Ted Robinson, the radio play-by-play announcer for the San Francisco 49ers, and Dennis Brown, former San Francisco 49ers defensive end, Super Bowl XXIX Championship team member, Rookie of the Year, and winner of the Ed Block Courage Award</li>\r\n	<li>Community engagement awards honoring local volunteers</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe IVSN Annual Benefit Breakfast is the largest event of its kind on the San Francisco Peninsula, with typically over 1,000 guests attending. This inspiring event promotes awareness about issues of homelessness and how the community can get involved to contribute to effective solutions. Event sponsorships, table hosts and day-of donations help fund IVSN housing programs and supportive services for homeless men, women, and children.\r\n\r\nEvent sponsorship information and table host opportunities are available online at <a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/breakfast\">www.ivsn.org/breakfast</a> or by emailing or calling Amy Wright, VP, Development <a href=\"mailto:awright@ivsn.org\">awright@ivsn.org</a>; (650) 685-5880 ext. 132.','InnVision Shelter Network Annual Benefit Breakfast Set for Thursday, October 8, 2015','','publish','closed','open','','innvision-shelter-network-annual-benefit-breakfast-set-for-thursday-october-8-2015','','','2015-07-28 21:58:45','2015-07-29 04:58:45','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/?p=1457',2,'post','',0),(1458,11,'2015-07-28 22:01:38','2015-07-29 05:01:38','','Ted Robinson and Dennis Brown keynote speakers at InnVision Shelter Network Breakfast 10-8-15','','inherit','closed','open','','ted-robinson-and-dennis-brown-keynote-speakers-at-innvision-shelter-network-breakfast-10-8-15','','','2015-07-28 22:01:38','2015-07-29 05:01:38','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Ted-Robinson-and-Dennis-Brown-keynote-speakers-at-InnVision-Shelter-Network-Breakfast-10-8-15.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(1460,11,'2015-09-02 20:53:27','2015-09-03 03:53:27','<h1>A.C.E.S. Program<img class=\"alignright wp-image-1461 size-medium\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Picture1-320x213.jpg\" alt=\"ACES Page Photo\" width=\"320\" height=\"213\" /></h1>\r\n<h2>Achieving Career and Educational Success with Homeless Children and Young Adults</h2>\r\nACES empowers children and young adults, who have experienced the stress and uncertainty of homelessness, to achieve higher education. <a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/ACES-Brochure-0518_Online.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-1462 size-full\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/brochure-button.png\" alt=\"ACES brochure button\" width=\"208\" height=\"51\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThe ACES Program hallmarks:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Grounded in STEM subjects</li>\r\n	<li>Encourages students to reach for higher education and post-secondary training<a href=\"https://14345.thankyou4caring.org/sslpage.aspx?pid=392\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-1471 size-full\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Donate-ACES.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"208\" height=\"51\" /></a></li>\r\n	<li>Establishes good learning habits</li>\r\n	<li>Sparks new interests that foster a lifetime love of learning</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Introducing ACES:</b>\r\n\r\nThe impact of homelessness on children is severe. Many children experience educational gaps, high levels of stress, and fall behind academically and socially over time. The destabilizing effect of homelessness interrupts the structures and routines that contribute to building good habits and attitudes toward learning. Children and their parents lack exposure to ideas and possibilities beyond their current circumstances.\r\n\r\nThe Achieving Career and Educational Success (ACES) program was conceived to complement formal education and rebuild the confidence in our learners which has been hindered by the inevitable stress and uncertainty created by homelessness. This is accomplished through engagement with Science, Technology, Engineering and Math (STEM) focused learning opportunities.\r\n\r\nResearch shows that students who experience homelessness are at far greater risk of developmental delays and exhibit emotional and behavioral problems. Poor school attendance caused by frequent moves drives lower academic performance, reduces social maturity, and enables the cycle of poverty to continue. InnVision Shelter Network is in a prime position to help disrupt this cycle. IVSN has already incorporated robust programing targeted at children in our “Beyond the Bed” model. Shelters serving families have full-time professional staff trained to work with the specific needs of children and youth. With our proven track record of instilling life-skills that contribute to real world success in adult clients, we have taken aim at doing the same for the children and youth who come through our doors.\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">For more information on this program or how you can help, please contact Ruth Richerson at <a href=\"mailto:rricherson@ivsn.org\"><span class=\"s2\">rricherson@ivsn.org</span></a> or (650) 685-5880 ext 171.</span></p>','A.C.E.S. Program','','publish','closed','open','','aces-program','','','2015-09-09 22:25:31','2015-09-10 05:25:31','',33,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=1460',117,'page','',0),(1461,11,'2015-07-28 22:28:07','2015-07-29 05:28:07','','ACES Page Photo','','in