 Mateo County)</li>\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Case-Manager-JSI.docx\">Julian Street Inn</a> (San Jose)</li>\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Case-Manager-MSI.doc\">Montgomery Street Inn</a> (San Jose)</li>\n	<li>SS</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Children-Services-Coordinator-CSI.doc\">Children Services Coordinator, Commercial Street Inn</a> (San Jose)</li>\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Asst.-CSC_Program-Aide_October-2015.doc\" target=\"_blank\">Assistant Children Services Coordinator, Haven Family House</a> (Menlo Park)</li>\n	<li>Residential Services Coordinator positions\n<ul>\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Residential-Services-Coordinator-First-Step.doc\">First Step for Families</a> (San Mateo)</li>\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Residential-Services-Coordinator-Maple-Street.doc\">Maple Street Shelter</a> (Redwood City)</li>\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Residential-Services-Coordinator-MSI.doc\">Montgomery Street Inn</a> (San Jose)</li>\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Residential-Services-Coordinator-San-Mateo-County-Part-Time-Relief.doc\">Part time/relief (San Mateo County)</a></li>\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Residential-Services-Coordinator-Santa-Clara-County-Part-Time-Relief.doc\">Part time/relief (Santa Clara County)</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Development</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>No current openings</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Finance</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>No current openings</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Human Resources</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/about/jobs/vp-human-resources/\">VP of Human Resources</a></li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Operations</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>No current openings</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Technology &amp; Compliance</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>No current openings</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;','Jobs','','inherit','closed','open','','251-autosave-v1','','','2015-11-08 21:14:31','2015-11-09 05:14:31','',251,'http://www.ivsn.org/251-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1497,11,'2015-08-31 20:38:41','2015-09-01 03:38:41','<h1>Program Director, Family &amp; Individual Sites</h1>\r\n<strong>JOB DESCRIPTION</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Title:</strong>                          Program Director, Family &amp; Individuals Sites\r\n\r\n<strong>Supervisor:</strong>                Programs/ Associate, Vice President\r\n\r\n<strong>Compensation:         </strong>DOE\r\n\r\n<strong>Status:                        </strong>FTE, Exempt + Benefits\r\n\r\nInnVision Shelter Network (IVSN) is the leading provider of shelter/housing and supportive services across Silicon Valley and the San Francisco Peninsula. IVSN operates 17 sites from San Jose to Daly City, providing interim and stabilization shelter, permanent supportive housing, outreach, rapid re-housing, and homelessness prevention services.\r\n\r\n<strong>Preferred Qualifications:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Masters in Social Work or equivalent, and at least 5 years’ experience providing direct client services in human services.</li>\r\n	<li>Strong leadership skills, experience in developing and managing programs serving <em>at risk</em> individuals and families.</li>\r\n	<li>Strong analytical and strategic thinking.</li>\r\n	<li>Strong written and oral communication required.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Position Summary &amp; Duties: </strong>\r\n\r\nUnder the direction of the Associate Vice President of Programs and Services, the Program Director will manage the day to day operations and budget of a residential program for homeless individuals or/and families.  The Program Director oversees staff, interns, and volunteers, and is responsible for ensuring high quality services, staff development and our client focused mission to return to self-sufficiency and permanent housing.\r\n\r\nDuties include, but are not limited, to the following:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><strong>Administration:</strong> Ensure the delivery of services in a professional, ethical and effective manner; ensure maintenance of a clean, safe, and supportive environment for clients and staff. Program operations oversight and budget management. Participate in administration and coordination of agency activities and programs via Program Director meetings. Understand and implement all InnVision Shelter Network policies and procedures. Be available on-call for site emergencies.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol start=\"2\">\r\n	<li><strong>Supervision:</strong> Responsibilities include, but not limited to, new staff hires, personnel management, orientations and training of staff, client programming and a site scheduling of staff and program volunteers. The director provides on-going leadership, guidance, and development regarding program and client issues. Also required are facilitation of regular staff meetings, oversight of agency needed committees (as assigned) and an understanding of developing and cultivating community partners.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol start=\"3\">\r\n	<li><strong>Case Management:</strong> Case management development and supervision and/or provide direct services where needed. Responsibilities include oversight of intake coordination, use of information and referral networks and its required documentation, and crisis management. Respond to client appeals/grievances.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol start=\"4\">\r\n	<li><strong>Community Relations:</strong> Develop and maintain strong relationships with area service providers, businesses, and community groups. Effectively communicate our eligibility criteria and referral process. Represent our programs to government, business, religious, civic, and community groups. Educate and inform the community on homeless issues and the direct work of the program. Develop and cultivate Program’s Support Committee. Effectively interact with Board, volunteers, donors, and the surrounding community.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol start=\"5\">\r\n	<li><strong>Program Statistics/Record Keeping:</strong> Supervise the collection, compilation, and submission of all program statistics. Submit monthly, quarterly, and annual reports to Administration. Ensure that all required program reports and documentation are completed a timely fashion and that the program remains in compliance with all funding and legal requirements.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>General Duties:</strong> Participate in Program Team and All-Staff Meetings, program open houses, fundraising events, and other agency-wide functions. Agency in a guest speaking engagements as necessary. Other duties as assigned.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<strong style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">How to Apply:           </strong>\r\n\r\nTo apply for this position please email cover letter and resume to Karyna Ha at <a href=\"mailto:kha@ivsn.org\">kha@ivsn.org</a>','Program Director, Family & Individuals Sites','','publish','closed','open','','program-director-family-individuals-sites','','','2015-08-31 20:58:30','2015-09-01 03:58:30','',251,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=1497',17,'page','',0),(1499,11,'2015-08-31 20:43:35','2015-09-01 03:43:35','<h1>ACES Director</h1>\r\n<strong>JOB DESCRIPTION</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Title:</strong>                          ACES Director\r\n\r\n<strong>Supervisor:</strong>               Program Workshop Coordinator\r\n\r\n<strong>Compensation:         </strong>DOE\r\n\r\n<strong>Status:                        </strong>FTE, Non Exempt + Benefits\r\n\r\n<span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">InnVision Shelter Network (IVSN) is a social enterprise committed to providing interim housing (shelter) and support services that create opportunities for homeless families and individuals to re-establish self-sufficiency and to return to permanent homes. Since 1987, our methodology for success has delivered consistent results for homeless families and individuals. Over 90 percent of transitional family graduates return to permanent housing. We are committed to employee satisfaction and the ongoing development of a work culture and environment that increases and maintains morale, productivity, engagement, and the attraction and retention of superior people.</span>\r\n\r\nThe Director will be charged with launching a new program called ACES -- Achieving Career and Educational Success. ACES aims to help children, young adults, and their families who have experienced the trauma and uncertainty of homelessness explore higher education and career opportunities.\r\n\r\nUsing a vetted curriculum created for IVSN, children and adults participate in activities, workshops, field trips, and discussions to spark their interest and explore educational and career opportunities they may not have realized were available to them. These activities, both STEM focused and career oriented, are designed to educate and build employment and academic skills, as well as self-awareness and confidence. The Director will fully implement and manage the curriculum at our 6 family shelters and provide ongoing support, make appropriate modifications to the curriculum, and implement program metrics. This is an exciting opportunity for a self-starter to take IVSN\'s successful children\'s programming to the next level.\r\n\r\n<strong>PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">BA degree in education, child development, or related strongly field recommended\r\n</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Strong leadership skills, experience in developing and managing programs serving at risk individuals, families, and children</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Ability to supervise and train staff and volunteers that will be working with children and provide coaching on how to deal with children\'s behavioral and learning challenges</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Sensitivity and understanding of different learning styles and learning difficulties in adults and children </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Knowledge of issues surrounding homelessness including, contributing factors and challenges homeless families and individuals face, especially children</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Strong analytical and strategic thinking skills; Excel and PowerPoint knowledge preferred</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Strong written and oral communication required, including oral presentations</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Ability to understand and grow in personnel management, and statistical trends and budget analysis</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Performance-driven attitude, with high standards and a proven ability to manage projects, achieve established goals and milestones</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Ability to influence without authority and to make progress in ambiguous situations</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>How to Apply:           </strong>\r\n\r\nInterested parties should send a cover letter and resume to <a href=\"mailto:jobs@ivsn.org\">jobs@ivsn.org</a>','ACES Director','','publish','closed','open','','aces-director','','','2015-08-31 20:45:02','2015-09-01 03:45:02','',251,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=1499',4,'page','',0),(1500,11,'2015-08-31 20:48:42','2015-09-01 03:48:42','<h1>Residential Services Coordinator</h1>\r\n<strong>JOB DESCRIPTION</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Title:</strong>                          Residential Services Coordinator\r\n\r\n<strong>Program/Department:</strong> InnVision Shelter Network, First Step for Families\r\n\r\n<strong>Compensation:         </strong>$12.50\r\n\r\n<strong>Status:                        </strong>Non Exempt hourly\r\n\r\n<strong>Program Description:</strong>\r\nFirst Step for Families is an IVSN shelter dedicated to helping families transition to permanent housing and self-sufficiency. We provide opportunities that build brighter futures for the next generation.\r\n\r\nInnVision Shelter Network (IVSN) is the leading provider of shelter/housing and supportive services across Silicon Valley and the San Francisco Peninsula. IVSN operates 17 sites from San Jose to Daly City, providing interim and stabilization shelter, permanent supportive housing, outreach, rapid re-housing, and homelessness prevention services.\r\n<strong>Preferred Qualifications: </strong>\r\nThis is an entry level position that will help you gain real life work experience working with the homeless and serving marginalized populations. We are seeking passionate, team orientated individuals who have a real desire to serve our community and help fight against homelessness.\r\n\r\nA minimum of high school diploma or GED required. A BA/BS in Social Services, Education a plus. Personal or professional experience/education working with mental health clients a plus. Bilingual/Spanish speaking preferred, but not mandatory.\r\n\r\n<strong>Position Summary: </strong>\r\n\r\nThe Residential Services Coordinator’s (RSC) primary role and responsibility is to provide safety supervision of program participants; and, work collaboratively with other staff in assisting clients towards the goals of permanent housing and stable income. Successful RSC’s will demonstrate a strong attention to detail, multi-tasking, and diplomatic limit setting. Duties include, but are not limited to: client exit and entry supervision, monitor client activities ensuring program rules are abided, answering phones, accepting donations and helping maintain cordial neighborhood relations.\r\n\r\n<strong>How to Apply:           </strong>\r\n\r\nInterested parties should send a cover letter and resume to <a href=\"mailto:jobs@ivsn.org\">jobs@ivsn.org</a>','Residential Services Coordinator','','publish','closed','open','','residential-services-coordinator','','','2015-08-31 20:48:42','2015-09-01 03:48:42','',251,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=1500',3,'page','',0),(1501,11,'2015-08-31 20:52:04','2015-09-01 03:52:04','<h1>Case Manager</h1>\r\n<strong>JOB DESCRIPTION</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Title:</strong>                        Case Manager\r\n\r\n<strong>Supervisor:</strong>            Program Director\r\n\r\n<strong>Compensation:        </strong>DOE\r\n\r\n<strong>Status:                        </strong>Full Time/Non-Exempt\r\n\r\nAre you a socially conscience individual with a genuine need to serve the homeless community in San Mateo County? Are you looking for hands on job opportunity that takes you outdoors, interacting with homeless individuals in their environment? Do you enjoy helping others in need? If so, then Innvision Shelter Network needs you! InnVision Shelter Network is looking for a motivated individual with a “can do” attitude to fill the role of a Housing Programs case manager.\r\n\r\nInnVision Shelter Network (IVSN) is one of the largest and most effective providers of shelter/housing and supportive services across Silicon Valley and the San Francisco Peninsula. IVSN operates over 18 major sites from San Jose to Daly City, providing emergency, transitional, and permanent supportive housing, along with a breadth of supportive resources to help clients secure a place to call home. The organization serves thousands of homeless clients annually through its \"Beyond the Bed\" service model -- a proven methodology that has historically delivered a 90% success rate in returning program graduates to permanent housing and self-sufficiency.\r\n\r\n<strong>Qualifications: </strong>Bachelor’s degree in social work or related field. Minimum two years experience serving homeless families and/or individuals in crisis. Excellent interpersonal skills and ability to interact effectively with other agencies, and a familiarity with issues of substance abuse and domestic violence. Bilingual English/Spanish is highly desirable. Understanding of the issues faced by low-income populations. Must be able to work well independently and in a fast paced environment. Reliable transportation, car insurance and a valid driver’s license is required.<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Responsibilities: </strong>The Case Manager assists clients participating in our programs in San Mateo and Santa Clara County to maintain stable housing and self-sufficiency. In addition, the Case Manager will also work with clients to locate housing, providing housing search education and conducting landlord outreach in the community to increase housing options for our clients. It is also expected that this position assist with special events and administrative duties as needed.\r\n\r\n<strong>Duties:</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><strong>Case Management: </strong>Provide case management services to families and individuals who have entered any one of our rental subsidy programs in SMC Conduct home visits, intakes, assessments, and weekly appointments to assist participants in meeting their goals and self-sufficiency. Assess needs, establish service contracts specifying goals and tasks, provide information and referrals, job development, housing search, life skills training, crisis intervention, and advocacy as needed. Develop and maintain positive relationships with landlords in the community to assist clients in obtaining and maintaining permanent housing. Maintain case files ensuring files are up-to-date, thorough, and accurate. Perform data entry on a consistent basis paying close attention to detail to ensure all data is quality and clean data. Thoroughly and timely document client progress and interactions in a concise and professional manner.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol start=\"2\">\r\n	<li><strong>Program Development: </strong>Assist Manager of Housing Services in planning and implementing client workshops, support groups, and special events. Participate in program development, both within the program and agency-wide. Develop and maintain strong community ties and help clients productively engage the community and maximize available resources. Maintain program statistics and assist in preparing reports.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Job Development:</strong> Assess participants’ work readiness, make referrals, and provide job search skills training. Research and distribute job opportunities. Develop contacts with potential employers. Maintain professional relationships with referral agencies.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol start=\"4\">\r\n	<li><strong>Housing Initiatives: </strong>Work with staff to conduct outreach to landlords in the community to increase housing opportunities for our clients. Assist with the development of housing search curriculum and other informational materials to provide education and promote awareness on housing trends and practices. Provide housing search education to teach clients how to conduct an effective housing search and how to present themselves to landlords.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol start=\"5\">\r\n	<li><strong>Meetings: </strong>Meet weekly with staff to coordinate delivery of services. Meet weekly with supervisor for supervision. Participate in meetings with other community agencies. Attend staff trainings, All Staff meetings, and other meetings as requested. Fill other reasonable requests as made by supervisor, including assistance across program lines.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol start=\"6\">\r\n	<li><strong>Other: </strong>Assist in maintaining a clean and safe environment. Other duties as assigned.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<strong>How to Apply:           </strong>\r\n\r\nInterested parties should send a cover letter and resume to <a href=\"mailto:jobs@ivsn.org\">jobs@ivsn.org</a>','Case Manager','','publish','closed','open','','case-manager','','','2015-08-31 20:52:49','2015-09-01 03:52:49','',251,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=1501',2,'page','',0),(1502,11,'2015-08-31 20:56:09','2015-09-01 03:56:09','<h1>Manager, Grant &amp; Contract Compliance</h1>\r\n<strong>JOB DESCRIPTION</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Title:</strong>                       Manager, Grant &amp; Contract Compliance\r\n\r\n<strong>Supervisor:</strong>            Sr. Director, Grants, Contracts, &amp;  Donor Database\r\n\r\n<strong>Status:                        </strong>Full-Time, Exempt\r\n\r\nInnVision Shelter Network  (IVSN) is a social enterprise committed to providing interim housing (shelter) and support services that create opportunities for homeless families and individuals to re-establish self-sufficiency and to return to stable housing. Since 1987, our methodology for success has delivered consistent results for homeless families and individuals. Over 90 percent of families completing our transitional housing program return to stable housing and self-sufficiency.\r\n\r\nIVSN is an innovative, cutting-edge, non-profit organization which embodies the entrepreneurial energy of an emerging growth company. The executive team is committed to employee satisfaction and the on-going development of a work culture and environment that increases and maintains morale, productivity, engagement, and the attraction and retention of superior people.\r\n\r\n<strong>PRIMARY DUTIES</strong>\r\n\r\nThe successful Manager, Grant &amp; Contract Compliance is a motivated, team-oriented individual responsible for overseeing all IVSN grant and contract execution, implementation, reporting, and close-out processes. The Manager, Grant &amp; Contract Compliance works closely with the Development, Finance, Program, and Compliance Teams to steward funders in order to achieve the fundraising goals of IVSN’s operating and strategic plans. This is a full-time, exempt position; some evenings and weekends required. Specific duties:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Review RFA and RFP solicitations and participate in proposal writing, preparation, and submission</li>\r\n	<li>Attend RFA and RFP information sessions across Bay Area region</li>\r\n	<li>Lead contract execution, kick-off, modification, and close-out processes</li>\r\n	<li>Participate in contract monitoring, e.g. spend-down, with appropriate Finance, Program, and internal point persons for all grant- and contract-related questions</li>\r\n	<li>Maintain “Circle of Life” public and private grant and contract database and reporting tracking tools</li>\r\n	<li>Provide cross-functional contract expertise in contract execution, implementation, and administration</li>\r\n	<li>Lead and manage public and private grant and contract updates and reporting, collaborating and coordinating with Program, Finance, and Compliance Teams for accurate, on-time submissions</li>\r\n	<li>Participate in writing, preparation, and submission of public and private Letters of Intent and proposals, including drafting creative, engaging cases for support</li>\r\n	<li>Organize and facilitate weekly grant and contract Kick-Off meeting with cross-functional organization representation</li>\r\n	<li>Maintain accurate and complete grant and contract records in electronic and paper formats</li>\r\n	<li>Provide regular updates of grant and contract activity, deadlines, and awards/declines</li>\r\n	<li>Participate in strategic planning, development team, and quarterly business review meetings</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>QUALIFICATIONS</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>BA degree</li>\r\n	<li>Experience managing grants and contracts, including obtaining approvals, working with multiple internal and external constituents, and negotiating contract amendments</li>\r\n	<li>Exceptional organizational, analytical, critical-thinking, and prioritization skills</li>\r\n	<li>Excellent, proactive interpersonal communication skills</li>\r\n	<li>Performance-driven attitude, with high standards and a proven ability to achieve established goals and milestones</li>\r\n	<li>Proven ability to work independently with multiple deadlines in a fast-paced environment</li>\r\n	<li>Raiser’s Edge experience preferred</li>\r\n	<li>English fluency required</li>\r\n	<li>Strong technical skill with Microsoft Office suite</li>\r\n	<li>Reliable transportation and access to personal vehicle required</li>\r\n	<li>Commitment to IVSN mission and values</li>\r\n</ul>','Manager, Grant & Contract Compliance','','publish','closed','open','','manager-grant-contract-compliance','','','2015-08-31 20:56:09','2015-09-01 03:56:09','',251,'http://www.ivsn.org/?page_id=1502',1,'page','',0),(1503,11,'2015-10-19 15:23:10','2015-10-19 22:23:10','<h1 class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Plan Your Holiday Giving and Volunteering Now!</span></h1>\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Generous support from the community during the holiday season is vital to creating a warm and meaningful experience </span><span class=\"s1\">for thousands of homeless adults and children in IVSN programs. Start planning now for ways you can help this year!</span></p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Questions? Contact our Volunteer Associate Jessie Ellington at <a href=\"mailto:jellington@ivsn.org\"><span class=\"s2\">jellington@ivsn.org</span></a> or (650) 685-5880 ext. 180.<img class=\"wp-image-1504 aligncenter\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Carolands-Holiday-Party_Children.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"450\" height=\"300\" /></span></p>\n\n<div align=\"center\">\n\n<hr align=\"center\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"1\" width=\"100%\" />\n\n</div>\n<h2>Give</h2>\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Give a Financial Contribution</strong></p>\n<p class=\"p2\">IVSN relies on generous financial support from the community. Your gift ensures that we may continue to provide high quality, effective services year-round. <a href=\"http://ivsn.wpengine.com/donate/\">Donate Now</a></p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Donate in Honor of a Friend or Family Member</strong></p>\n<p class=\"p2\">Make a financial donation to IVSN in honor of a loved one. We will mail the honoree a special holiday card with artwork created by children at our shelters. <a href=\"http://ivsn.wpengine.com/donate/\">Donate Now</a></p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong><a href=\"https://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/form73/index.html?1444862360261\" target=\"_blank\">Host a “Party with a Purpose”</a></strong></p>\n<p class=\"p2\">In lieu of traditional presents, ask your friends, family, or coworkers to bring a cash gift for neighbors in need to your next holiday gathering.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong><a href=\"https://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/form73/index.html?1444862360261\" target=\"_blank\">Adopt-a-Household</a></strong></p>\n<p class=\"p2\">Every IVSN client participating in housing services will receive two holiday gift wishes. You can make these wishes come true by “adopting” a family or individual. Purchase a single gift, or shop for a whole family!</p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong><a href=\"https://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/form73/index.html?1444862360261\" target=\"_blank\">Donate a Thanksgiving or Holiday Dinner Basket</a></strong></p>\n<p class=\"p2\">With your donation of gift cards and/or dinner baskets, every family in IVSN programs will be able to enjoy a holiday meal together. To participate by donating a Holiday Dinner Basket, email <span class=\"s1\">Jessie Ellington at </span><span class=\"s1\"><a href=\"mailto:jellington@ivsn.org\">jellington@ivsn.org</a></span>.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong><a href=\"https://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/form73/index.html?1444862360261\" target=\"_blank\">Host a Gift Drive</a></strong></p>\n<p class=\"p2\">Ask your friends, family or co-workers to bring gifts for homeless neighbors. Most needed items include gift cards ($30 value), linens, new socks and undergarments.</p>\n\n<h2>Volunteer</h2>\n<strong><a href=\"https://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/form73/index.html?1444862360261\" target=\"_blank\">Plan a Holiday Party at a Shelter</a></strong>\n\nHost a party or a “Cookies &amp; Carols” event at one of our shelter residences with your friends, coworkers, or volunteer group. A festive celebration makes the holidays bright and memorable for our clients. To find availability and sign up to host an event, email <span class=\"s1\">Jessie Ellington at </span><span class=\"s1\"><a href=\"mailto:jellington@ivsn.org\">jellington@ivsn.org</a></span><a href=\"mailto:%20nporras@ivsn.org.\">.</a> <a href=\"http://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/form43/index.html\" target=\"_blank\">\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"https://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/form73/index.html?1444862360261\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Provide and Serve Holiday Meals</strong></a>\n\nGather a group of your friends or coworkers to provide and serve a special meal to our residents. On Thanksgiving Day, Christmas Eve, Christmas Day, New Year’s Eve, or New Year’s Day—in addition to weekends (Saturdays and Sundays) throughout the year.<a href=\"https://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/form73/index.html?1444862360261\" target=\"_blank\">\n</a>\n\n<a title=\"Meal Provider Volunteer Manual\" href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/volunteer/meal-programs/\">Click here to find availability and sign up to provide a meal.</a>\n\n<strong><a href=\"https://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/form73/index.html?1444862360261\" target=\"_blank\">Decorate a Shelter</a></strong>\n\nVolunteer with a group of your friends or colleagues to bring in decorations and turn a shelter into a winter wonderland. To find availability and sign up to decorate a shelter, email <span class=\"s1\">Jessie Ellington at </span><span class=\"s1\"><a href=\"mailto:jellington@ivsn.org\">jellington@ivsn.org</a>.</span><a href=\"http://www.formsite.com/shelternetwork/form43/index.html\" target=\"_blank\">\n</a>\n\n&nbsp;','Holiday Giving','','inherit','closed','open','','216-autosave-v1','','','2015-10-19 15:23:10','2015-10-19 22:23:10','',216,'http://www.ivsn.org/216-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1504,11,'2015-09-02 20:39:12','2015-09-03 03:39:12','','Carolands Holiday Party_Children','','inherit','closed','open','','carolands-holiday-party_children','','','2015-09-02 20:39:12','2015-09-03 03:39:12','',216,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Carolands-Holiday-Party_Children.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1506,11,'2015-09-02 20:59:37','2015-09-03 03:59:37','','Achieving Career and Educational Success Program','','publish','closed','closed','','1506','','','2015-10-18 22:05:52','2015-10-19 05:05:52','',33,'http://www.ivsn.org/?p=1506',11,'nav_menu_item','',0),(1508,11,'2015-09-03 20:16:43','2015-09-04 03:16:43','','Sponsor Logos 9.3.15','','inherit','closed','open','','website-logos-9-3-15','','','2015-09-03 20:16:59','2015-09-04 03:16:59','',1397,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/website-logos-9.3.15.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1509,11,'2015-09-03 20:24:01','2015-09-04 03:24:01','','website logos 9.3.15','','inherit','closed','open','','website-logos-9-3-15-2','','','2015-09-03 20:24:01','2015-09-04 03:24:01','',1397,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/website-logos-9.3.151.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1510,11,'2015-09-05 18:59:58','2015-09-06 01:59:58','','register now','','inherit','closed','open','','register-now','','','2015-09-05 18:59:58','2015-09-06 01:59:58','',1397,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/register-now.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1516,11,'2015-09-16 20:15:47','2015-09-17 03:15:47','','ivsn_fall newsletter 2015_final_Page_1','','inherit','closed','closed','','ivsn_fall-newsletter-2015_final_page_1','','','2015-09-16 20:15:47','2015-09-17 03:15:47','',250,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ivsn_fall-newsletter-2015_final_Page_1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1517,11,'2015-09-16 20:16:42','2015-09-17 03:16:42','','ivsn_fall newsletter 2015_final','','inherit','closed','closed','','ivsn_fall-newsletter-2015_final','','','2015-09-16 20:16:42','2015-09-17 03:16:42','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/ivsn_fall-newsletter-2015_final.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(1518,11,'2015-09-16 20:21:14','2015-09-17 03:21:14','','ivsn_fall newsletter 2015_final_website','','inherit','closed','closed','','ivsn_fall-newsletter-2015_final_website','','','2015-09-16 20:21:14','2015-09-17 03:21:14','',250,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ivsn_fall-newsletter-2015_final_website.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1519,11,'2015-09-16 20:25:35','2015-09-17 03:25:35','','ivsn_fall newsletter 2015_final_website','','inherit','closed','closed','','ivsn_fall-newsletter-2015_final_website-2','','','2015-09-16 20:25:35','2015-09-17 03:25:35','',250,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ivsn_fall-newsletter-2015_final_website1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1522,12,'2015-09-21 14:24:50','2015-09-21 21:24:50','<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1146 size-large\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/DSC_7637-1024x685.jpg\" alt=\"DSC_7637\" width=\"550\" height=\"367\" /></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"http://14345.thankyou4caring.org/ivsn/ride-to-end-homelessness-2015\"><img class=\"wp-image-1083 size-medium aligncenter\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Join-Us-button-320x72.png\" alt=\"Join Us button\" width=\"320\" height=\"72\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1086\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"320\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1086 size-medium\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/IMG_5207-320x365.jpg\" alt=\"IVSNers, Eli, Eric, and Dwight \" width=\"320\" height=\"365\" /> Left to right: IVSNers, Eli, Eric, and Dwight[/caption]\r\n\r\n<strong>What: </strong>\r\n\r\nHosted by the IVSN <a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/about/nextgen/\">NextGen Advisory Board</a>, the <em>Ride to End Homelessness</em> is intended to promote awareness of – and solutions for – homelessness. It is a reminder to our community that every night in San Mateo and Santa Clara Counties, 7,000 people are unsheltered.\r\n\r\n<strong>On Sunday, October 25, at 8:30am, </strong>professional and amateur cyclists and their families and supporters will join together for a day of fun, food, and of course, riding.\r\n\r\nRiders will have the option to choose between three routes (12 miles, 25 miles, or 34 miles) with various start times. The routes are:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.strava.com/routes/3344782\" target=\"_blank\">Family</a>: Start time 10:30am</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.strava.com/routes/2186641\" target=\"_blank\">Intermediate</a>: Start time 9:30am</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.strava.com/routes/2186619\" target=\"_blank\">Advanced</a>: Start time 9am</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>When: </strong>\r\n\r\n8:30am, Sunday, October 25, 2015\r\n\r\n<strong>Where:</strong>\r\n\r\nFlood Park in Menlo Park. Address: <strong>215 Bay Road</strong><strong>, Menlo Park, CA 94025</strong>\r\n\r\nNote: There is a $6 daily fee to park in the park.\r\n\r\n<strong>Who: </strong>\r\n\r\nIVSN staff, volunteers, friends, and supporters from the community.\r\n\r\n<strong>Donations:</strong>\r\n\r\nAll proceeds raised from The Ride to End Homelessness will support InnVision Shelter Network\'s mission to return local homeless individuals and families to permanent housing and self-sufficiency. <strong>We ask that all riders donate a suggested minimum donation of $25, as well as raise at least $100 from supporters.</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Donation Matching!</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>All donations from new donors will be matched 1:1 by the Sobrato Family Foundation!</li>\r\n	<li>Many employers offer matching donations for employees that donate to charitable causes. Ask your employer for a matching gift form!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Use the links below to donate, see complete details about the ride, and sign up to ride or volunteer!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">  <a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/The-Ride-to-End-Homelessness-Flyer-2015.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1084\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Complete-ride-Dets-button-320x72.png\" alt=\"Complete ride Dets button\" width=\"150\" height=\"34\" /></a> <a href=\" http://14345.thankyou4caring.org/ivsn/ride-to-end-homelessness-2015\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"wp-image-1108 alignnone\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Volunteer-button-320x72.png\" alt=\"Volunteer button\" width=\"150\" height=\"34\" /></a> <a href=\"http://14345.thankyou4caring.org/ivsn/ride-to-end-homelessness-2015\"><img class=\"wp-image-1083 alignnone\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Join-Us-button-320x72.png\" alt=\"Join Us button\" width=\"150\" height=\"34\" /></a> <a href=\" http://14345.thankyou4caring.org/ivsn/ride-to-end-homelessness-2015\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1078\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Donate-Now-button-320x72.png\" alt=\"Donate Now button\" width=\"150\" height=\"34\" /></a>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">Some of our riders include...</h2>\r\n<strong><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-1107\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Eli-Riding-320x425.png\" alt=\"Eli Riding\" width=\"320\" height=\"425\" />Name of Rider:</strong>\r\n\r\nEli Latimerlo\r\n\r\n<strong>I am riding to end homelessness because...</strong>\r\n\r\n“Everyday, IVSN is making a profound difference in the lives of a thousand of the most vulnerable citizens of San Mateo and Santa Clara Counties. I’ve experienced it first hand. The work IVSN is doing is disruptive to the patterns of homelessness. It’s a cause that I believe in.”\r\n\r\n<strong>Message to Others:</strong>\r\n\r\nThe Ride to End Homelessness is a bike ride. It is one thing that many of us can do to make a difference in the lives of the very poorest of our neighbors. It needn’t be the cause that drives you to realize your purpose in this life, but it could be. Join us, and make a small step in the direction of your calling.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1116\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"320\"]<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-1116\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Rider-Charlie-320x228.jpg\" alt=\"I found this shelter during a crossing of the United States on bicycle. Protected from the rain, I found solace in rock \'n\' roll! Whatever it takes, right?\" width=\"320\" height=\"228\" /> I found this shelter during a crossing of the United States on bicycle. Protected from the rain, I found solace in rock \'n\' roll! Whatever it takes, right?[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong><span class=\"s1\"><b>Name of the Rider:</b></span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Charlie Walker</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><strong>I am riding to end homelessness because...</strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">I am riding to help those in need of shelter. Nothing in life is more basic than finding a safe haven, protected from the elements, guarded against the unknown, and getting nurtured to carry on.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong><span class=\"s1\"><b>Message to Others:</b></span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Good people need to stick together, at all times! That is what InnVision Shelter Network is all about. Come join us if you can, cheer us on from afar, or just pray for us as we brave the elements. Thank you for your support.</span></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-1126\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/image001-320x240.jpg\" alt=\"image001\" width=\"320\" height=\"240\" />\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><b>Name of Rider:</b></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Eric Welsh</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><b>I am riding to end homelessness because….</b></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">We live in one of the richest areas in the country.  It is a crime that so many people go unhoused each night.  I want to bring this issue to the forefront of the cycling communities minds.     </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><b>Message to others:</b></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">To all my riding brethren out on the road: We are extremely lucky to have the means and opportunity to ride in such an amazing area!  This really is a mecca for cycling.  Sometimes we take this for granted and do not realize so many people here are struggling to feed and shelter themselves.  I hope you can all take a moment and read more about the wonderful work InnVision Shelter Network does to help end this problem!    </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-1130\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Sara-Headley-TIBCO-indiv.-320x339.jpg\" alt=\"Sara Headley - TIBCO indiv.\" width=\"320\" height=\"339\" /></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><strong>Name of Rider:</strong> Sara Headley</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong><span class=\"s1\"><b>I am riding to end homelessness because...</b></span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">I want to increase awareness of the families and individuals in need, especially during the holiday season. Taking the time out of our busy schedules is the least we can do to show our support. As a professional rider, it is refreshing to ride for a cause much bigger than my daily training ride. It adds a special glimmer of hope to my life, but more importantly, to those we are representing on that day. If we can gather others interested in helping IVSN fight homelessness, we have accomplished something very special indeed. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong><span class=\"s1\"><b>Message to Others: </b></span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Bicycles have the magical power to bring people together in fun and fitness. Pictures from the event will show how people joining together in a healthy activity can create a flow of ideas and determination to fight homelessness in the Bay Area. No matter how young or old, rich or poor, one can always find joy on 2 wheels!</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><b><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-1136\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/IMG_5560-320x426.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_5560\" width=\"320\" height=\"426\" /></b></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><b>Name of Rider:</b></span><span class=\"s2\"><b> </b>Dwight Powery</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p3\"><span class=\"s3\"><b>I am riding to end homelessness because….</b></span><span class=\"s1\"><b> </b>I want to bring awareness to the homelessness situation in one of the richest areas in the country.  Many of us are not aware that over 7,000 people </span>(including children) live in homelessness every night and we have a responsibility to fight for what is a basic human right.  IVSN is at the forefront of not only bringing that awareness, but also bringing a solution to those in need.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p3\"><span class=\"s3\"><b>Message to others:</b></span><span class=\"s1\"> Homelessness takes on many forms within our community – from those that we see to those that we don’t see.  When you cycle, you pass a little slower by the pockets that you miss when you drive. Will you join InnVision Shelter Network in bringing the voice to those that we don’t see?</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><em>And many more... Thank you to all 2015 riders and supporters!\r\n</em></p>','Ride to End Homelessness 2015','','publish','closed','closed','','ride-to-end-homelessness-2015','','','2015-09-26 16:22:18','2015-09-26 23:22:18','',0,'http://www.ivsn.org/?post_type=event&#038;p=1522',1,'event','',0),(1524,5,'2015-09-23 18:05:49','2015-09-24 01:05:49','<h1><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-403\" src=\"http://ivsn.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/volunteer_food_meal_service-320x241.jpg\" alt=\"volunteer_food_meal_service\" width=\"320\" height=\"241\" />Meal Programs</h1>\nYour volunteer group can provide and serve healthy and nutritious meals to homeless families and individuals at several InnVision Shelter Network facilities.\n\nPlease note that we request your group buy and prepare the food for our clients; IVSN’s housing sites are not “soup kitchens,” and as such we ask volunteers to donate the food and their time to serve our clients.\n<h2>Meal Provider Volunteer Manual</h2>\nWe recommend you review the <a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/Meal-Provider-Volunteer-Manual-020415.pdf\">Meal Provider Volunteer Manual</a> for site-specific details and guidance on how to ensure a fun and productive volunteer experience.\n<h2>Sign Up to Provide a Meal</h2>\nTo provide a meal for <strong>Commercial Street Inn </strong> in San Jose, view the <a href=\"http://volunteer.ivsn.org/IVSNCalendar.aspx?CLR=14\">Commercial Street Inn Meal Provider Calendar</a> and register for an available meal.\n\nTo provide a meal for <strong>First Step for Families</strong> in San Mateo, view the<a href=\"http://volunteer.ivsn.org/IVSNCalendar.aspx?CLR=9\"> First Step Meal Provider Calendar</a> and register for an available meal.\n\nTo provide a meal for <strong>Julian Street Inn *</strong> in San Jose, view the <a title=\"Julian Street Inn Meal Provider Calendar \" href=\"http://volunteer.ivsn.org/IVSNCalendar.aspx?LocID=22\">Julian Street Inn Meal Provider Calendar</a> and register for an available meal.\n\nTo provide a meal for <strong>Maple Street Shelter </strong> in Redwood City, view the <a href=\"http://volunteer.ivsn.org/IVSNCalendar.aspx?LocID=53\">Maple St. Meal Provider Calendar</a> and register for an available meal.\n\nTo provide a meal for <strong>Montgomery Street Inn *</strong><strong> </strong> in San Jose, view the <a href=\"http://volunteer.ivsn.org/IVSNCalendar.aspx?LocID=24\">Montgomery Street Inn Meal Provider Calendar</a> and register for an available meal.\n\nTo provide a meal for <strong>Villa Shelter </strong> in San Jose, view the <a title=\"Villa Meal Provider Calendar\" href=\"http://volunteer.ivsn.org/IVSNCalendar.aspx?LocID=26\">Villa Meal Provider Calendar</a> and register for an available meal.\n\n<strong>*must be 18 years of age to volunteer at this site. </strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">To provide a meal for all other sites, please contact </span><span class=\"s1\">Jessie Ellington at <a href=\"mailto:Jellington@ivsn.org\"><span class=\"s2\">Jellington@ivsn.org</span></a></span><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">.</span>','Meal Programs','','inherit','closed','closed','','188-autosave-v1','','','2015-09-23 18:05:49','2015-09-24 01:05:49','',188,'http://www.ivsn.org/188-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1526,11,'2015-09-23 23:27:40','2015-09-24 06:27:40','','sponsor logos 9.23.15','','inherit','closed','closed','','sponsor-logos-9-23-15','','','2015-09-23 23:27:40','2015-09-24 06:27:40','',1397,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/sponsor-logos-9.23.15.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1528,18,'2015-09-24 15:13:59','2015-09-24 22:13:59','<h1><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-414\" src=\"http://ivsn.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/services_family_housing_first-320x240.jpg\" alt=\"services_family_housing_first\" width=\"320\" height=\"240\" />Housing First Program</h1>\n<h2>Housing First rapidly transitions people from homelessness into permanent housing.</h2>\nThrough Housing First, clients who are homeless but have a reliable income receive move-in assistance and shallow rent subsidies.\n\nBy providing financial assistance to move directly into permanent housing (accompanied by case management and supportive services), clients are able to <i>bypass</i> the shelter stay altogether. This model is not only fiscally efficient from an organizational standpoint, but also circumvents the psychological impact of short-term housing solutions, which can be particularly devastating for children.\n\nAdditionally, the Housing First program helps preserve urgently needed shelter beds for those most in need.\n<h2>Eligibility</h2>\nTo qualify for Housing First, clients must be homeless, working or gaining reliable income, but earning less than 200% of the national poverty level. Families and individuals may receive up to $2,000 for move-in assistance, depending on income, and a 50% rent subsidy for up to six months. After securing permanent housing, clients receive follow-up case management to ensure their long-term success.\n\nFor questions about the Housing First program, contact Teresa Brown at (650) 315-3503 or <a href=\"mailto:tbrown@ivsn.org\">tbrown@ivsn.org</a>.\n\n&nbsp;','Housing First Program','','inherit','closed','closed','','119-autosave-v1','','','2015-09-24 15:13:59','2015-09-24 22:13:59','',119,'http://www.ivsn.org/119-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1529,12,'2015-09-26 16:21:57','2015-09-26 23:21:57','<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1146 size-large\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/DSC_7637-1024x685.jpg\" alt=\"DSC_7637\" width=\"550\" height=\"367\" /></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"http://14345.thankyou4caring.org/ivsn/ride-to-end-homelessness-2015\"><img class=\"wp-image-1083 size-medium aligncenter\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Join-Us-button-320x72.png\" alt=\"Join Us button\" width=\"320\" height=\"72\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1086\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"320\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1086 size-medium\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/IMG_5207-320x365.jpg\" alt=\"IVSNers, Eli, Eric, and Dwight \" width=\"320\" height=\"365\" /> Left to right: IVSNers, Eli, Eric, and Dwight[/caption]\r\n\r\n<strong>What: </strong>\r\n\r\nHosted by the IVSN <a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/about/nextgen/\">NextGen Advisory Board</a>, the <em>Ride to End Homelessness</em> is intended to promote awareness of – and solutions for – homelessness. It is a reminder to our community that every night in San Mateo and Santa Clara Counties, 7,000 people are unsheltered.\r\n\r\n<strong>On Sunday, October 25, at 8:30am, </strong>professional and amateur cyclists and their families and supporters will join together for a day of fun, food, and of course, riding.\r\n\r\nRiders will have the option to choose between three routes (12 miles, 25 miles, or 34 miles) with various start times. The routes are:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.strava.com/routes/3344782\" target=\"_blank\">Family</a>: Start time 10:30am</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.strava.com/routes/2186641\" target=\"_blank\">Intermediate</a>: Start time 9:30am</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.strava.com/routes/2186619\" target=\"_blank\">Advanced</a>: Start time 9am</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>When: </strong>\r\n\r\n8:30am, Sunday, October 25, 2015\r\n\r\n<strong>Where:</strong>\r\n\r\nFlood Park in Menlo Park. Address: <strong>215 Bay Road</strong><strong>, Menlo Park, CA 94025</strong>\r\n\r\nNote: There is a $6 daily fee to park in the park.\r\n\r\n<strong>Who: </strong>\r\n\r\nIVSN staff, volunteers, friends, and supporters from the community.\r\n\r\n<strong>Donations:</strong>\r\n\r\nAll proceeds raised from The Ride to End Homelessness will support InnVision Shelter Network\'s mission to return local homeless individuals and families to permanent housing and self-sufficiency. <strong>We ask that all riders donate a suggested minimum donation of $25, as well as raise at least $100 from supporters.</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Donation Matching!</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>All donations from new donors will be matched 1:1 by the Sobrato Family Foundation!</li>\r\n	<li>Many employers offer matching donations for employees that donate to charitable causes. Ask your employer for a matching gift form!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Use the links below to donate, see complete details about the ride, and sign up to ride or volunteer!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">  <a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/The-Ride-to-End-Homelessness-Flyer-2015.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1084\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Complete-ride-Dets-button-320x72.png\" alt=\"Complete ride Dets button\" width=\"150\" height=\"34\" /></a> <a href=\" http://14345.thankyou4caring.org/ivsn/ride-to-end-homelessness-2015\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"wp-image-1108 alignnone\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Volunteer-button-320x72.png\" alt=\"Volunteer button\" width=\"150\" height=\"34\" /></a> <a href=\"http://14345.thankyou4caring.org/ivsn/ride-to-end-homelessness-2015\"><img class=\"wp-image-1083 alignnone\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Join-Us-button-320x72.png\" alt=\"Join Us button\" width=\"150\" height=\"34\" /></a> <a href=\" http://14345.thankyou4caring.org/ivsn/ride-to-end-homelessness-2015\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1078\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Donate-Now-button-320x72.png\" alt=\"Donate Now button\" width=\"150\" height=\"34\" /></a>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">Some of our riders include...</h2>\r\n<strong><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-1107\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Eli-Riding-320x425.png\" alt=\"Eli Riding\" width=\"320\" height=\"425\" />Name of Rider:</strong>\r\n\r\nEli Latimerlo\r\n\r\n<strong>I am riding to end homelessness because...</strong>\r\n\r\n“Everyday, IVSN is making a profound difference in the lives of a thousand of the most vulnerable citizens of San Mateo and Santa Clara Counties. I’ve experienced it first hand. The work IVSN is doing is disruptive to the patterns of homelessness. It’s a cause that I believe in.”\r\n\r\n<strong>Message to Others:</strong>\r\n\r\nThe Ride to End Homelessness is a bike ride. It is one thing that many of us can do to make a difference in the lives of the very poorest of our neighbors. It needn’t be the cause that drives you to realize your purpose in this life, but it could be. Join us, and make a small step in the direction of your calling.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1116\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"320\"]<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-1116\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Rider-Charlie-320x228.jpg\" alt=\"I found this shelter during a crossing of the United States on bicycle. Protected from the rain, I found solace in rock \'n\' roll! Whatever it takes, right?\" width=\"320\" height=\"228\" /> I found this shelter during a crossing of the United States on bicycle. Protected from the rain, I found solace in rock \'n\' roll! Whatever it takes, right?[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong><span class=\"s1\"><b>Name of the Rider:</b></span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Charlie Walker</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><strong>I am riding to end homelessness because...</strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">I am riding to help those in need of shelter. Nothing in life is more basic than finding a safe haven, protected from the elements, guarded against the unknown, and getting nurtured to carry on.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong><span class=\"s1\"><b>Message to Others:</b></span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Good people need to stick together, at all times! That is what InnVision Shelter Network is all about. Come join us if you can, cheer us on from afar, or just pray for us as we brave the elements. Thank you for your support.</span></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-1126\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/image001-320x240.jpg\" alt=\"image001\" width=\"320\" height=\"240\" />\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><b>Name of Rider:</b></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Eric Welsh</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><b>I am riding to end homelessness because….</b></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">We live in one of the richest areas in the country.  It is a crime that so many people go unhoused each night.  I want to bring this issue to the forefront of the cycling communities minds.     </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><b>Message to others:</b></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">To all my riding brethren out on the road: We are extremely lucky to have the means and opportunity to ride in such an amazing area!  This really is a mecca for cycling.  Sometimes we take this for granted and do not realize so many people here are struggling to feed and shelter themselves.  I hope you can all take a moment and read more about the wonderful work InnVision Shelter Network does to help end this problem!    </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-1130\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Sara-Headley-TIBCO-indiv.-320x339.jpg\" alt=\"Sara Headley - TIBCO indiv.\" width=\"320\" height=\"339\" /></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><strong>Name of Rider:</strong> Sara Headley</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong><span class=\"s1\"><b>I am riding to end homelessness because...</b></span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">I want to increase awareness of the families and individuals in need, especially during the holiday season. Taking the time out of our busy schedules is the least we can do to show our support. As a professional rider, it is refreshing to ride for a cause much bigger than my daily training ride. It adds a special glimmer of hope to my life, but more importantly, to those we are representing on that day. If we can gather others interested in helping IVSN fight homelessness, we have accomplished something very special indeed. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong><span class=\"s1\"><b>Message to Others: </b></span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Bicycles have the magical power to bring people together in fun and fitness. Pictures from the event will show how people joining together in a healthy activity can create a flow of ideas and determination to fight homelessness in the Bay Area. No matter how young or old, rich or poor, one can always find joy on 2 wheels!</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><b><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-1136\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/IMG_5560-320x426.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_5560\" width=\"320\" height=\"426\" /></b></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><b>Name of Rider:</b></span><span class=\"s2\"><b> </b>Dwight Powery</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p3\"><span class=\"s3\"><b>I am riding to end homelessness because….</b></span><span class=\"s1\"><b> </b>I want to bring awareness to the homelessness situation in one of the richest areas in the country.  Many of us are not aware that over 7,000 people </span>(including children) live in homelessness every night and we have a responsibility to fight for what is a basic human right.  IVSN is at the forefront of not only bringing that awareness, but also bringing a solution to those in need.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p3\"><span class=\"s3\"><b>Message to others:</b></span><span class=\"s1\"> Homelessness takes on many forms within our community – from those that we see to those that we don’t see.  When you cycle, you pass a little slower by the pockets that you miss when you drive. Will you join InnVision Shelter Network in bringing the voice to those that we don’t see?</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><em>And many more... Thank you to all 2015 riders and supporters!\r\n</em></p>','Ride to End Homelessness 2015','','inherit','closed','closed','','1522-autosave-v1','','','2015-09-26 16:21:57','2015-09-26 23:21:57','',1522,'http://www.ivsn.org/1522-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1530,12,'2015-09-26 16:13:08','2015-09-26 23:13:08','','The Ride to End Homelessness Flyer 2015','','inherit','closed','closed','','the-ride-to-end-homelessness-flyer-2015','','','2015-09-26 16:13:08','2015-09-26 23:13:08','',1522,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/The-Ride-to-End-Homelessness-Flyer-2015.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(1532,11,'2015-10-06 16:50:07','2015-10-06 23:50:07','','sponsor logos 10.6.15','','inherit','closed','closed','','sponsor-logos-10-6-15','','','2015-10-06 16:50:07','2015-10-06 23:50:07','',1397,'http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/sponsor-logos-10.6.15.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1538,12,'2015-10-09 13:33:27','2015-10-09 20:33:27','<h1>Case Manager</h1>\r\n<strong>JOB DESCRIPTION</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Title:</strong>                        Case Manager\r\n\r\n<strong>Supervisor:</strong>            Program Director\r\n\r\n<strong>Compensation:        </strong>DOE\r\n\r\n<strong>Status:                        </strong>Full Time/Non-Exempt\r\n\r\nAre you a socially conscience individual with a genuine need to serve the homeless community in San Mateo County? Are you looking for hands on job opportunity that takes you outdoors, interacting with homeless individuals in their environment? Do you enjoy helping others in need? If so, then Innvision Shelter Network needs you! InnVision Shelter Network is looking for a motivated individual with a “can do” attitude to fill the role of a Housing Programs case manager.\r\n\r\nInnVision Shelter Network (IVSN) is one of the largest and most effective providers of shelter/housing and supportive services across Silicon Valley and the San Francisco Peninsula. IVSN operates over 18 major sites from San Jose to Daly City, providing emergency, transitional, and permanent supportive housing, along with a breadth of supportive resources to help clients secure a place to call home. The organization serves thousands of homeless clients annually through its \"Beyond the Bed\" service model -- a proven methodology that has historically delivered a 90% success rate in returning program graduates to permanent housing and self-sufficiency.\r\n\r\n<strong>Qualifications: </strong>Bachelor’s degree in social work or related field. Minimum two years experience serving homeless families and/or individuals in crisis. Excellent interpersonal skills and ability to interact effectively with other agencies, and a familiarity with issues of substance abuse and domestic violence. Bilingual English/Spanish is highly desirable. Understanding of the issues faced by low-income populations. Must be able to work well independently and in a fast paced environment. Reliable transportation, car insurance and a valid driver’s license is required.<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Responsibilities: </strong>The Case Manager assists clients participating in our programs in San Mateo and Santa Clara County to maintain stable housing and self-sufficiency. In addition, the Case Manager will also work with clients to locate housing, providing housing search education and conducting landlord outreach in the community to increase housing options for our clients. It is also expected that this position assist with special events and administrative duties as needed.\r\n\r\n<strong>Duties:</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><strong>Case Management: </strong>Provide case management services to families and individuals who have entered any one of our rental subsidy programs in SMC Conduct home visits, intakes, assessments, and weekly appointments to assist participants in meeting their goals and self-sufficiency. Assess needs, establish service contracts specifying goals and tasks, provide information and referrals, job development, housing search, life skills training, crisis intervention, and advocacy as needed. Develop and maintain positive relationships with landlords in the community to assist clients in obtaining and maintaining permanent housing. Maintain case files ensuring files are up-to-date, thorough, and accurate. Perform data entry on a consistent basis paying close attention to detail to ensure all data is quality and clean data. Thoroughly and timely document client progress and interactions in a concise and professional manner.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol start=\"2\">\r\n	<li><strong>Program Development: </strong>Assist Manager of Housing Services in planning and implementing client workshops, support groups, and special events. Participate in program development, both within the program and agency-wide. Develop and maintain strong community ties and help clients productively engage the community and maximize available resources. Maintain program statistics and assist in preparing reports.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Job Development:</strong> Assess participants’ work readiness, make referrals, and provide job search skills training. Research and distribute job opportunities. Develop contacts with potential employers. Maintain professional relationships with referral agencies.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol start=\"4\">\r\n	<li><strong>Housing Initiatives: </strong>Work with staff to conduct outreach to landlords in the community to increase housing opportunities for our clients. Assist with the development of housing search curriculum and other informational materials to provide education and promote awareness on housing trends and practices. Provide housing search education to teach clients how to conduct an effective housing search and how to present themselves to landlords.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol start=\"5\">\r\n	<li><strong>Meetings: </strong>Meet weekly with staff to coordinate delivery of services. Meet weekly with supervisor for supervision. Participate in meetings with other community agencies. Attend staff trainings, All Staff meetings, and other meetings as requested. Fill other reasonable requests as made by supervisor, including assistance across program lines.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol start=\"6\">\r\n	<li><strong>Other: </strong>Assist in maintaining a clean and safe environment. Other duties as assigned.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<strong>How to Apply:           </strong>\r\n\r\nInterested parties should send a cover letter and resume to <a href=\"mailto:jobs@ivsn.org\">jobs@ivsn.org</a>','Case Manager','','inherit','closed','closed','','1501-autosave-v1','','','2015-10-09 13:33:27','2015-10-09 20:33:27','',1501,'http://www.ivsn.org/1501-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1539,12,'2015-10-15 16:31:08','2015-10-15 23:31:08','<h1>Jobs</h1>\n<h2>Join the team at InnVision Shelter Network!</h2>\nThank you for your interest in joining our team! IVSN offers employer-paid insurance premiums with nominal cost share, a 401k plan, a comprehensive benefits package (the “Happiness Plan”), and a diverse, fun work environment. If you desire to work with a dedicated, passionate group to make a difference in ending homelessness, IVSN is the right place for you.\n\n<img class=\"wp-image-1557 size-large aligncenter\" src=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Staff1-1024x425.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"228\" />\n<h2>To Apply<b></b></h2>\nTo apply for any of the job openings below, please send your resume to <a href=\"mailto:jobs@ivsn.org\">jobs@ivsn.org</a>. Please list the title of the position in the subject line, and send your resume and cover letter with salary requirements as attachments. No phone calls will be accepted.\n<h2>Open Positions</h2>\n<strong>Programs </strong>\n<ul>\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ACES-Director.doc\">ACES (Achieving Career and Educational Success) Director</a></li>\n	<li>Case Manager positions\n<ul>\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Case-Manager-Outreach.doc\">Outreach</a> (San Mateo County) - 2 positions available</li>\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Case-Manager-Haven.doc\">Haven Family House</a> (Menlo Park) - 2 positions available</li>\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Case-Manager-VA-Specialist-JSI.docx\">VA Specialist, Julian Street Inn</a> (San Jose)</li>\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Case-Manager-JSI.docx\">Julian Street Inn</a> (San Jose)</li>\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Case-Manager-MSI.doc\">Case Manager MSI</a> (San Jose)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Children-Services-Coordinator-CSI.doc\">Children Services Coordinator, Commercial Street Inn</a> (San Jose)</li>\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Program-Administrative-Assistant.doc\">Program Administrative Assistant</a> (San Mateo)</li>\n	<li>Residential Services Coordinator positions\n<ul>\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Residential-Services-Coordinator-First-Step.doc\">First Step for Families</a> (San Mateo)</li>\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Residential-Services-Coordinator-Maple-Street.doc\">Maple Street Shelter</a> (Redwood City)</li>\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Residential-Services-Coordinator-CSI.doc\">Commercial Street Inn</a> (San Jose)</li>\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Residential-Services-Coordinator-JSI.doc\">Julian Street Inn</a> (San Jose)</li>\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Residential-Services-Coordinator-MSI.doc\">Montgomery Street Inn</a> (San Jose)</li>\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Residential-Services-Coordinator-San-Mateo-County-Part-Time-Relief.doc\">Part time/relief (San Mateo County)</a></li>\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Residential-Services-Coordinator-Santa-Clara-County-Part-Time-Relief.doc\">Part time/relief (Santa Clara County)</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Development</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ivsn.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Manager-Grant-and-Contract-Compliance.docx\">Manager, Gr